(2, 'Tulip Festival', 'tulip-festival', '<p>Tulip Festival in Srinagar is a grand affair of natural beauty where flower beds are scattered upon several terraces. Your trip to Kashmir in April 2025 would not be considered complete without visiting Asia&rsquo;s most extensive Tulip Garden. This magnificent festival in Srinagar is celebrated every year with full fervor and joy. The Floriculture Department organizers announced plans to plant 1.5 million tulip bulbs of 62 varieties in 2025 Tulip Garden. The picturesque garden sprawls over 30 hectares. In short, the Tulip Festival in 2025 will take your breath away! This is a detailed guide for Tulip Festival Kashmir for you to decide whether to visit or not and, if yes, what to expect.</p>\r\n<h2>Starting and Ending Dates of Tulip Festival in 2025</h2>\r\n<p>Tulip Festival is hosted in Kashmir Valley during the onset of the Spring Season. You can get ready to be a part of it in April 2025 as the festival will commence from 3rd April to 20th April 2025.</p>\r\n<h2>Timings of Tulip Garden</h2>\r\n<p>The Tulip Garden opens at 8 am and closes at 7 pm.</p>\r\n<h2>Entry Fee at Tulip Garden in 2025</h2>\r\n<p>The entry fee to the garden is INR 25 for children and INR 60 for adults.</p>\r\n<h2>Major Highlights of the Tulip Festival in 2025</h2>\r\n<p>Tulip Festival 2025 is a must-attend event for flower enthusiasts, nature lovers, fans, aficionados, tulip lovers, and tourists worldwide. There are many varieties of these amazing flowers; some are mentioned below. Let&rsquo;s see how many of them you can find at the Tulip Festival.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Standard Tulips</span>&nbsp;-These are the normal tulips available from florists to local gardens.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Double Bloom</span>&nbsp;-Instead of a single petal of a standard tulip, the double bloom has many layers.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Parrot Tuplips</span>&nbsp;-They appear as ruffled petals in various hues depicting the plumage of tropical parrot.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Fringed Tulips</span>&nbsp;-The edges and shape are frilly and fringed.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Bi-Color Standard Tulips</span>&nbsp;-They display a variation in terms of color when compared with the standard tulip.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Rembrandt</span>&nbsp;-pale-colored tall tulips</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Fosteriana Tulips</span>&nbsp;-They vary in height and have pretty buds.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Lily-Flowering Tulips</span>&nbsp;- These flowers have long, pointed petals with an arch at the tips.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Single Late Tulips</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;-Stunning cup-shaped tulips with the widest range of colors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s special about the Tulip Festival Srinagar of 2025?</h2>\r\n<p>There are some added attractions in the Tulip Festival of 2025. Nature has bestowed the garden with more varieties of flowers this year. Moreover, visitors can benefit from surplus facilities like free Wi-Fi, more fountains, washrooms (separate for the specially-abled persons), and drinking points.</p>\r\n<p>More green spaces are included in the garden area keeping in mind the comforts of the tourists. Extra plants like daffodils, hyacinths, narcissus, and other ornamental plants are planted to ornate the area. In addition, the water channels running through the terraces will add charm to the g</p>\r\n<p>Visitors will now be able to buy souvenirs and savor Kashmiri dishes from outside the garden area. This will be possible because of the decorated stalls and kiosks exhibiting the cuisine and handicrafts of Kashmir.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to witness the beautiful Tulip Garden and explore the city, book Kashmir tour packages with Indian Holiday for a smooth and memorable travel experience.</p>\r\n<h3>Places to visit near Tulip Garden Srinagar</h3>\r\n<p>The prime location of the Tulip Garden makes it the most visited place in Srinagar. This park is surrounded by scenic hills, attractive gardens of the Mughal era, and most importantly, it overlooks the awe-inspiring Dal Lake. Given below are some other attractions that lie nearby</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Chashme Shahi Garden &ndash;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;This garden is the center of attraction for housing a natural spring that flows from it.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Pari Mahal &ndash;</span>&nbsp;Overlooking the amazing Chashm-E-Shahi Gardens, this historic monument was once a Buddhist Monastery.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Shankaracharya Temple &ndash;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Soak in the beauty of the snow-laden Pin Panjal Range from this age-old temple situated at 1100 feet.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Dal Lake &ndash;</span>&nbsp;Dal Lake is truly a paradise on Earth. The beauty of this breathtaking lake is beyond description. A Shikara Ride is a must here.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"fw-bold\">Nishat Gardens &ndash;&nbsp;</span>Spotted at a distance of 3.2 km from Tulip Garden, Nishat Bagh is home to long avenues of Cypress and Chinar trees, rare flowers, and fountains.</li>\r\n</ul>', '1741075771.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-04 08:09:31', '2025-04-16 07:30:18'),
(3, 'A Snowy Paradise', 'a-snowy-paradise', '<p><strong>Winter in Kashmir: A Snowy Paradise</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kashmir, often referred to as &ldquo;Paradise on Earth,&rdquo; transforms into a breathtaking winter wonderland as the temperature drops and snow blankets its valleys, mountains, and meadows. Winter in Kashmir is an experience like no other, offering mesmerizing landscapes, adventure sports, and a glimpse into the region&rsquo;s rich culture and traditions.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Beauty of Snow-Covered Kashmir</strong></h3>\r\n<p>As winter arrives, the entire region is draped in pristine white snow, making it look straight out of a fairytale. The majestic Himalayan peaks covered in snow, the frozen lakes, and the quaint villages nestled in the valleys create a serene and picturesque atmosphere. Dal Lake, partially frozen, with shikaras (traditional wooden boats) gliding through the mist, is a sight to behold. The famous Mughal Gardens and the pine-clad mountains of Pahalgam and Gulmarg take on a magical charm during this season.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Gulmarg: The Winter Wonderland</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Gulmarg, known as one of Asia&rsquo;s best ski resorts, is a major attraction during winter. Adventure seekers and skiing enthusiasts from all over the world visit this place to enjoy activities like skiing, snowboarding, and the thrilling Gondola ride, which offers a panoramic view of the snow-covered Pir Panjal range. The crisp mountain air and the enchanting beauty of the surroundings make it a dream destination for winter lovers.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Winter Sports and Adventure Activities</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Kashmir offers a range of exciting winter sports, making it a paradise for adventure lovers. Some of the most popular activities include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Skiing &amp; Snowboarding</strong> &ndash; Gulmarg is the go-to destination for skiing enthusiasts.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sledging &amp; Ice Skating</strong> &ndash; Tourists can enjoy sledging down snowy slopes or skating on frozen surfaces.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Snow Trekking</strong> &ndash; Exploring trails through snow-covered pine forests is a unique experience.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gondola Ride</strong> &ndash; Asia&rsquo;s highest cable car ride in Gulmarg provides an unmatched view of the snowy peaks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>The Charm of Kashmiri Winters</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Winter in Kashmir is not just about scenic beauty and adventure; it is also about experiencing the warmth of Kashmiri hospitality. The traditional Kashmiri attire, <strong>pheran</strong> (a long woolen robe), keeps people warm, while the <strong>kangri</strong> (a small fire pot) provides additional heat during the chilly months. The markets come alive with vibrant Pashmina shawls, handcrafted rugs, and exquisite dry fruits.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Delicious Winter Cuisine</strong></h3>\r\n<p>No trip to Kashmir in winter is complete without indulging in its traditional cuisine. Some must-try dishes include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Harissa</strong> &ndash; A rich and flavorful mutton dish, perfect for keeping warm.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Kahwa</strong> &ndash; A saffron-infused traditional green tea that provides warmth and energy.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rogan Josh</strong> &ndash; A mouthwatering mutton curry infused with aromatic spices.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gushtaba</strong> &ndash; Tender meatballs in a yogurt-based gravy, served during special occasions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Festivals and Celebrations</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Winter in Kashmir is marked by festivals like <strong>Shishur</strong> (traditional winter celebrations) and <strong>Christmas</strong>, especially in the churches of Srinagar and Gulmarg. The start of the New Year sees tourists and locals alike celebrating amidst the snowy landscape.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '1741077182.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-04 08:33:02', '2025-03-04 08:33:02'),
(4, 'Summer in Kashmir', 'summer-in-kashmir', '<p><strong>Summer in Kashmir: A Paradise on Earth</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kashmir, often referred to as the \"Paradise on Earth,\" is a dream destination for travelers. While it remains a year-round attraction, summer in Kashmir is truly enchanting. With lush green valleys, snow-capped mountains, and pleasant weather, it is the perfect escape from the scorching heat of the plains.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Weather in Summer</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Summer in Kashmir lasts from May to August, with temperatures ranging from 15&deg;C to 30&deg;C. Unlike other parts of India, where summer can be unbearably hot, Kashmir offers a refreshing climate. The days are warm yet comfortable, while the nights remain cool and pleasant. This makes it an ideal time for sightseeing, adventure activities, and relaxation.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Top Places to Visit</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Srinagar</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Srinagar, the summer capital of Jammu and Kashmir, is famous for its mesmerizing Dal Lake and Nigeen Lake. The houseboats and Shikara rides offer a unique and serene experience. The Mughal Gardens, such as Shalimar Bagh, Nishat Bagh, and Chashme Shahi, are in full bloom during summer, adding to the charm of the city.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Gulmarg</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Gulmarg, also known as the \"Meadow of Flowers,\" is a breathtaking hill station. In summer, the valley is covered in vibrant wildflowers, making it a picture-perfect destination. Adventure enthusiasts can indulge in activities like trekking, golfing, and the famous Gulmarg Gondola ride, one of the highest cable cars in the world.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Pahalgam</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Pahalgam, the \"Valley of Shepherds,\" is another must-visit summer retreat. It serves as the base for the Amarnath Yatra and is known for its scenic landscapes. The Lidder River flowing through Pahalgam is perfect for white-water rafting. Aru Valley and Betaab Valley are nearby attractions offering breathtaking views.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>4. Sonamarg</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Sonamarg, meaning \"Meadow of Gold,\" is a paradise for trekkers. The Thajiwas Glacier remains partially covered with snow even in summer, providing an awe-inspiring view. Adventure lovers can embark on treks to Vishansar Lake, Krishansar Lake, and the Zoji La Pass.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Things to Do in Kashmir During Summer</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Shikara Ride &amp; Houseboat Stay</strong> &ndash; Enjoy the tranquil waters of Dal and Nigeen Lakes.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Trekking &amp; Camping</strong> &ndash; Explore the scenic trails of Kashmir Valley.</li>\r\n<li><strong>White-Water Rafting</strong> &ndash; Experience thrilling river rafting in the Lidder River.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gondola Ride in Gulmarg</strong> &ndash; Witness breathtaking panoramic views from the world&rsquo;s second-highest cable car.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Photography &amp; Nature Walks</strong> &ndash; Capture the essence of Kashmir&rsquo;s beauty.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Shopping for Handicrafts</strong> &ndash; Buy authentic Pashmina shawls, Kashmiri carpets, and traditional dry fruits.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Local Delicacies to Try</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Kashmiri cuisine is an essential part of the travel experience. Some must-try dishes include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Rogan Josh</strong> &ndash; A flavorful mutton curry.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Yakhni</strong> &ndash; A mild yogurt-based mutton dish.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Dum Aloo</strong> &ndash; Spicy and aromatic potato curry.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Kahwa</strong> &ndash; Traditional Kashmiri green tea infused with saffron and dry fruits.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gushtaba</strong> &ndash; Minced meatballs cooked in a creamy yogurt gravy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Summer in Kashmir is an experience like no other. The pleasant weather, mesmerizing landscapes, and rich culture make it a perfect holiday destination. Whether you are a nature lover, adventure seeker, or someone looking for peace, Kashmir has something for everyone. So, pack your bags and witness the unparalleled beauty of Kashmir this summer!</p>', '1741081104.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-04 09:38:24', '2025-03-04 09:38:24'),
(5, 'Gulmarg - A Meadow of Flowers', 'gulmarg-a-meadow-of-flowers', '<p>Gulmarg, often referred to as the \"Meadow of Flowers,\" is a breathtaking destination nestled in the Pir Panjal range of the Himalayas in Jammu and Kashmir, India. Known for its lush green meadows, snow-capped peaks, and vibrant flora, Gulmarg is a year-round paradise for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts alike.</p>\r\n<h3>Why Visit Gulmarg?</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Skiing and Snowboarding</strong>: During winter, Gulmarg transforms into a premier skiing destination, attracting enthusiasts from around the globe.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Gulmarg Gondola</strong>: One of the highest cable cars in the world, it offers panoramic views of the surrounding mountains and valleys.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Alpather Lake</strong>: A serene alpine lake that remains frozen until late summer, perfect for trekking and photography.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Golfing</strong>: Home to one of the highest golf courses in the world, Gulmarg is a golfer\'s dream.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Wildlife and Flora</strong>: The Gulmarg Biosphere Reserve is a haven for wildlife enthusiasts, featuring species like the musk deer and a variety of birds.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', '1742969011.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-26 06:03:31', '2025-03-26 06:03:31'),
(6, 'Pahalgam - Valley of Shepherds', 'pahalgam-valley-of-shepherds', '<p>Pahalgam, often referred to as the \"Valley of Shepherds,\" is a picturesque town in the Anantnag district of Jammu and Kashmir, India. Nestled at the confluence of the Lidder River and Sheshnag Lake, Pahalgam is a haven for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those seeking tranquility.</p>\r\n<h3>Why Visit Pahalgam?</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Betaab Valley</strong>: Famous for its lush greenery and serene landscapes, this valley is named after the Bollywood movie \"Betaab,\" which was filmed here.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Aru Valley</strong>: A charming village surrounded by dense forests and snow-capped peaks, perfect for trekking and camping.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Chandanwari</strong>: The starting point of the Amarnath Yatra, known for its pristine beauty and religious significance.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Sheshnag Lake</strong>: A high-altitude lake surrounded by mountains, offering breathtaking views and a peaceful atmosphere.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Activities in Pahalgam</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Trekking</strong>: Explore trails leading to Kolahoi Glacier and Lidderwat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Fishing</strong>: The Lidder River is a great spot for trout fishing.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Horse Riding</strong>: A unique way to explore the valleys and meadows.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Rafting</strong>: Experience the thrill of white-water rafting in the Lidder River.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Best Time to Visit</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Summer (March to June)</strong>: Ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Winter (November to February)</strong>: Perfect for enjoying snow-covered landscapes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1743056476.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-27 06:21:16', '2025-03-27 06:21:16'),
(7, 'Gurez Valley - A hidden gem of Jammu and Kashmir', 'gurez-valley-a-hidden-gem-of-jammu-and-kashmir', '<p>Gurez Valley, often described as a hidden gem of Jammu and Kashmir, is a pristine and untouched paradise nestled in the high Himalayas. Located about 123 kilometers from Srinagar, this valley is a treasure trove of natural beauty, history, and culture.</p>\r\n<h3>Why Visit Gurez Valley?</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Breathtaking Landscapes</strong>: Surrounded by snow-capped peaks and lush green meadows, Gurez offers some of the most stunning views in the region.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Kishanganga River</strong>: The river flows gracefully through the valley, adding to its charm and providing opportunities for fishing and riverside picnics.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Habba Khatoon Peak</strong>: Named after the famous Kashmiri poetess, this pyramid-shaped peak is a symbol of love and beauty.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Rich History</strong>: Gurez was once part of the ancient Silk Route, connecting South and Central Asia. The valley is dotted with archaeological sites and inscriptions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Activities in Gurez Valley</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Trekking</strong>: Explore trails leading to Dawar, Tulail, and other picturesque spots.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Wildlife Spotting</strong>: The valley is home to species like the Himalayan brown bear and snow leopard.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Cultural Exploration</strong>: Interact with the Dard-Shin community, known for their unique traditions and language.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Best Time to Visit</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Summer (May to September)</strong>: Ideal for trekking, sightseeing, and enjoying the lush greenery.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Winter (November to March)</strong>: Perfect for experiencing the snow-covered landscapes, though the valley remains cut off due to heavy snowfall.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Travel Tips</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Carry warm clothing, even in summer, as temperatures can drop unexpectedly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Respect local customs and traditions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Plan your visit carefully, as the valley is remote and requires permits for entry.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1743057647.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-27 06:40:47', '2025-03-27 06:40:47'),
(8, 'Ladakh - Land of High Passes', 'ladakh-land-of-high-passes', '<p>Ladakh, often referred to as the \"Land of High Passes,\" is a mesmerizing region in the northernmost part of India. Known for its stark landscapes, vibrant culture, and thrilling adventures, Ladakh is a dream destination for travelers seeking serenity and excitement.</p>\r\n<h3>Why Visit Ladakh?</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Pangong Lake</strong>: A stunning high-altitude lake that changes colors throughout the day, offering breathtaking views.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Nubra Valley</strong>: Famous for its sand dunes, double-humped camels, and picturesque villages.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Leh Palace</strong>: A historic palace that provides panoramic views of Leh town and the surrounding mountains.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Magnetic Hill</strong>: A unique phenomenon where vehicles appear to defy gravity.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Monasteries</strong>: Hemis, Thiksey, and Diskit monasteries are spiritual havens showcasing Ladakh\'s rich Buddhist heritage.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Activities in Ladakh</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Trekking</strong>: Explore trails like Markha Valley and Stok Kangri.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Motorbiking</strong>: Ride through the challenging terrains of Khardung La and Chang La.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Rafting</strong>: Experience the thrill of rafting in the Zanskar River.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Camping</strong>: Spend nights under the starry skies at Pangong Lake and Tso Moriri.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Best Time to Visit</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Summer (May to September)</strong>: Ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Winter (November to February)</strong>: Perfect for experiencing the snow-covered landscapes and Ladakhi festivals.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Local Cuisine</h3>\r\n<p>Relish traditional dishes like Thukpa, Momos, and Butter Tea.</p>\r\n<h3>Travel Tips</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Acclimatize to the high altitude to avoid sickness.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Carry warm clothing, even in summer, as temperatures can drop unexpectedly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Respect local customs and traditions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1743058333.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-27 06:52:13', '2025-03-27 06:52:13'),
(9, 'Sonamarg - A Meadow of Gold', 'sonamarg-a-meadow-of-gold', '<p>Sonamarg, meaning \"Meadow of Gold,\" is a breathtaking destination in Jammu and Kashmir, India. Known for its golden-hued peaks and lush landscapes, Sonamarg is a paradise for nature lovers and adventure seekers.</p>\r\n<h3>Why Visit Sonamarg?</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Thajiwas Glacier</strong>: A must-visit spot for snow lovers, offering activities like sledding and trekking.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Nilagrad River</strong>: A river believed to have healing properties, perfect for a serene picnic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Baltal Valley</strong>: A picturesque camping ground for pilgrims heading to Amarnath.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Zojila Pass</strong>: A high mountain pass connecting Sonamarg to Leh, offering stunning views.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Activities in Sonamarg</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Trekking</strong>: Explore trails leading to hidden lakes and glaciers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Fishing</strong>: Enjoy trout fishing in the Sindh River.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Camping</strong>: Spend nights under the starry skies in the Baltal Valley.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Best Time to Visit</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Summer (April to June)</strong>: Ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Winter (November to February)</strong>: Perfect for experiencing snow-covered landscapes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Local Cuisine</h3>\r\n<p>Relish Kashmiri dishes like Rogan Josh, Dum Aloo, and the famous Kahwa tea.</p>\r\n<h3>Travel Tips</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Carry warm clothing, even in summer, as temperatures can drop unexpectedly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Respect local customs and traditions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Book accommodations in advance during peak seasons.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1743065633.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-03-27 08:53:53', '2025-04-17 07:35:09'),
(10, 'Asia\'s Largest Tulip Garden', 'asias-largest-tulip-garden', '<p>The Tulip Garden in Kashmir, also known as Indira Gandhi Memorial Tulip Garden, is a mesmerizing place that draws visitors from around the globe. Nestled in the enchanting Zabarwan range overlooking the Dal Lake in Srinagar, it is Asia\'s largest tulip garden, boasting over 1.5 million tulip bulbs in various vibrant hues. Here&rsquo;s a blog about this floral wonderland:</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">The Paradise of Tulips: Kashmir\'s Jewel</span></h3>\r\n<p>Imagine walking amidst a sea of tulips, each bloom bursting with colors so vivid that they seem to paint the landscape. This dream-like experience becomes a reality at the Indira Gandhi Memorial Tulip Garden in Srinagar, Kashmir. Every spring, this garden transforms into a kaleidoscope of colors, enchanting visitors with its unparalleled beauty.</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">A Riot of Colors</span></h4>\r\n<p>Spread over 30 hectares, the Tulip Garden showcases more than 60 varieties of tulips. From vivid reds and sunny yellows to delicate pinks and regal purples, the garden is a visual treat. The blooming period typically lasts for 2-3 weeks in March and April, depending on the weather. It\'s a short but magical window that leaves an indelible mark on every visitor.</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">History and Vision</span></h4>\r\n<p>Established in 2007, the garden was the brainchild of the then Chief Minister of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, Ghulam Nabi Azad. The aim was to boost tourism and provide a spectacular addition to the natural beauty of Kashmir. Today, it stands as a testament to that vision, drawing lakhs of tourists annually.</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">Beyond the Tulips</span></h4>\r\n<p>While the tulips steal the show, the garden also features other spring flowers like daffodils, hyacinths, and ranunculus. The backdrop of the snow-capped Zabarwan mountains and the Dal Lake adds to the charm, making it a photographer\'s paradise. Visitors can also enjoy cultural programs and local Kashmiri handicrafts during the Tulip Festival held in the garden.</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">Visiting Tips</span></h4>\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Timing is Everything</strong>: Visit during the peak bloom period for the most stunning views.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Early Bird Advantage</strong>: Arrive early to avoid crowds and capture the serene beauty in its entirety.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Comfortable Attire</strong>: Wear comfortable shoes and carry a light jacket as mornings can be chilly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Respect Nature</strong>: Help maintain the garden\'s beauty by avoiding any damage to the flowers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: rgb(185, 106, 217);\">Why You Should Visit</span></h4>\r\n<p>The Tulip Garden is more than just a collection of flowers&mdash;it\'s a celebration of nature\'s artistry. It offers a rejuvenating escape from daily life, a chance to connect with nature, and an opportunity to experience the unmatched beauty of Kashmir.</p>', '1744814350.jpeg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-09 09:48:09', '2025-04-16 14:42:37'),
(11, 'Indus Valley in Ladakh', 'indus-valley-in-ladakh', '<p><strong>Ladakh: The Confluence of Heaven and Earth</strong></p>\r\n<p>Nestled in India\'s northernmost regions, Ladakh is a place of unadulterated beauty, historic monasteries, and starry skies. Often referred to as \"The Land of High Passes,\" it is a place unto itself, serene, bleak, and utterly remarkable.</p>\r\n<p><strong>üìç Where Is Ladakh?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ladakh is part of the Union Territory of Ladakh, which was separated from Jammu and Kashmir in 2019. It is a crossroads of cultures and geography, sharing borders with Tibet, Himachal Pradesh, and Pakistan.</p>\r\n<p>Leh and Kargil are its two primary districts; Leh is the most visited base.</p>\r\n<p>üßò&zwj;‚ôÇÔ∏è Peace, Monasteries, and Culture</p>\r\n<p>Tibetan Buddhism has a strong cultural influence in Ladakh. Clinging to mountainside, ancient Gompas (monasteries) like Hemis, Thiksey, and Diskit are teeming with chanting monks, prayer wheels, and murals.</p>', '1745578293.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 10:51:33', '2025-05-17 10:31:14'),
(13, 'Sunsets and Silence: The Magic of Shanti Stupa', 'sunsets-and-silence-the-magic-of-shanti-stupa', '<p><strong>Shanti Stupa Leh is a Himalayan peace lighthouse.</strong></p>\r\n<p>One of those locations that immediately slows you down, inhales a little deeper, and lets you just feel is Shanti Stupa, perched high above the little Ladakh town. More than just a lovely white-domed building, it\'s a spiritual experience that lingers long after you\'ve left and a tranquil haven with expansive views of the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p><strong>A peaceful mission With a strong message.<br></strong><br>Together with Ladakhi Buddhists, Japanese Buddhist Bhikshu Gyomyo Nakamura built Shanti Stupa in<strong> 1991</strong>. The aim is To honor the close relationship between India and Japan and advance peace. The <strong>Dalai Lama</strong> personally blessed the stumas and placed Buddha relics at their base.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '1745578882.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:01:22', '2025-05-17 10:49:26'),
(14, 'Tso Moriri Lake - Ladakh‚Äôs Hidden Gem of Stillness and Sky', 'tso-moriri-lake-ladakhs-hidden-gem-of-stillness-and-sky', '<p><strong>Tso Moriri lake</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tso Moriri is the place to be if you ever find yourself yearning silence&mdash;that sort of silence that permeates your soul. Hidden in the far-off hills of Ladakh, this high-altitude lake seems out of a dream. One of those places where you forget your phone even exists: less visitors, more unspoiled beauty, and a great feeling of peace.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Travel Part of the magic exists here.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Arriving at Tso Moriri is not the easiest trip. About 220 km from Leh, the road winds across stretches of total nothingness, small towns, and difficult terrain. Still, I promise you&mdash;each turn on the road is well worth it. The scenery keeps changing: brown mountains, turquoise streams, and the occasional herd</p>', '1745579117.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:05:17', '2025-05-17 10:50:56'),
(15, 'Lost in Blue ‚Äì A Day at Pangong Lake', 'lost-in-blue-a-day-at-pangong-lake', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"141\" data-end=\"181\"><strong data-start=\"141\" data-end=\"181\">Pangong lake</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"183\" data-end=\"493\">There are some places that don&rsquo;t feel real, and for me, <strong data-start=\"239\" data-end=\"255\">Pangong Lake</strong> was one of them. I&rsquo;d seen all the photos, watched the videos, even planned for the cold. But nothing&mdash;<em data-start=\"357\" data-end=\"366\">nothing</em>&mdash;prepared me for that first glimpse. It was like someone had spilled an ocean of blue ink right in the middle of the mountains.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"495\" data-end=\"535\">The Ride That Shakes You (Literally)</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"537\" data-end=\"864\">The journey from Leh to Pangong isn&rsquo;t the smoothest. It&rsquo;s bumpy, dusty, and long&mdash;but also absolutely unforgettable. You drive past valleys that look like paintings, climb hairpin bends that seem to lead to the sky, and cross frozen streams that make you pause just to take it all in. And then, without warning, Pangong appears.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"866\" data-end=\"968\">I remember the car going silent. Everyone just looked out the window. No words&mdash;just wide eyes and awe.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"1004\">The Lake That Changes Its Mind</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1302\">One minute it&rsquo;s turquoise, then it turns deep blue, and then, just as suddenly, a dusty grey. Pangong Lake is moody&mdash;in the best way. It reflects the sky, the sun, the clouds, and somehow, even your mood. It stretches so far you can&rsquo;t see where it ends. On the far side? That&rsquo;s China. Wild, right?</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1304\" data-end=\"1465\">I sat by the lake for hours. Not doing anything, just watching. Breathing. I don&rsquo;t know what it was&mdash;maybe the stillness, maybe the cold&mdash;but it felt like therapy.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1467\" data-end=\"1497\">Camp Life and Starry Skies</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1499\" data-end=\"1836\">We stayed the night in one of the camps nearby&mdash;Spangmik village is where most travelers set up. The tents are simple, the food is hot, and the people are kind. At night, the temperature drops fast, but the sky&mdash;my god&mdash;the sky is something else. I&rsquo;ve never seen so many stars. No streetlights, no noise, just you, the lake, and the cosmos.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1838\" data-end=\"1922\">I wrapped myself in every layer I had, held a cup of butter tea, and just stared up.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1924\" data-end=\"1948\">A Few Real-Talk Tips</h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"2348\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"2031\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1952\" data-end=\"2031\"><strong data-start=\"1952\" data-end=\"1969\">Time to visit</strong>: May to September. Roads are safer and the lake isn&rsquo;t frozen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2032\" data-end=\"2117\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2034\" data-end=\"2117\"><strong data-start=\"2034\" data-end=\"2054\">Altitude is real</strong>: Acclimatize properly in Leh before heading here. It&rsquo;s <em data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2116\">high</em>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2118\" data-end=\"2185\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2120\" data-end=\"2185\"><strong data-start=\"2120\" data-end=\"2141\">No signal = peace</strong>: It&rsquo;s a break from the world. Lean into it.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2186\" data-end=\"2261\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2188\" data-end=\"2261\"><strong data-start=\"2188\" data-end=\"2207\">Layers are life</strong>: Even if the sun is shining, the nights are icy cold.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2262\" data-end=\"2348\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2264\" data-end=\"2348\"><strong data-start=\"2264\" data-end=\"2284\">Respect the land</strong>: Don&rsquo;t litter, and don&rsquo;t take anything but photos and memories.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1745579370.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:09:30', '2025-04-25 11:09:30'),
(18, 'Nubra Valley: The Hidden Desert Oasis of the Himalayas', 'nubra-valley-the-hidden-desert-oasis-of-the-himalayas', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"194\"><strong data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"194\">Nubra Valley &ndash; A Desert Dream in the Lap of the Himalayas</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"196\" data-end=\"586\">If I had to describe <strong data-start=\"217\" data-end=\"233\">Nubra Valley</strong> in one word, it would be: <em data-start=\"260\" data-end=\"272\">unexpected</em>. You don&rsquo;t imagine finding sand dunes, double-humped camels, and a lush river cutting through the desert&mdash;all surrounded by snow-capped mountains&mdash;<em data-start=\"418\" data-end=\"450\">at 10,000 feet above sea level</em>. But that&rsquo;s Nubra for you. Quietly magical, full of surprises, and the kind of place that lingers in your memory like a favorite dream.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"588\" data-end=\"635\">The Journey There &ndash; A Ride You Won&rsquo;t Forget</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"637\" data-end=\"940\">Reaching Nubra means crossing <strong data-start=\"667\" data-end=\"682\">Khardung La</strong>, one of the highest motorable roads in the world. The road itself feels like an adventure&mdash;hairpin bends, thin air, prayer flags fluttering wildly at the top, and then suddenly, you descend into this stunning green valley that seems to appear out of nowhere.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"942\" data-end=\"1047\">The contrast is unreal. One moment you&rsquo;re surrounded by snow, and the next, you&rsquo;re staring at sand dunes.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1049\" data-end=\"1089\">Where the Desert Meets the Mountains</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1091\" data-end=\"1347\">The first time I saw <strong data-start=\"1112\" data-end=\"1122\">Hunder</strong>, I had to blink twice. There were camels&mdash;actual <em data-start=\"1171\" data-end=\"1181\">Bactrian</em> camels with two humps&mdash;just chilling in the dunes, with jagged peaks in the background. It felt like I&rsquo;d accidentally wandered into a National Geographic documentary.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1349\" data-end=\"1575\">You can take a short camel ride at sunset, or just wander through the dunes with bare feet and let the soft, cold sand sink under you. It&rsquo;s peaceful in a way that&rsquo;s hard to explain&mdash;like the valley is quietly watching over you.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1577\" data-end=\"1612\">Diskit Monastery &ndash; Above It All</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1614\" data-end=\"1988\">High up on a hill, overlooking the entire valley, sits the <strong data-start=\"1673\" data-end=\"1693\">Diskit Monastery</strong>. And beside it? A giant statue of <strong data-start=\"1728\" data-end=\"1747\">Maitreya Buddha</strong>, calmly gazing out over the landscape. The climb up to the monastery is worth every step. Inside, it&rsquo;s quiet and sacred, but it&rsquo;s the view outside that really hits you&mdash;layers of mountain, river, and light all blending into something unreal.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1990\" data-end=\"2022\">People, Simplicity, and Soul</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2024\" data-end=\"2296\">The people of Nubra are some of the kindest I&rsquo;ve ever met. Life here is simple, but full. Kids playing outside in the cold, families tending to their farms, and locals always ready with a smile or a hot cup of tea. It reminded me how little we actually need to be content.</p>', '1745579720.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:15:20', '2025-04-25 11:15:20'),
(19, 'Khardung La Pass: Reaching the Heights of the Himalayan World', 'khardung-la-pass-reaching-the-heights-of-the-himalayan-world', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"189\"><strong data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"189\">Khardung La Pass &ndash; Conquering the Roof of the World</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"191\" data-end=\"470\">If there&rsquo;s one road that feels like a true test of both courage and awe, it&rsquo;s <strong data-start=\"269\" data-end=\"289\">Khardung La Pass</strong>. Tucked high in the mountains, this road claims to be one of the highest motorable roads in the world (at over 18,000 feet), and the journey up to it is nothing short of thrilling.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"472\" data-end=\"525\">The Road to Khardung La &ndash; A Journey of a Lifetime</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"527\" data-end=\"740\">The drive to Khardung La is not for the faint-hearted. Winding roads, steep climbs, and the ever-present danger of altitude sickness make it a challenging but rewarding adventure. But the reward? That&rsquo;s the magic.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"742\" data-end=\"1008\">As you ascend from Leh, the world starts to change&mdash;lush valleys give way to barren, rocky slopes. The air thins, and every breath feels more precious. At times, it feels like you&rsquo;re climbing into the sky, and with every turn, the views get more and more spectacular.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1010\" data-end=\"1057\">At the Top &ndash; An Experience You Won&rsquo;t Forget</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1059\" data-end=\"1387\">When you finally reach Khardung La, you&rsquo;ll feel a rush of accomplishment. The wind hits you with a cold bite, and the surroundings are stark, almost otherworldly. But there&rsquo;s also something deeply humbling about standing at the top of this road, surrounded by nothing but mountains and sky. You&rsquo;re on top of the world&mdash;literally.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1389\" data-end=\"1671\">The <strong data-start=\"1393\" data-end=\"1418\">Khardung La Pass sign</strong> at the top is a popular photo spot. Be sure to snap a picture with the backdrop of towering peaks before you lose yourself in the serenity of the place. You might even spot a prayer flag fluttering in the wind, adding a bit of spirituality to the view.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1673\" data-end=\"1696\">The Altitude Factor</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1698\" data-end=\"2034\">At over 18,000 feet, the air here is <em data-start=\"1735\" data-end=\"1741\">thin</em>, and the altitude can affect you in unexpected ways. Take it slow&mdash;take breaks, drink plenty of water, and respect your body&rsquo;s limits. Many travelers experience mild symptoms of altitude sickness (headaches, nausea, dizziness), so it&rsquo;s crucial to acclimatize properly in Leh before heading up.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2036\" data-end=\"2063\">The Vibe of Khardung La</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2065\" data-end=\"2423\">Despite the cold and the altitude, Khardung La is surprisingly lively. There&rsquo;s a small tea shop at the top where you can sip on some warm chai, exchange stories with fellow travelers, and bask in the shared sense of achievement. The place feels like a junction between adventure and spirituality, a threshold between the mundane world and the high Himalayas.</p>', '1745579974.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:19:34', '2025-04-25 11:19:34'),
(20, 'Magnetic Hill ‚Äì The Hill That Defies Logic', 'magnetic-hill-the-hill-that-defies-logic', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"78\" data-end=\"124\"><strong data-start=\"78\" data-end=\"124\">Magnetic Hill &ndash; The Hill That Defies Logic</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"126\" data-end=\"374\">If there&rsquo;s one thing I&rsquo;ve learned from traveling, it&rsquo;s that the world is full of surprises. But nothing could&rsquo;ve prepared me for <strong data-start=\"255\" data-end=\"272\">Magnetic Hill</strong>&mdash;a place that makes you question your understanding of physics, gravity, and the natural world itself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"404\" data-end=\"778\">Magnetic Hill is famous for its mysterious ability to make vehicles appear as though they&rsquo;re rolling uphill, even though the road is actually sloping downhill.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1708\" data-end=\"1731\">A Stop Worth Making</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1733\" data-end=\"2142\">Magnetic Hill is located just outside Leh, and the drive to get there is an adventure in itself. Surrounded by the vast, open landscape of Ladakh, you&rsquo;ll find yourself in a place that feels both surreal and peaceful. Even though it&rsquo;s a popular tourist spot, there&rsquo;s still something calming about the place&mdash;maybe it&rsquo;s the quiet, or maybe it&rsquo;s the fact that you&rsquo;re standing in the middle of a real-life mystery.</p>', '1745580217.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:23:37', '2025-04-25 11:23:37'),
(21, 'Chang La Pass ‚Äì Conquering the Heights of Ladakh', 'chang-la-pass-conquering-the-heights-of-ladakh', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"129\" data-end=\"461\">Chang La Pass<br><br>If you\'re up for an adventure that pushes you to the limits, <strong data-start=\"190\" data-end=\"207\">Chang La Pass</strong> is the place to be. At an altitude of over 17,500 feet, it\'s one of the highest motorable passes in the world. The journey to get there is nothing short of thrilling&mdash;winding roads, thin air, and towering peaks make every moment feel like an achievement.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"463\" data-end=\"481\">The Journey Up</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"483\" data-end=\"823\">The drive to Chang La from Leh is a test of both endurance and excitement. The road is rough, and the altitude can take its toll, so it&rsquo;s crucial to acclimatize before heading up. But once you reach the top, the feeling is indescribable. The wind bites at your face, and the landscape stretches out in every direction like an endless dream.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"825\" data-end=\"851\">A Sense of Achievement</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"853\" data-end=\"1109\">At the top, there&rsquo;s a small tea stall and an army post, offering a warm cup of chai and a chance to soak in the awe-inspiring surroundings. The snow-capped peaks, the vast desert landscape, and the feeling of being on top of the world make it all worth it.</p>', '1745580410.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-25 11:26:50', '2025-04-25 11:26:50'),
(22, 'Doodhpathri Valley ‚Äì Kashmir‚Äôs Untouched Gem', 'doodhpathri-valley-kashmirs-untouched-gem', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"310\">&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"271\" data-end=\"286\">Doodhpathri</strong> ( Valley of Milk)</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"312\" data-end=\"722\">Tucked away in the Budgam district of Kashmir, Doodhpathri (which literally means &ldquo;Valley of Milk&rdquo;) is still under the radar for most travelers, and honestly, that&rsquo;s what makes it so special. You won&rsquo;t find swarms of tourists here. What you will find is raw, untouched beauty - endless green meadows, pine-covered hills, a milky river that lives up to its name, and the kind of peace that feels almost surreal.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"\" data-start=\"724\" data-end=\"750\"><strong data-start=\"729\" data-end=\"750\">The Journey There</strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"752\" data-end=\"1180\">Getting to Doodhpathri is part of the adventure. It\'s around 45 km from Srinagar &mdash; a drive of about 2 hours if you&rsquo;re not in a hurry (and you shouldn&rsquo;t be). The roads snake through villages, forests, and finally open up to views that&rsquo;ll have you reaching for your camera every two minutes. But trust me &mdash; no photo can capture what it feels like to stand there, surrounded by nature that hasn&rsquo;t been touched by concrete or chaos.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"\" data-start=\"1182\" data-end=\"1227\"><strong data-start=\"1187\" data-end=\"1227\">Why Is It Called the Valley of Milk?</strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1229\" data-end=\"1589\">The name &ldquo;Doodhpathri&rdquo; comes from a local legend. It&rsquo;s said that the river flowing through the valley was once full of milk, not water. Of course, it&rsquo;s not literal &mdash; but when the sunlight hits the water just right, it turns a shimmering white, and you kind of start believing the story. It&rsquo;s cold, crystal clear, and flows with a melody that sounds like peace.</p>', '1745648085.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:14:45', '2025-04-26 06:14:45'),
(23, 'Yousmarg ‚Äì Kashmir‚Äôs Quiet Whisper', 'yousmarg-kashmirs-quiet-whisper', '<p>The name <strong data-start=\"1297\" data-end=\"1309\">Yousmarg</strong> means <em data-start=\"1316\" data-end=\"1335\">&ldquo;Meadow of Jesus&rdquo;</em>. If Kashmir is a symphony of nature, <strong data-start=\"225\" data-end=\"237\">Yousmarg</strong> is the gentle pause between its louder notes &mdash; a soft, green sigh in the middle of mountains, where time slows down and silence speaks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"375\" data-end=\"605\">I hadn&rsquo;t even heard of Yousmarg before planning my Kashmir trip. Everyone talks about Gulmarg, Sonmarg, Pahalgam &mdash; and rightly so. But Yousmarg? It&rsquo;s still a secret to most tourists. And that, honestly, makes it even more special.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"\" data-start=\"607\" data-end=\"665\"><strong data-start=\"612\" data-end=\"665\">A Valley That Doesn\'t Try to Impress &mdash; It Just Is</strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"667\" data-end=\"1017\">Located about <strong data-start=\"681\" data-end=\"704\">50 km from Srinagar</strong>, the drive to Yousmarg is beautiful in itself &mdash; winding roads, sleepy little villages, and pine trees tall enough to touch the sky. The last few kilometers feel like you\'re entering a different world. No crowds, no chaos &mdash; just green meadows, snowy peaks in the distance, and the sweet sound of birds and breeze.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1019\" data-end=\"1247\">When I reached, the first thing I did was... nothing. I just stood there. The air was cooler, the sky bluer, and the land &mdash; it stretched out like a soft green carpet rolled out just for me. No filter needed. No caption required.</p>', '1745649502.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:38:22', '2025-04-26 06:38:22');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `image`, `status`, `published_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(25, 'Bungas Valley: Where Silence Speaks in Green', 'bungas-valley-where-silence-speaks-in-green', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"224\" data-end=\"508\"><strong>Bungas Valley</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"224\" data-end=\"508\">Tucked away from the hustle of the city and the buzz of the usual tourist trails lies <strong data-start=\"310\" data-end=\"327\">Bungas Valley</strong>, a place that feels like a whispered secret between the mountains. You won\'t find it on most travel brochures, but that\'s part of the magic&mdash;it&rsquo;s raw, real, and incredibly peaceful.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"510\" data-end=\"834\">The first thing that hit me as I arrived was the silence. Not the eerie kind, but the kind that makes you slow down and just breathe. The air smelled like earth and pine, and the wind carried stories from the hills. The valley itself stretches wide, framed by rolling green hills that look like they&rsquo;ve been painted by hand.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"836\" data-end=\"1079\">Small farms dot the landscape, with villagers working the land in a rhythm that feels centuries old. Children laugh as they run barefoot along dirt paths, and locals greet you with warm smiles that make you feel like you&rsquo;ve been there forever.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1081\" data-end=\"1450\">What stood out most to me was how <strong data-start=\"1115\" data-end=\"1136\">time feels slower</strong> in Bungas Valley. Mornings start with mist rising from the grass and birdsong echoing through the trees. By midday, the sun casts golden light across the valley, turning everything into a postcard. And when night falls, the stars&mdash;oh, the stars&mdash;blanket the sky so thickly you forget about streetlights and screens.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1452\" data-end=\"1627\">If you&rsquo;re someone who craves connection&mdash;to nature, to people, to yourself&mdash;this valley is a gentle reminder of what matters. No filters, no noise, just life in its purest form.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1629\" data-end=\"1779\">So if you\'re ever nearby, don&rsquo;t just pass through. Stop. Stay a while. Let Bungas Valley work its quiet magic on you. I promise, you&rsquo;ll leave lighter.</p>', '1745649803.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:43:23', '2025-04-26 06:43:23'),
(26, 'Tulail Valley: A Place That Feels Like a Secret', 'tulail-valley-a-place-that-feels-like-a-secret', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"190\" data-end=\"291\"><strong data-start=\"259\" data-end=\"276\">Tulail Valley</strong> is the latter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"600\">&nbsp;Tulail feels almost untouched by time. Getting there isn&rsquo;t exactly easy&mdash;the roads are narrow, the ride is long, and your phone signal starts to disappear the closer you get. But somehow, that makes it even better.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"602\" data-end=\"874\">When I first arrived, it felt like stepping into a storybook. Wooden homes with slanted rooftops peeked out from green hills, and the Kishanganga River wound its way through the valley like a silver thread. Snow-capped peaks stood tall in the distance, silent and ancient.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"876\" data-end=\"1136\">The beauty here isn&rsquo;t loud&mdash;it&rsquo;s gentle, like a soft song playing in the background. Life moves slowly. Kids wave at you from rooftops. Shepherds guide their flocks across the meadows. And the air&mdash;clean, crisp, and so still you can hear your own thoughts again.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1418\">I stayed with a local family who treated me like I belonged. We drank salty noon chai by the fire, shared stories over simple meals, and watched the sky turn pink each evening. There&rsquo;s something humbling about being so far from everything you know, yet feeling so deeply at peace.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1420\" data-end=\"1502\">Tulail isn&rsquo;t about sights to tick off. It&rsquo;s about moments&mdash;quiet, honest, and real.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1504\" data-end=\"1676\">If you ever make the journey, come with an open heart and no rush. This valley doesn&rsquo;t shout. It whispers. And if you listen closely, it just might change something in you.</p>', '1745650068.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:47:48', '2025-04-26 06:47:48'),
(27, 'Lolab Valley: The Poetry of Peace', 'lolab-valley-the-poetry-of-peace', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"373\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><em><strong>Lolab Valley: Kashmir&rsquo;s Quiet Poem&nbsp;</strong></em></span><br><br>Sometimes, the most beautiful places aren&rsquo;t the ones everyone talks about&mdash;they&rsquo;re the ones you stumble upon by chance, the ones that feel like a gentle sigh from the earth. <strong data-start=\"333\" data-end=\"349\">Lolab Valley</strong> is one of those places.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"375\" data-end=\"688\">Nestled in the north of Kashmir, not far from Kupwara, Lolab doesn&rsquo;t scream for attention. It doesn&rsquo;t need to. The valley has this quiet grace&mdash;lush forests, endless meadows, and a silence that somehow says more than words ever could. The locals call it the &ldquo;Land of Love and Beauty,&rdquo; and honestly, that name fits.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"980\">Driving into Lolab, the first thing I noticed was how green everything was. Not just green&mdash;<strong data-start=\"781\" data-end=\"790\">vivid</strong>. The kind of green that makes your eyes widen a little and your heart slow down. Pine trees stand tall like old guardians, and walnut orchards stretch out across the land like a soft quilt.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"982\" data-end=\"1251\">What struck me the most, though, wasn&rsquo;t just the landscape&mdash;it was the life. Farmers working in the fields with hands weathered by the sun. Kids chasing each other along muddy paths. Women chatting outside their homes, their laughter floating into the breeze like music.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1253\" data-end=\"1522\">I spent a few days here, and they felt like a gentle pause. I stayed in a modest guesthouse, woke up to the sound of birds instead of alarms, drank chai that tasted like it was brewed with care, and watched the light change across the mountains with every passing hour.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1524\" data-end=\"1606\">Lolab doesn&rsquo;t try to impress you. It just <strong data-start=\"1566\" data-end=\"1572\">is</strong>. Honest, slow, and soul-soothing.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1608\" data-end=\"1841\">So if you ever find yourself in Kashmir, and you&rsquo;re looking for a place that feels like a deep breath after a long journey&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1731\" data-end=\"1746\">go to Lolab</strong>. Let the valley welcome you with open arms and whisper its story in the quietest, kindest way.</p>', '1745650290.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:51:30', '2025-04-26 06:51:30'),
(28, 'Aharbal Waterfall: Kashmir‚Äôs Untold Harmony', 'aharbal-waterfall-kashmirs-untold-harmony', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"192\" data-end=\"490\"><strong data-start=\"365\" data-end=\"386\">Aharbal Waterfall</strong> in Kashmir is no exception. It&rsquo;s not just a sight to behold; it&rsquo;s an experience that tugs at your soul.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"492\" data-end=\"792\">Tucked away in the lush forests of the Pir Panjal range, Aharbal feels like nature&rsquo;s best-kept secret. Getting there isn&rsquo;t difficult, but once you&rsquo;re standing at the base of the falls, you realize it&rsquo;s one of those places that doesn&rsquo;t need to be discovered by everyone. It holds onto its quiet magic.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"794\" data-end=\"1170\">The waterfall itself is breathtaking. The water tumbles down from a height of over 30 meters, crashing into the rocky gorge below. The roar of the water is both powerful and calming, like the mountains are speaking in a language only the heart can understand. The mist rising from the base of the falls adds an ethereal touch, making everything feel like a scene from a dream.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1172\" data-end=\"1648\">What I loved most about Aharbal wasn&rsquo;t just the falls&mdash;it was the journey to get there. As I walked along the narrow path leading to the viewpoint, I passed through dense forests of pine and cedar, where the air was so fresh it almost felt like it was cleansing me from within. Along the way, I met locals who spoke of the falls like an old friend, telling stories of how the area comes alive with the sounds of the water, the chirping of birds, and the rustling of the leaves.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1650\" data-end=\"1986\">At the falls, I sat on a rock by the water\'s edge, watching the mist rise and listening to the rush of the water. It was peaceful in a way that felt almost sacred. There&rsquo;s a humbling beauty in the rawness of nature here. You can&rsquo;t help but feel small in the best possible way&mdash;reminded of how powerful, yet delicate, the world really is.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1988\" data-end=\"2174\">If you ever find yourself in Kashmir, do yourself a favor and make the trip to Aharbal. It&rsquo;s not a place you rush through. It&rsquo;s somewhere you linger, take a deep breath, and just <strong data-start=\"2167\" data-end=\"2173\">be</strong>.</p>', '1745650591.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 06:54:56', '2025-04-26 06:56:31'),
(29, 'Kokernag: Kashmir‚Äôs Tranquil Escape', 'kokernag-kashmirs-tranquil-escape', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"83\" data-end=\"124\"><strong data-start=\"83\" data-end=\"124\">Kokernag: A Slice of Peace in Kashmir</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"126\" data-end=\"407\"><strong data-start=\"206\" data-end=\"218\">Kokernag</strong>, a serene village tucked away in Kashmir&rsquo;s Anantnag district, is one of those places. It&rsquo;s not a well-known tourist spot, but it has a quiet magic that stays with you long after you leave.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"409\" data-end=\"794\">As soon as I arrived in Kokernag, the air felt different&mdash;fresh, clean, and filled with the scent of pine trees and mountain soil. The village is famous for its <strong data-start=\"569\" data-end=\"588\">Kokernag Spring</strong>, a beautiful natural water source that seems to come straight out of a fairytale. The spring is massive, its waters clear and cool, trickling down from the hills like a life source for the land and people.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"796\" data-end=\"1155\">What&rsquo;s most enchanting about Kokernag is its tranquility. There&rsquo;s no rush here. No noise. Just the gentle sound of flowing water and the soft rustle of leaves in the wind. I found a quiet spot by the spring, watching the water shimmer in the sunlight, feeling time slow down around me. It&rsquo;s a place that allows you to breathe deeply, to pause, and to just be.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1157\" data-end=\"1589\">The villagers, too, reflect the calm of the land. I met a local woman who invited me to sit with her and share a cup of <strong data-start=\"1277\" data-end=\"1293\">Kashmiri tea</strong>. As we chatted (in a mix of broken English and gestures), she told me how the spring was at the heart of their village, a source of life and livelihood for generations. It was clear that Kokernag&rsquo;s charm comes from more than just its beauty&mdash;it&rsquo;s the connection between the people and their land.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1591\" data-end=\"1941\">Beyond the spring, Kokernag is a haven for nature lovers. There are walking trails through the lush forests, where the air smells of fresh pine, and the only sounds are birds and rustling leaves. The view of the distant snow-capped mountains is nothing short of breathtaking, and if you&rsquo;re lucky, you might even spot a few wildflowers along the path.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1943\" data-end=\"2228\">Kokernag doesn&rsquo;t rush. It doesn&rsquo;t boast. It simply invites you to experience its quiet beauty. If you&rsquo;re looking for a place in Kashmir that feels like a hidden paradise, where the pace of life slows down and the natural world is at its most peaceful, Kokernag is where you need to be.</p>', '1745651016.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:03:36', '2025-04-26 07:03:36'),
(30, 'Verinag: The Spring That Starts a Story', 'verinag-the-spring-that-starts-a-story', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"142\" data-end=\"432\"><strong>Verinag doesn&rsquo;t ask for attention&mdash;it simply welcomes you, gently.</strong><br><br>There&rsquo;s something incredibly calming about <strong data-start=\"185\" data-end=\"196\">Verinag</strong>&mdash;the kind of calm that settles in your chest the moment you arrive. Known as the source of the Jhelum River, Verinag isn&rsquo;t loud or flashy, but it carries centuries of history in its waters and whispers of Mughal elegance in its gardens.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"434\" data-end=\"669\">The spring, encased in old stone and framed by ancient chinars, feels sacred&mdash;like nature and time made a quiet pact here. Locals come to sit, to reflect, to just be. And as I dipped my hand into the cold, clear water, I understood why.<br><br>There&rsquo;s a quiet grace to Verinag&mdash;less about grand sights, more about peaceful moments. A place where history, nature, and stillness meet in perfect harmony.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"671\" data-end=\"736\">&nbsp;</p>', '1745651974.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:19:34', '2025-04-26 07:19:34'),
(31, 'Daksum: Where the Forest Hugs You Back', 'daksum-where-the-forest-hugs-you-back', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"329\"><strong data-start=\"270\" data-end=\"280\">Daksum</strong>,<strong> that breathe life back into you slowly, gently.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"331\" data-end=\"530\">Tucked between Anantnag and Sinthan Top, Daksum isn&rsquo;t flashy. It doesn&rsquo;t try to impress. It just wraps you in tall deodar trees, lets a cold stream sing beside you, and gives you space to <strong data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"529\">exhale</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"532\" data-end=\"768\">The drive there was beautiful, but it was when I stepped out and heard nothing but birdsong and the rush of the Bringi River that I truly felt the difference. It&rsquo;s wild, green, and peaceful in a way most places have forgotten how to be.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"770\" data-end=\"1004\">Locals pass by with baskets of firewood or grazing sheep, always with a nod or a soft &ldquo;salaam.&rdquo; I sat for hours by the river, just listening. No phone, no schedule&mdash;just me, the trees, and the sound of water flowing over smooth stones.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1077\">Daksum isn&rsquo;t about doing. It&rsquo;s about being. And that&rsquo;s its quiet magic.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1079\" data-end=\"1183\">If your soul&rsquo;s been asking for a break, this little forested corner of Kashmir might just be the answer.</p>', '1745652095.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:21:35', '2025-04-26 07:21:35'),
(32, 'Manasbal Lake: A Mirror Where Time Slows Down', 'manasbal-lake-a-mirror-where-time-slows-down', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"388\">There&rsquo;s something special about <strong data-start=\"166\" data-end=\"183\">Manasbal Lake</strong>&mdash;something that makes you stop mid-thought, mid-step, and just look. Maybe it&rsquo;s the stillness of the water, or how the mountains reflect so perfectly in its surface, like a memory you don&rsquo;t want to forget.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"390\" data-end=\"608\">Tucked away in the Ganderbal district of Kashmir, Manasbal isn&rsquo;t as famous as Dal or Wular, but that&rsquo;s part of its charm. It&rsquo;s quieter, more intimate. The kind of place you discover by chance, then never want to leave.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"610\" data-end=\"959\">When I visited, lotus flowers floated gently across the lake like tiny pink poems. A fisherman rowed by in his wooden shikara, barely making a ripple. Children laughed in the distance, their voices soft and carried by the breeze. And there I was&mdash;just sitting at the edge, feet dangling above the water, watching the sky change colors over the hills.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"961\" data-end=\"1099\">Locals say it&rsquo;s the deepest lake in Kashmir. To me, it felt deep in a different way&mdash;like it knew how to hold silence, how to cradle peace.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1101\" data-end=\"1236\">If you ever find yourself in the Valley, don&rsquo;t miss Manasbal. Go early. Go with time. Let it show you what stillness really feels like.</p>', '1745652373.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:26:13', '2025-04-26 07:26:13'),
(33, 'Sinthan Top: Where the Sky Feels Close Enough to Touch', 'sinthan-top-where-the-sky-feels-close-enough-to-touch', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"187\" data-end=\"469\">The road to <strong data-start=\"199\" data-end=\"214\">Sinthan Top</strong> isn&rsquo;t just a journey&mdash;it&rsquo;s a slow, winding climb into silence, snow, and sky. Sitting high up in the Pir Panjal range, between South Kashmir and Kishtwar, Sinthan isn&rsquo;t just a pass&mdash;it&rsquo;s a feeling. One that stays with you long after the altitude wears off.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"471\" data-end=\"679\">As I drove up through dense pine forests and sharp curves, the air kept getting thinner, cleaner, and colder. And then, just like that, the trees stopped, the land opened, and I found myself above the clouds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"681\" data-end=\"893\">At <strong data-start=\"684\" data-end=\"699\">12,000 feet</strong>, Sinthan Top feels like the roof of Kashmir. Snow clings to the peaks year-round, and on clear days, you can see the horizon stretch endlessly, as if the world itself paused to admire the view.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"895\" data-end=\"1197\">What struck me most wasn&rsquo;t just the beauty&mdash;it was the <strong data-start=\"949\" data-end=\"962\">stillness</strong>. No cities, no signal, no noise. Just the whisper of the wind and the occasional call of a bird. I saw families building snowmen, bikers catching their breath, and locals selling tea with the kind of smile that says, &ldquo;You&rsquo;ve made it.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1199\" data-end=\"1352\">I sipped on a cup of hot Kahwa, sitting on a rock with the sun warming my face and snow beneath my feet, and thought&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1316\" data-end=\"1352\">this is what freedom feels like.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1354\" data-end=\"1498\">Sinthan Top doesn&rsquo;t ask for much. Just your time, your awe, and a little bit of courage to reach it. But in return, it gives you a piece of sky.</p>', '1745653327.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:42:07', '2025-04-26 07:42:07'),
(34, 'Dal Lake: The Heartbeat of Srinagar', 'dal-lake-the-heartbeat-of-srinagar', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"290\"><strong data-start=\"178\" data-end=\"190\">Dal Lake</strong>, you haven&rsquo;t truly seen Kashmir. And after spending just one quiet morning there, I understood why.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"292\" data-end=\"602\">Dal Lake isn&rsquo;t just water&mdash;it&rsquo;s a way of life. It\'s where Srinagar wakes up gently, with shikaras gliding through the mist like floating dreams. I remember sitting in one of them, wrapped in a blanket, watching the sun slowly rise behind the mountains. Everything felt soft&mdash;the light, the air, even time itself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"604\" data-end=\"867\">As we floated past <strong data-start=\"623\" data-end=\"643\">floating gardens</strong>, wooden houseboats, and old willow trees dipping into the water, I couldn&rsquo;t help but feel like I was inside a painting. The lake mirrors the sky so perfectly, it&rsquo;s sometimes hard to tell where one ends and the other begins.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"869\" data-end=\"1135\">What made Dal even more special were the quiet moments. A saffron seller paddling by with a warm smile. A child waving from a houseboat window. A couple sipping noon chai under a carved wooden awning. There&rsquo;s life here, simple and beautiful, held gently by the lake.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1137\" data-end=\"1264\">Dal Lake isn&rsquo;t just a place to visit. It&rsquo;s a place to feel, to slow down, and to watch the world float by&mdash;one ripple at a time.</p>', '1745654368.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 07:59:28', '2025-04-26 07:59:28'),
(35, 'Pari Mahal: A Garden Between Heaven and Earth', 'pari-mahal-a-garden-between-heaven-and-earth', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"467\">High above the bustling heart of Srinagar, perched like a secret on the Zabarwan hills, sits <strong data-start=\"253\" data-end=\"267\">Pari Mahal</strong>&mdash;the Palace of Fairies. The name alone feels like an invitation to something magical. And when you finally get there, standing among its ancient arches, you understand: this place was made for dreams.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"469\" data-end=\"805\">Pari Mahal isn&rsquo;t flashy. It doesn&rsquo;t overwhelm you with gold or grandeur. Instead, it greets you with open terraces, stone corridors, and the kind of view that makes you go completely still. From up here, <strong data-start=\"673\" data-end=\"685\">Dal Lake</strong> glistens below, the city hums quietly in the distance, and the mountains stand tall behind you like timeless guardians.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"807\" data-end=\"1013\">What I loved most wasn&rsquo;t just the history (though it&rsquo;s rich&mdash;once a Sufi school, later a Mughal garden). It was the feeling. The kind of peace that wraps around your shoulders and whispers, &ldquo;Take your time.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1015\" data-end=\"1313\">I wandered the garden paths slowly, brushing my fingers along cool stone walls. The scent of flowers, the sound of wind slipping through arches&mdash;it all felt like a gentle echo of lives once lived here. It made me wonder: how many poets stood where I stood, watching the same sky turn soft at sunset?</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1315\" data-end=\"1448\"><strong data-start=\"1315\" data-end=\"1329\">Pari Mahal</strong> isn&rsquo;t just a monument. It&rsquo;s a moment. One where you realize how small, how lucky, and how deeply human you really are.</p>', '1745659772.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:29:32', '2025-04-26 09:29:32'),
(36, 'Nishat Garden: Where Kashmir Smiles in Flowers', 'nishat-garden-where-kashmir-smiles-in-flowers', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"181\"><strong data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"181\">Nishat Garden: Where Kashmir Smiles in Flowers</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"183\" data-end=\"348\"><strong data-start=\"250\" data-end=\"265\">Nishat Bagh</strong>, right by the shimmering edge of <strong data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"311\">Dal Lake</strong>, offers it in the most graceful way.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"665\">I visited on a golden afternoon, when the sun was soft and the breeze carried the faint scent of roses. <strong data-start=\"454\" data-end=\"464\">Nishat</strong> isn&rsquo;t just a Mughal garden&mdash;it\'s a place where history and beauty walk hand in hand. Laid out in twelve terraces, each one representing a step closer to paradise, the garden unfolds like a gentle poem.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"667\" data-end=\"869\">The sound of water flowing through the old stone channels, the chirping of birds in the chinar trees, and the laughter of families picnicking under the shade&mdash;everything felt alive, and somehow timeless.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"871\" data-end=\"1137\">I sat on the grass for a long while, watching the lake glisten and the mountains stand quietly in the background. Locals wandered by with ice creams and cameras, but no one seemed in a hurry. That&rsquo;s the magic of Nishat&mdash;you don&rsquo;t need to do anything. You just <strong data-start=\"1130\" data-end=\"1136\">be</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1139\" data-end=\"1373\">The garden was built by Asif Khan in the 17th century, but it still holds that same Mughal grace: precise, peaceful, and endlessly romantic. It&rsquo;s easy to imagine poets and emperors walking here, lost in their thoughts just like I was.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1375\" data-end=\"1520\">If you ever find yourself in Srinagar, take a few slow hours and walk through <strong data-start=\"1453\" data-end=\"1468\">Nishat Bagh</strong>. Let it remind you how healing quiet beauty can be.</p>', '1745659998.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:33:18', '2025-04-26 09:33:18'),
(37, 'Shalimar Garden: A Mughal Love Letter in Bloom', 'shalimar-garden-a-mughal-love-letter-in-bloom', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"185\" data-end=\"349\"><strong data-start=\"203\" data-end=\"220\">Shalimar Bagh</strong> feels like walking into a story. Not a loud, dramatic one&mdash;but a quiet, enduring love story written in stone, water, and flowers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"351\" data-end=\"651\">Built by <strong data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"380\">Emperor Jahangir</strong> for his beloved wife, Nur Jahan, Shalimar is more than just a garden&mdash;it\'s a feeling. The moment you step through its grand gates, you\'re wrapped in the soft rustle of chinar leaves, the gentle splash of fountains, and a stillness that makes you forget the world outside.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"653\" data-end=\"903\">The garden unfolds in three grand terraces, each one more peaceful than the last. Mughal architecture lines the paths&mdash;arched pavilions, black marble benches, and delicate carvings that whisper of a time when kings and poets walked these same grounds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"905\" data-end=\"1195\">I visited in the late afternoon, when sunlight filtered through the trees and danced on the water channels. Families were scattered across the lawns, some sipping tea, others simply sitting in silence. A couple walked hand in hand near the canal, like a scene pulled straight from the past.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1197\" data-end=\"1459\">But Shalimar isn&rsquo;t just about beauty&mdash;it&rsquo;s about <strong data-start=\"1245\" data-end=\"1258\">intention</strong>. Every stone, every stream, every flowerbed was placed with care, meant to soothe the soul. It&rsquo;s a space designed not to impress, but to <strong data-start=\"1396\" data-end=\"1407\">inspire</strong>&mdash;to reflect love, peace, and connection with nature.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1461\" data-end=\"1661\">If you ever find yourself in Srinagar, don&rsquo;t just <em data-start=\"1511\" data-end=\"1516\">see</em> Shalimar Bagh. Take your time. Let it slow you down. Let it remind you how love, when expressed through something lasting, can turn into legacy.</p>', '1745660219.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:36:59', '2025-04-26 09:36:59'),
(38, 'Harwan Garden: A Quiet Corner of Kashmir', 'harwan-garden-a-quiet-corner-of-kashmir', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"395\">Sometimes, you don&rsquo;t need grand palaces or perfectly manicured terraces. Sometimes, all you need is a little space, a soft breeze, and the sound of water flowing nearby. That&rsquo;s exactly what <strong data-start=\"369\" data-end=\"386\">Harwan Garden</strong> gave me.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"613\">Nestled at the base of the Zabarwan hills, Harwan feels more like a retreat than a tourist spot. There are no crowds, no noise&mdash;just wide open lawns, tall chinar trees, and a cold stream weaving gently through it all.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"615\" data-end=\"852\">I spent a lazy afternoon here, lying on the grass, watching sunlight filter through leaves. Locals strolled by, some with families, some alone, and no one seemed in a rush. That&rsquo;s the charm of Harwan&mdash;it <strong data-start=\"818\" data-end=\"836\">slows you down</strong> without asking.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"854\" data-end=\"1015\">What I loved most was how natural it felt. Less formal, more real. Kids were playing, elders were chatting under the trees, and everything felt... human. Honest.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1017\" data-end=\"1200\">If you\'re in Srinagar and want a break from the busy, postcard-perfect spots, go to Harwan. Sit by the stream, listen to the breeze, and let the silence do what it does best&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1191\" data-end=\"1199\">heal</strong>.</p>', '1745660403.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:40:03', '2025-04-26 09:40:03'),
(39, 'Patnitop: Wrapped in Pines and Quiet', 'patnitop-wrapped-in-pines-and-quiet', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"162\" data-end=\"391\">The first thing you notice in <strong data-start=\"192\" data-end=\"204\">Patnitop</strong> is the air&mdash;cool, clean, and carrying the scent of pine. It&rsquo;s the kind of place that doesn&rsquo;t just feel like a break from the world, it feels like a deep breath you didn&rsquo;t know you needed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"393\" data-end=\"730\">Perched in the Jammu region, Patnitop isn&rsquo;t about flashy landmarks or tourist crowds. It&rsquo;s about <strong data-start=\"490\" data-end=\"499\">peace</strong>. Rolling meadows, tall deodar trees, and winding trails that invite you to walk slowly, look around, and just be. I remember sitting on a patch of grass with the sun warming my back and thinking, <em data-start=\"696\" data-end=\"730\">why don&rsquo;t we do this more often?</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"732\" data-end=\"983\">Locals here are kind in that quiet, genuine way. A tea seller poured me a cup of kehwa without a word, just a smile. I watched families picnic, children race up tiny hills, and couples wander hand in hand, saying nothing&mdash;but somehow saying everything.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"985\" data-end=\"1088\">And when the fog rolls in&mdash;soft, slow, and silver&mdash;it feels like the whole world is pausing for a moment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1090\" data-end=\"1308\">If you&rsquo;re tired of noise, of rush, of always having somewhere to be, <strong data-start=\"1159\" data-end=\"1171\">Patnitop</strong> gives you permission to stop. To listen to the wind through the trees. To watch clouds drift by. To feel small in the best possible way.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1310\" data-end=\"1353\">Come for the views. Stay for the stillness.</p>', '1745660602.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:43:22', '2025-04-26 09:43:22'),
(40, 'Zojila Pass: Where Roads Dare and Mountains Roar', 'zojila-pass-where-roads-dare-and-mountains-roar', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"168\" data-end=\"403\">There are places that humble you&mdash;and then there&rsquo;s&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"218\" data-end=\"233\">Zojila Pass</strong>. Winding its way through the mighty Himalayas, this high-altitude mountain pass isn&rsquo;t just a road&mdash;it&rsquo;s an experience you feel in your chest, your breath, and your bones.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"405\" data-end=\"681\">As we drove up from Sonamarg, the air grew thinner and the silence louder. Jagged cliffs stood tall on one side, and deep valleys yawned on the other. The road was narrow, unpredictable, and thrilling&mdash;a kind of adventure that keeps your heart just a little faster than normal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"683\" data-end=\"1013\">But in the middle of that ruggedness, there was something deeply moving. Snow-dusted peaks surrounded us like guardians. The wind was sharp, yes, but it carried a kind of freedom with it. And when we finally reached the top&mdash;<strong data-start=\"907\" data-end=\"938\">11,649 feet above sea level</strong>&mdash;I just stood there, letting the cold hit my face and the vastness sink in.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1015\" data-end=\"1163\">Zojila isn&rsquo;t polished or gentle. It&rsquo;s raw. Fierce. Alive. It reminds you how powerful nature is&mdash;and how small, yet lucky, we are to move through it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1165\" data-end=\"1400\">Locals call it the lifeline between Kashmir and Ladakh. Soldiers, truckers, shepherds&mdash;they all pass through here, day after day, in all kinds of weather. And you realize: this isn&rsquo;t just a road. It&rsquo;s courage, carved into the mountains.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1402\" data-end=\"1531\">If you ever find yourself on this route, don&rsquo;t rush. Stop. Look around. Let Zojila show you what strength and beauty really mean.</p>', '1745660949.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:49:09', '2025-04-26 09:49:09'),
(41, 'Nigeen Lake: Kashmir‚Äôs Quiet Escape', 'nigeen-lake-kashmirs-quiet-escape', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"157\" data-end=\"341\">If Dal Lake is the crown of Srinagar, then <strong data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"215\">Nigeen Lake</strong> is the quiet, peaceful jewel tucked just beside it&mdash;less crowded, more serene, and full of charm that creeps up on you slowly.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"343\" data-end=\"606\">I first found myself there on a misty morning, the kind where the world feels soft and the air is thick with stillness. As I stepped onto a shikara, the soft creak of the boat beneath me was the only sound, and for a moment, I felt like I was floating in a dream.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"1040\">Nigeen Lake is sometimes called &ldquo;the jewel in the heart of Srinagar,&rdquo; and I quickly understood why. The water is calm, reflecting the distant mountains, and there&rsquo;s an undeniable sense of peace here. You can still see the houseboats bobbing gently, but they feel like a part of the landscape, not an interruption. The trees that line the lake seem to bow slightly, offering a kind of silent blessing to those who come here to pause.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1042\" data-end=\"1391\">I paddled slowly through the lake, past willow trees that dipped their branches in the water and small wooden shikaras carrying locals going about their day. In the distance, the snow-covered peaks of the Himalayas added a touch of majesty to the scene. It felt like nature&rsquo;s own version of quiet luxury&mdash;nothing too grand, but everything just right.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1393\" data-end=\"1764\">What I love about Nigeen is how unhurried it is. It&rsquo;s a place for reflection, for sitting still, for watching the way the light dances on the water as evening falls. Locals smile, greet you in the most gentle way, and invite you to share a cup of saffron tea on their houseboats. There&rsquo;s no rush here&mdash;just a deep, soulful calm that makes you want to stay a little longer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1766\" data-end=\"2019\">If Dal Lake is the heart of Srinagar, <strong data-start=\"1804\" data-end=\"1814\">Nigeen</strong> is its soul. If you&rsquo;re ever in Kashmir, don&rsquo;t just visit&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1872\" data-end=\"1882\">linger</strong>. Let it show you how peaceful life can be when you step away from the noise and find a little corner of the world where time slows down.</p>', '1745661335.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:55:35', '2025-04-26 09:55:35'),
(42, 'Wular Lake: The Majestic Heart of Kashmir', 'wular-lake-the-majestic-heart-of-kashmir', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"120\" data-end=\"356\">Larger than life and less visited,&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"155\" data-end=\"169\">Wular Lake</strong> holds a quiet kind of power. Situated in the heart of Kashmir, it stretches endlessly, surrounded by hills and reeds that sway in the breeze. The air here is different&mdash;cool and peaceful.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"358\" data-end=\"597\">Unlike Dal Lake&rsquo;s touristy buzz, Wular feels raw, untamed, and ancient. I watched fishermen glide across its surface, their boats cutting through the calm water. It&rsquo;s the kind of place where time slows down, and you can&rsquo;t help but reflect.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"599\" data-end=\"710\">If you&rsquo;re looking for a slice of Kashmir untouched by the crowds,&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"665\" data-end=\"674\">Wular</strong> offers it in full, tranquil beauty.</p>', '1745661592.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 09:59:52', '2025-04-26 09:59:52'),
(43, 'Tarsar & Marsar: Kashmir‚Äôs Twin Jewels in the Mountains', 'tarsar-marsar-kashmirs-twin-jewels-in-the-mountains', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"218\" data-end=\"505\">Sometimes, the journey is as breathtaking as the destination&mdash;and that&rsquo;s exactly how I felt on the trek to <strong data-start=\"324\" data-end=\"351\">Tarsar and Marsar Lakes</strong>. Tucked high in the Kashmir Valley, these twin lakes seem to exist in a world of their own, where the earth meets the sky and everything else falls away.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"507\" data-end=\"1006\">The path to Tarsar starts in the meadows, surrounded by wildflowers and the soft hum of the wind. As we ascended, the air grew crisper, the colors more vibrant, and the world around us turned into an untouched, dreamlike landscape. After a day of trekking, the first glimpse of <strong data-start=\"785\" data-end=\"800\">Tarsar Lake</strong> took my breath away&mdash;its waters reflecting the snow-capped peaks above, almost as if the sky had spilled into the ground. It felt like standing at the edge of the world, where everything was pure and still.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1008\" data-end=\"1304\">But the true magic of the lakes lies in their duality. <strong data-start=\"1063\" data-end=\"1078\">Marsar Lake</strong>, just a little higher, is equally stunning&mdash;its waters surrounded by jagged cliffs, framed by a halo of snow. While Tarsar feels soft and inviting, Marsar has an edge, as if it holds the secrets of the mountains in its depths.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1699\" data-end=\"1952\">If you\'re up for an adventure that takes you off the beaten path, and you long for a place that feels untouched by time, <strong data-start=\"1820\" data-end=\"1841\">Tarsar and Marsar</strong> are waiting. They don&rsquo;t just show you the beauty of Kashmir&mdash;they show you how vast and humbling nature can be.</p>', '1745661782.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:03:02', '2025-04-26 10:03:02'),
(44, 'Gangbal Lake: Kashmir‚Äôs Sacred Mirror in the Mountains', 'gangbal-lake-kashmirs-sacred-mirror-in-the-mountains', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"193\" data-end=\"445\">There are places that call to you, gently but insistently, and <strong data-start=\"256\" data-end=\"272\">Gangbal Lake</strong> was one of those for me. Tucked beneath the towering peak of <strong data-start=\"334\" data-end=\"351\">Mount Harmukh</strong>, this sacred alpine lake is a hidden gem, where the world seems to pause and let you breathe.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"447\" data-end=\"881\">The trek to Gangbal is a journey that unfolds slowly&mdash;one step at a time, through dense forests and rugged terrain, with the scent of pine in the air. As I climbed higher, the landscape began to change, revealing alpine meadows and crystal-clear streams that whispered as they passed by. Every corner turned brought something new&mdash;wildflowers, the distant sound of a waterfall, and the promise of something tranquil awaiting at the top.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"883\" data-end=\"1326\">When I finally reached Gangbal Lake, the sight was nothing short of magical. The lake sat quietly, its water so still it mirrored the mountains surrounding it&mdash;sharp, clear reflections as if the sky and earth had melted into one. The silence was profound, only broken by the occasional breeze that stirred the surface, creating ripples that danced like a secret. It&rsquo;s a place that makes you pause, not just to admire its beauty, but to reflect.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1328\" data-end=\"1743\">Locals believe Gangbal is sacred, and I can understand why. It feels like a peaceful haven, a space where the rush of life slows down. The feeling here is unlike anything else&mdash;a blend of spiritual tranquility and natural grandeur. You sit by the shores, watching the light change over the water, and you realize how small you are in the vastness of it all, but at the same time, how deeply connected you feel to it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1745\" data-end=\"1925\">Gangbal isn&rsquo;t just a lake&mdash;it&rsquo;s a reminder of how nature, in its quietest form, has the power to <strong data-start=\"1841\" data-end=\"1849\">heal</strong>, to <strong data-start=\"1854\" data-end=\"1864\">ground</strong>, and to make you feel at home, no matter where you are from.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1927\" data-end=\"2110\">If you&rsquo;re looking for something more than a beautiful view, if you&rsquo;re craving peace, solitude, and a chance to reconnect with nature, <strong data-start=\"2061\" data-end=\"2077\">Gangbal Lake</strong> is the perfect place to find it.</p>', '1745661894.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:04:54', '2025-04-26 10:04:54'),
(45, 'Chashme Shahi: A Mughal Garden of Tranquil Beauty', 'chashme-shahi-a-mughal-garden-of-tranquil-beauty', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"181\" data-end=\"533\">The garden&rsquo;s name, &ldquo;Chashme Shahi,&rdquo; means \"Royal Spring,\" and it&rsquo;s easy to see why. The cool, crystal-clear water flows from a natural spring, and its purity feels like it&rsquo;s been part of the land forever. You can almost feel the history in the air, knowing that the Mughal emperors walked these paths, taking in the same views of the mountains and lake that we do today.<br><br>There&rsquo;s something truly special about <strong data-start=\"219\" data-end=\"236\">Chashme Shahi</strong>&mdash;the way it sits quietly by the side of Dal Lake, its beauty almost understated yet undeniably captivating. I first visited the garden on a warm afternoon, the kind where the sunlight feels soft, and the breeze carries a hint of sweetness. As soon as I stepped in, I knew this place was different.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"535\" data-end=\"932\">Unlike the grandiosity of some other Mughal gardens, Chashme Shahi feels intimate, like a hidden retreat. It&rsquo;s not just the fountains that charm you, though they&rsquo;re spectacular&mdash;they create a soothing rhythm, the sound of water flowing almost like a quiet conversation with nature. It&rsquo;s the <strong data-start=\"825\" data-end=\"843\">careful design</strong>, the <strong data-start=\"849\" data-end=\"890\">balance of water, stone, and greenery</strong> that lets you feel as if time slows down.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1962\">Chashme Shahi isn&rsquo;t just a place to visit; it&rsquo;s a place to <strong data-start=\"1731\" data-end=\"1745\">experience</strong>&mdash;to pause, reflect, and let the beauty of nature soak in. The combination of the cool water, the terraced gardens, and the distant view of Dal Lake makes it a perfect spot to simply sit, breathe, and enjoy the moment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1964\" data-end=\"2240\">If you&rsquo;re ever in Srinagar, don&rsquo;t just walk through Chashme Shahi&mdash;<strong data-start=\"2030\" data-end=\"2040\">linger</strong>. Take a moment to absorb the tranquility, let the gentle flow of water remind you that life doesn&rsquo;t always need to be rushed, and appreciate the quiet majesty of one of Kashmir&rsquo;s most serene gardens.</p>', '1745662120.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:08:40', '2025-04-26 10:08:40'),
(46, 'Warwan Valley: Kashmir‚Äôs Hidden Haven', 'warwan-valley-kashmirs-hidden-haven', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"181\" data-end=\"449\">The road to&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"193\" data-end=\"210\">Warwan Valley</strong> isn&rsquo;t for the faint-hearted. Winding through rugged terrain, steep hills, and scattered villages, the journey is as much an adventure as the destination. But the moment I set foot in Warwan, I knew every twist and turn had been worth it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"451\" data-end=\"803\">Nestled between towering peaks, Warwan feels like a world untouched by time. The first thing that strikes you is the vastness&mdash;the way the valley stretches out beneath snow-capped mountains, with lush meadows and pristine rivers weaving through it all. It&rsquo;s a place where nature isn&rsquo;t just present; it&rsquo;s alive, breathing, and unapologetically beautiful.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"805\" data-end=\"1190\">The valley is remote, which is part of its magic. The roads here are rarely traveled, and the villages seem as though they&rsquo;re from another era, tucked away in a place that feels far from the rush of modern life. The locals, mostly shepherds and farmers, welcome you with a kind of warmth that feels genuine, their lives deeply connected to the land they&rsquo;ve called home for generations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1192\" data-end=\"1608\">I spent my days wandering the valley, marveling at the sheer beauty of it all. The meadows here seem to roll on forever, dotted with wildflowers, and the river runs clear and fast, carving its way through the valley. There&rsquo;s a sense of stillness, a quiet that settles into your bones. It&rsquo;s the kind of place that invites you to slow down, to be in the moment, to take it all in without the distractions of the world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1610\" data-end=\"1866\">Warwan is perfect for those who are looking to escape the noise of everyday life. The silence here is a kind of comfort, a space for reflection, and the air, fresh and untainted, fills your lungs with a sense of peace you don&rsquo;t realize you&rsquo;ve been craving.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2153\" data-end=\"2334\">&nbsp;</p>', '1745662614.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:15:19', '2025-04-26 10:16:54'),
(47, 'Margan Top: Kashmir‚Äôs Hidden Horizon', 'margan-top-kashmirs-hidden-horizon', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"125\" data-end=\"496\">If you&rsquo;re looking for an offbeat adventure in Kashmir, <strong data-start=\"180\" data-end=\"194\">Margan Top</strong> is a place that will steal your heart. Tucked away in the Himalayas, this remote peak offers one of the most breathtaking panoramic views you&rsquo;ll ever witness. The trek to the top is challenging but worth every step, with the landscape changing from dense forests to vast meadows and snow-capped peaks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"498\" data-end=\"814\">At the summit, the silence is profound, broken only by the wind and the occasional birdcall. It feels like you&rsquo;re standing on the edge of the world, surrounded by nature in its purest form. Whether you&rsquo;re a hiker, a nature lover, or simply seeking a quiet escape, Margan Top offers a slice of solitude like no other.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"816\" data-end=\"935\">If you want to experience the untouched beauty of Kashmir, <strong data-start=\"875\" data-end=\"889\">Margan Top</strong> is waiting&mdash;untamed and ready for exploration.</p>', '1745662966.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:22:46', '2025-04-26 10:22:46'),
(48, 'Char Chinar: Kashmir‚Äôs Tranquil Escape on Dal Lake', 'char-chinar-kashmirs-tranquil-escape-on-dal-lake', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"194\" data-end=\"532\"><strong data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"292\">Char Chinar</strong> on <strong data-start=\"296\" data-end=\"308\">Dal Lake</strong> is where that dream comes to life. This little island, with its four grand Chinar trees, is one of Srinagar&rsquo;s most serene spots&mdash;yet it often flies under the radar, making it the perfect place to find solitude amidst nature.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"534\" data-end=\"887\">I took a shikara ride out to Char Chinar one quiet afternoon, and the moment we reached the island, it felt like stepping into another world. The majestic Chinar trees, their leaves a fiery mix of green and gold, stood tall, casting a comforting shade over the island. They seemed to guard the peacefulness that enveloped this hidden corner of Dal Lake.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"889\" data-end=\"1289\">Unlike the bustle of the city, Char Chinar is tranquil&mdash;no crowds, no rush, just the occasional whisper of the wind and the soft lapping of water against the boat. Sitting under the shade of the trees, I felt a sense of stillness that&rsquo;s hard to find these days. The island is small, but it&rsquo;s perfect for reflection, a quiet walk, or simply soaking in the beauty of Dal Lake in its most untouched form.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1291\" data-end=\"1619\">The view from Char Chinar is spectacular too. You look out over Dal Lake, with its houseboats and shikaras drifting lazily by, and in the distance, the misty mountains stand tall and proud, watching over the lake. The scene feels timeless, as if the island has existed for centuries, quietly watching the world change around it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1621\" data-end=\"1864\">For anyone looking to experience Kashmir in a way that&rsquo;s both peaceful and deeply connected to nature, <strong data-start=\"1724\" data-end=\"1739\">Char Chinar</strong> is a must-see. It&rsquo;s a place where you can sit back, breathe deeply, and let the world slow down, if only for a little while.</p>', '1745663145.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:25:45', '2025-04-26 10:25:45');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `image`, `status`, `published_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(49, 'Dargah Hazratbal: Kashmir‚Äôs Sacred Heart', 'dargah-hazratbal-kashmirs-sacred-heart', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"185\" data-end=\"477\">In the heart of Srinagar, by the serene shores of Dal Lake, stands <strong data-start=\"252\" data-end=\"272\">Dargah Hazratbal</strong>&mdash;a place of immense spiritual significance and tranquility. This revered shrine, dedicated to Hazratbal, is more than just a landmark; it&rsquo;s a living testament to the faith, history, and culture of Kashmir.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"479\" data-end=\"973\">I first visited Hazratbal on a quiet morning, the mist still clinging to the surface of Dal Lake. As I approached the shrine by shikara, the pristine white marble dome of the Dargah stood out against the backdrop of the snow-capped mountains, radiating a sense of calm that reached deep within. There&rsquo;s something undeniably peaceful about this place&mdash;the gentle ripple of water, the soft murmur of prayers, and the cool breeze that sweeps across the lake make it feel like time has stopped here.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"975\" data-end=\"1384\">Stepping into the shrine felt like stepping into a different realm. The air was thick with devotion, with locals and visitors alike quietly paying their respects. Inside, the atmosphere was serene, filled with an aura of reverence. The relic believed to be the hair of Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) is kept here, and it is said to be visible only on certain occasions, adding an air of sacred mystery to the shrine.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1386\" data-end=\"1730\">But Hazratbal is not just about the relic or the history; it&rsquo;s about the feeling that the place evokes. There&rsquo;s a deep sense of peace that washes over you as you sit by the shores, looking at the shrine across the water. It&rsquo;s a place for reflection, for prayer, and for reconnecting with the spirituality that runs through the heart of Kashmir.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1732\" data-end=\"1998\">As the sun began to set, casting a golden glow over the lake, I felt deeply moved by the beauty and tranquility of Hazratbal. It&rsquo;s not just a spiritual destination; it&rsquo;s a place that invites you to slow down, breathe, and appreciate the calm in the world around you.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2201\">If you ever find yourself in Srinagar, <strong data-start=\"2039\" data-end=\"2059\">Dargah Hazratbal</strong> is more than just a place to visit&mdash;it&rsquo;s a place to feel. To connect with the profound silence and the deep spirituality that defines Kashmir.</p>', '1745663469.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:31:09', '2025-04-26 10:31:09'),
(50, 'Jamia Masjid: Where Silence Speaks in Wood and Stone', 'jamia-masjid-where-silence-speaks-in-wood-and-stone', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"522\">Tucked into the heart of Srinagar&rsquo;s bustling <strong data-start=\"234\" data-end=\"246\">Old City</strong>, the <strong data-start=\"252\" data-end=\"268\">Jamia Masjid</strong> rises with quiet grace&mdash;a striking wooden structure surrounded by the echo of centuries. It doesn&rsquo;t shout for attention. Instead, it invites you in with stillness, with symmetry, and with a spiritual calm that wraps around you the moment you step inside.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"524\" data-end=\"796\">Walking through the narrow alleys of <strong data-start=\"561\" data-end=\"573\">Nowhatta</strong>, past shops, tea stalls, and the hum of daily life, you suddenly find yourself at the gates of the mosque&mdash;and everything slows down. The noise fades. The chaos settles. And in front of you stands a piece of Kashmir&rsquo;s soul.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"798\" data-end=\"1164\">Built in the 14th century by Sultan Sikandar and later expanded by Zain-ul-Abidin, <strong data-start=\"881\" data-end=\"897\">Jamia Masjid</strong> is unlike any other mosque in India. Its Indo-Islamic architecture is carved almost entirely out of wood, supported by <strong data-start=\"1017\" data-end=\"1048\">378 majestic wooden pillars</strong>, each one standing like a silent witness to the prayers, hopes, and histories that have echoed through these halls.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1166\" data-end=\"1533\">I visited during the afternoon, when the courtyard was bathed in soft sunlight, and the scent of old wood lingered in the air. A few people sat in quiet prayer, others simply resting under the open sky that the courtyard frames so beautifully. The entire space felt like a deep breath&mdash;a place where faith lives not just in ritual, but in the quiet moments in between.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1535\" data-end=\"1792\">There&rsquo;s something timeless about Jamia Masjid. It doesn&rsquo;t dazzle&mdash;it grounds. It reminds you that spirituality isn&rsquo;t always loud or ornate. Sometimes, it&rsquo;s carved in cedar, whispered in the rustling chinar leaves, or found in the silence between two prayers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1794\" data-end=\"1968\">If you&rsquo;re in Srinagar and want to experience not just the architecture, but the <strong data-start=\"1874\" data-end=\"1882\">soul</strong> of the city, make your way to <strong data-start=\"1913\" data-end=\"1929\">Jamia Masjid</strong>. Sit for a while. Let the quiet speak.</p>', '1745663615.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:33:35', '2025-04-26 10:33:35'),
(51, 'Badamwari: Where Kashmir Wakes Up in Blossoms', 'badamwari-where-kashmir-wakes-up-in-blossoms', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"184\" data-end=\"436\">Spring in Kashmir doesn&rsquo;t tiptoe in&mdash;it arrives with a soft pink explosion at <strong data-start=\"261\" data-end=\"281\">Badamwari Garden</strong>. Nestled at the foot of Hari Parbat in Srinagar, this hidden gem isn&rsquo;t just a garden&mdash;it&rsquo;s a celebration of life&rsquo;s gentle return after a long, cold winter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"438\" data-end=\"845\">I visited Badamwari on a crisp March morning, and the sight stopped me in my tracks. <strong data-start=\"523\" data-end=\"553\">Almond trees in full bloom</strong>, their branches heavy with soft white and blush-pink flowers, danced in the breeze like they had waited all year just for this moment. The scent in the air was light and sweet, and the ground was speckled with fallen petals&mdash;like spring itself had made a quiet entrance, barefoot and smiling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"847\" data-end=\"1249\">Locals wandered between the trees, many of them carrying thermoses of kehwa or cups of tea, chatting under the blossoms as if they were visiting old friends. Kids ran across the lawns, families sat in circles sharing snacks, and laughter floated through the air like pollen. It felt less like a tourist spot and more like <strong data-start=\"1169\" data-end=\"1191\">Kashmir&rsquo;s backyard</strong>, where people come to breathe again after months of snow.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1251\" data-end=\"1505\">But even in its buzz, Badamwari holds moments of quiet. I found a bench under a blooming tree, sat back, and just listened&mdash;to the birds, the breeze, and the soft murmur of happiness all around. It wasn&rsquo;t loud joy. It was gentle, rooted, and deeply human.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1507\" data-end=\"1757\">Badamwari doesn&rsquo;t stay in bloom for long, and maybe that&rsquo;s why it feels so special. It\'s fleeting, like all beautiful things. But for a few short weeks, it reminds everyone&mdash;locals and visitors alike&mdash;that even the coldest winters give way to blossoms.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1759\" data-end=\"1882\">If you ever find yourself in Kashmir as winter fades, <strong data-start=\"1813\" data-end=\"1837\">don&rsquo;t miss Badamwari</strong>. Come for the flowers, stay for the feeling.</p>', '1745663749.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:35:49', '2025-04-26 10:35:49'),
(52, 'Hari Parbat Fort: The Stone Sentinel of Srinagar', 'hari-parbat-fort-the-stone-sentinel-of-srinagar', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"221\" data-end=\"483\">Perched high above Srinagar, <strong data-start=\"250\" data-end=\"270\">Hari Parbat Fort</strong> doesn&rsquo;t just stand&mdash;it <strong data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"304\">watches</strong>. From its stone ramparts, the entire city stretches below like a painted story, with Dal Lake shimmering in the distance and the mountains wrapping the valley in a quiet embrace.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"485\" data-end=\"890\">Climbing up to the fort isn&rsquo;t just a physical journey&mdash;it feels like you\'re walking back through time. The path winds gently, past ancient walls and wildflowers, each step echoing with the weight of centuries. Originally built by the Mughals and later fortified by the Durrani rulers, <strong data-start=\"769\" data-end=\"784\">Hari Parbat</strong> is more than just a stronghold&mdash;it&rsquo;s a <strong data-start=\"823\" data-end=\"844\">keeper of stories</strong>, layered with cultures, empires, and beliefs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"892\" data-end=\"1198\">As I reached the top, the breeze caught me first&mdash;cool, clean, and carrying the faint scent of pine and stone. The fort, though weathered, stands proud. Inside, it&rsquo;s quiet. There are no grand halls or bustling crowds, just long corridors, thick walls, and windows that frame the world like living paintings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1200\" data-end=\"1512\">But what struck me most wasn&rsquo;t just the architecture or the history&mdash;it was the <strong data-start=\"1279\" data-end=\"1287\">view</strong>. From up there, <strong data-start=\"1304\" data-end=\"1316\">Srinagar</strong> feels small, peaceful. The chaos of markets, the winding streets, the calm of the lake&mdash;all melt into one. It&rsquo;s the kind of place where you sit down, take a deep breath, and feel completely still.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1514\" data-end=\"1688\">Hari Parbat Fort isn&rsquo;t flashy. It doesn&rsquo;t scream for attention. But it offers something rarer&mdash;a moment to feel connected. To history, to the land, and maybe even to yourself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1690\" data-end=\"1920\">If you ever want to see Srinagar from a different lens&mdash;from above, with a sense of calm and perspective&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1794\" data-end=\"1820\">walk up to Hari Parbat</strong>. Let the fort tell you its stories. And in the silence between its stones, you might hear your own.</p>', '1745663931.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:38:51', '2025-04-26 10:38:51'),
(53, 'Betaab Valley: Where Kashmir Feels Like a Dream', 'betaab-valley-where-kashmir-feels-like-a-dream', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"415\">The first time I saw&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"217\">Betaab Valley</strong>, I didn&rsquo;t say much. I just stood there, quietly, letting the view wash over me. It looked like something out of a postcard&mdash;but real. So real, in fact, that I had to remind myself I wasn&rsquo;t dreaming.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"417\" data-end=\"763\">Tucked between <strong data-start=\"432\" data-end=\"444\">Pahalgam</strong> and the hills of <strong data-start=\"462\" data-end=\"469\">Aru</strong>, Betaab Valley is where the mountains lean in close, the Lidder River runs wild and free, and the meadows stretch like velvet under your feet. Named after a Bollywood film shot here, the valley may be famous&mdash;but when you\'re standing there, it doesn&rsquo;t feel like a movie set. It feels <strong data-start=\"753\" data-end=\"762\">alive</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"765\" data-end=\"1004\">There&rsquo;s something about the way the river dances through the valley, the way the wind carries the scent of pine and earth, the way the snow-dusted peaks hold the sky&mdash;it slows you down. Makes you listen. Not just to nature, but to yourself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1308\">I walked along the riverbank, boots crunching softly on gravel, heart a little fuller with every breath. Locals smiled as they passed by, wrapped in warmth and simplicity. And all around, there was this quiet magic&mdash;<strong data-start=\"1221\" data-end=\"1242\">not loud or showy</strong>, just the kind that reminds you how beautiful the world still is.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1310\" data-end=\"1428\">Betaab isn&rsquo;t just a place you visit. It&rsquo;s a place you feel. A moment of peace tucked inside the wild heart of Kashmir.</p>', '1745665155.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 10:59:15', '2025-04-26 10:59:15'),
(54, 'Keran Valley: Where Kashmir Whispers from the Border', 'keran-valley-where-kashmir-whispers-from-the-border', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"216\" data-end=\"516\">Some places don&rsquo;t just feel remote&mdash;they feel sacred, like the earth has chosen to stay quiet there. <strong data-start=\"316\" data-end=\"332\">Keran Valley</strong>, resting right along the Line of Control in North Kashmir, is one of those rare gems. A place where the noise of the world fades, and all that remains is <strong data-start=\"487\" data-end=\"515\">mountain, river, and sky</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"518\" data-end=\"957\">The road to Keran winds through thick forests and sleepy villages, each turn pulling you further into a quieter version of Kashmir. And then suddenly, the view opens up&mdash;green meadows sloping gently down to the <strong data-start=\"728\" data-end=\"749\">Kishanganga River</strong>, which flows like a ribbon between <strong data-start=\"785\" data-end=\"807\">India and Pakistan</strong>, calm but watchful. Across the water, you can see houses on the other side&mdash;so close, yet unreachable. It\'s surreal, beautiful, and a little haunting.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"959\" data-end=\"1315\">But Keran isn&rsquo;t defined by politics or borders. It&rsquo;s defined by its <strong data-start=\"1027\" data-end=\"1037\">people</strong>, its <strong data-start=\"1043\" data-end=\"1056\">stillness</strong>, and its <strong data-start=\"1066\" data-end=\"1085\">unshaken beauty</strong>. The locals are warm and deeply rooted to the land. Time moves slowly here&mdash;measured not by clocks, but by the rhythm of nature. Children play in open fields, women tend to gardens, and the air feels lighter, almost like a prayer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1317\" data-end=\"1633\">I stayed in a simple wooden guesthouse, with nothing but the sound of the river and the occasional call of a bird. At night, under a blanket of stars, it felt like the valley was <strong data-start=\"1496\" data-end=\"1515\">breathing peace</strong>. It&rsquo;s hard to describe how healing that silence was&mdash;how much it made me listen, not just to the place, but to myself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1635\" data-end=\"1762\">Keran isn&rsquo;t a tourist spot. It&rsquo;s a soul-space. A reminder that even on the edge of conflict, <strong data-start=\"1728\" data-end=\"1761\">beauty and kindness can bloom</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1764\" data-end=\"1916\">If you&rsquo;re ever lucky enough to make it here, don&rsquo;t come just to see it. <strong data-start=\"1836\" data-end=\"1856\">Come to feel it.</strong> Keran has a way of staying with you long after you&rsquo;ve left.</p>', '1745666035.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 11:13:55', '2025-04-26 11:13:55'),
(55, 'Aru Valley: A Quiet Poem in Green and Sk', 'aru-valley-a-quiet-poem-in-green-and-sk', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"174\" data-end=\"440\">There are places that speak to the soul in whispers, not shouts&mdash;and&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"242\" data-end=\"256\">Aru Valley</strong> is one of them. Just a short drive from the more famous <strong data-start=\"313\" data-end=\"325\">Pahalgam</strong>, Aru feels like its quieter, softer cousin&mdash;the kind of place you go to lose your hurry and find your breath again.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"442\" data-end=\"799\">The road to Aru is a gentle climb, winding past forests, streams, and meadows that seem to stretch endlessly into the arms of snow-capped mountains. The air gets cooler, crisper. The noise of the world starts to fall away. And then suddenly, you&rsquo;re there&mdash;in a valley so perfectly still, it feels like you&rsquo;ve stepped into a painting someone forgot to finish.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"801\" data-end=\"1156\">I arrived in the late afternoon. The light was golden, casting long shadows across wooden cottages, grazing horses, and fields that shimmered like velvet. It wasn&rsquo;t just beautiful&mdash;it was <strong data-start=\"988\" data-end=\"1024\">peaceful in a way that felt rare</strong>. Kids laughed in the distance, a river murmured nearby, and every now and then, the wind carried the scent of pine and wildflowers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1158\" data-end=\"1451\">Aru isn&rsquo;t about big sights or busy itineraries. It&rsquo;s about slowing down. Wandering through meadows. Watching clouds curl around the peaks. Drinking kehwa while wrapped in a blanket, with nothing to do and nowhere to be. And maybe that&rsquo;s what makes it magical&mdash;it gives you space to just <strong data-start=\"1444\" data-end=\"1450\">be</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1453\" data-end=\"1669\">At night, the sky opened up like a storybook of stars. No filters. No streetlights. Just the Milky Way stretched across the heavens, and the kind of silence that makes you realize how much noise we live in every day.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1671\" data-end=\"1861\">&nbsp;</p>', '1745666404.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 11:20:04', '2025-04-26 11:20:04'),
(56, 'Naranag: Where Silence Meets the Sacre', 'naranag-where-silence-meets-the-sacre', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"177\">In the heart of Kashmir, far from the crowded tourist spots and the noise of the world, lies <strong data-start=\"272\" data-end=\"283\">Naranag</strong>&mdash;a quiet village tucked in the foothills of the mighty <strong data-start=\"338\" data-end=\"351\">Himalayas</strong>. It&rsquo;s a place where time feels different, where the rhythm of life is set by the rising and setting of the sun, and the silence of nature.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"492\" data-end=\"905\">Naranag is known for its ancient <strong data-start=\"525\" data-end=\"541\">temple ruins</strong>, believed to be built in the 8th century by King Avantivarman. The ruins are both humbling and awe-inspiring. As I wandered around the stone structures, I could almost feel the weight of the centuries pressing gently down. <strong data-start=\"765\" data-end=\"785\">The sacred space</strong> here doesn&rsquo;t just come from the temples&mdash;it&rsquo;s in the air, in the mountain breeze, and in the quiet whispers of the past.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"907\" data-end=\"1364\">The journey to Naranag is half the magic. The roads take you through green meadows, thick pine forests, and the soft rush of streams that cut through the valley. It&rsquo;s a place where the mountains are close enough to touch but far enough to keep you in awe. As you walk through the village, you might hear the call of a shepherd or the distant hum of a prayer. Everything feels <strong data-start=\"1283\" data-end=\"1295\">grounded</strong>, like you&rsquo;ve found a secret pocket of Kashmir that most people miss.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1366\" data-end=\"1708\">At the foot of the temple ruins, I paused for a moment. The only sounds were the chirping of birds, the rustle of leaves, and the distant roar of the mountain streams. There was a peace here that was rare, almost sacred. You can&rsquo;t help but feel connected to the land, the history, and the people who have called this place home for centuries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1710\" data-end=\"1915\">Naranag isn&rsquo;t just a place to visit&mdash;it&rsquo;s a place to experience. It&rsquo;s where you can <strong data-start=\"1793\" data-end=\"1811\">breathe deeply</strong>, feel the weight of history in your bones, and leave with a sense of calm you won&rsquo;t find anywhere else.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1917\" data-end=\"2110\">So if you&rsquo;re ever in Kashmir, take the detour. <strong data-start=\"1964\" data-end=\"1993\">Find your way to Naranag.</strong> Let the ruins speak to you, let the mountains hold you, and let the peace of this hidden valley seep into your soul.</p>', '1745666579.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 11:22:59', '2025-04-26 11:22:59'),
(57, 'Chandanwari: The Gateway to Serenity', 'chandanwari-the-gateway-to-serenity', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"184\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"186\" data-end=\"565\">If Kashmir is the land of unmatched beauty, then <strong data-start=\"235\" data-end=\"250\">Chandanwari</strong> is one of its most peaceful corners. Nestled in the foothills of the <strong data-start=\"320\" data-end=\"333\">Himalayas</strong>, just a few kilometers from <strong data-start=\"362\" data-end=\"374\">Pahalgam</strong>, Chandanwari feels like the beginning of something sacred. It&rsquo;s a place where the air smells of pine, the mountains stand tall and proud, and the land seems to breathe in rhythm with nature.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"821\">Chandanwari is perhaps most famous as the starting point for the <strong data-start=\"632\" data-end=\"650\">Amarnath Yatra</strong>, a pilgrimage that draws thousands of devotees every year. But beyond its religious significance, it&rsquo;s a spot that invites you to pause, to breathe, and to simply <strong data-start=\"814\" data-end=\"820\">be</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"823\" data-end=\"1183\">When I visited, the valley was still waking up from winter. The <strong data-start=\"887\" data-end=\"908\">snow-capped peaks</strong> surrounding Chandanwari reflected the soft morning light, casting a peaceful glow on everything below. The river flowed calmly, its waters clear and cold, while the meadows were just beginning to show hints of green, as if the earth was slowly stretching after a long sleep.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1185\" data-end=\"1532\">As I stood on the banks of the river, I realized that Chandanwari is about much more than a destination&mdash;it&rsquo;s about <strong data-start=\"1300\" data-end=\"1311\">journey</strong>. The path ahead, whether for pilgrims or travelers like me, leads to something greater. It&rsquo;s a space to reflect, to connect with the natural world, and to discover a quiet peace you won&rsquo;t find in the hustle of city life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1534\" data-end=\"1787\">Locals greeted me with smiles, their faces warm and welcoming despite the cold mountain air. <strong data-start=\"1627\" data-end=\"1642\">Chandanwari</strong>, with its simple beauty and untouched landscapes, feels like a place where life is lived slowly, where people are rooted in nature and in faith.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2143\" data-end=\"2322\">if you ever find yourself in Kashmir, make your way to&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2217\">Chandanwari</strong>. It&rsquo;s not just the beginning of a pilgrimage&mdash;it&rsquo;s the beginning of finding peace, within and around you.</p>', '1745666757.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-26 11:25:57', '2025-04-26 11:25:57'),
(58, 'Buta Pathri: Kashmir‚Äôs Hidden Meadow', 'buta-pathri-kashmirs-hidden-meadow', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"126\" data-end=\"490\"><strong data-start=\"163\" data-end=\"178\">Buta Pathri</strong> (also called Botapathri) feels like a secret the mountains are keeping. Unlike the touristy hustle of Gulmarg, Buta Pathri greets you with quiet meadows, tall deodar trees, and a silence that speaks peace. The air is crisp, the flowers wild, and the only crowds you\'ll find are grazing sheep and chirping birds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"492\" data-end=\"695\">Locals call it <strong data-start=\"507\" data-end=\"523\">Nagin Valley</strong>, and in summer, it\'s a dreamscape&mdash;lush green, dotted with Gujjar huts, and perfect for slow walks or thoughtful picnics. It&rsquo;s not just a place to see, but a place to feel.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"697\" data-end=\"855\">If you\'re in Gulmarg and want to step off the beaten path, this is your pause button. Just remember&mdash;it&rsquo;s close to the border, so check permissions beforehand.</p>', '1745832852.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 09:34:12', '2025-04-28 09:34:12'),
(59, 'Khilanmarg: A Tranquil Retreat in Gulmarg', 'khilanmarg-a-tranquil-retreat-in-gulmarg', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Khilanmarg </strong>is a picturesque valley situated approximately 6 km from Gulmarg, nestled in the Baramulla district of Jammu and Kashmir.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">This serene locale is renowned for its breathtaking views of the Himalayan peaks, including Nanga Parbat, and offers a tranquil escape amidst nature\'s beauty.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Khilanmarg boasts panoramic views of the majestic Himalayan peaks, including Nanga Parbat and the twin summits of Nun and Kun. The valley is adorned with wildflowers during spring and summer, transforming it into a vibrant tapestry of colors. In winter, it becomes a snow-covered wonderland, ideal for snow sports enthusiasts.</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"515\" data-end=\"650\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"517\" data-end=\"650\"><strong data-start=\"517\" data-end=\"529\">Trekking</strong>: <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Embark on treks that provide stunning vistas of the surrounding valley and peaks. The route to Alpather Lake, a high-altitude lake surrounded by snow-capped peaks, is particularly popular among trekkers</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"652\" data-end=\"795\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"654\" data-end=\"795\"><strong data-start=\"654\" data-end=\"670\">Horse Riding</strong>: <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Enjoy pony rides that take you up to Khilanmarg Snow Point or around the meadow, allowing you to experience the landscape in a unique way.</span> ‚Äã</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"652\" data-end=\"795\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"654\" data-end=\"795\"><strong data-start=\"799\" data-end=\"814\">Photography</strong>: <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Capture the panoramic views, especially during the golden hours of sunrise and sunset, when the soft sunlight illuminates the landscape in warm tones.</span> ‚Äã</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1745833252.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 09:40:52', '2025-04-28 09:40:52'),
(60, 'Exploring the Mystical Alpather Frozen Lake: A Winter Wonderland', 'exploring-the-mystical-alpather-frozen-lake-a-winter-wonderland', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Alpather Lake, often referred to as the <strong>\"Frozen Lake,\"</strong> is a captivating destination nestled at the foot of the twin Apharwat Peaks in Gulmarg, Jammu &amp; Kashmir.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">This high-altitude glacial lake remains frozen from November to June, offering a surreal experience for trekkers and nature enthusiast.<br><br>its Situated at an elevation of approximately <strong>4,390 meters (14,400 feet)</strong> above sea level, Alpather Lake is surrounded by rugged terrain and snow-capped peaks, making it a picturesque spot for photography and nature walks.<br><br>In winter, the lake\'s surface freezes completely, creating a mirror-like effect surrounded by snow-covered terrain.<br><br>The trek to Alpather Lake is a rewarding experience. The journey offers stunning views of the surrounding mountains and valleys. It\'s advisable to start early, preferably around 5 AM, to complete the trek during daylight hours. The terrain can be challenging, so proper footwear and physical preparation are recommended..<br></span></p>', '1745833620.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 09:47:00', '2025-04-28 09:47:00'),
(61, 'A Journey Through Gogaldara: Kashmir‚Äôs Unseen Paradise', 'a-journey-through-gogaldara-kashmirs-unseen-paradise', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"54\" data-end=\"67\">Gogaldara</strong> is a tranquil village in the Gulmarg tehsil of Baramulla district.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Approximately 13 kilometers from Tangmarg, this picturesque location offers a peaceful retreat for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] bg-[#FCECC1] dark:bg-[#64572A] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">One of Gogaldara\'s standout features is the <strong data-start=\"44\" data-end=\"59\">Chill Point</strong>, a remarkable 35-foot icicle formation surrounded by snow-covered pine forests.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] bg-[#FCECC1] dark:bg-[#64572A] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">This natural wonder has become a focal point for tourists, photographers, and social media enthusiasts, drawing visitors from various parts of India.</span> The unique combination of the towering icicle and the pristine forest backdrop creates a surreal, dreamlike atmosphere that captivates all who visit. ‚Äã</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2544\" data-end=\"2669\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Gogaldara, with its untouched beauty and authentic experiences, offers a refreshing escape from the bustling tourist spots.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Whether you\'re seeking adventure, tranquility, or a glimpse into the local culture, Gogaldara promises a memorable journey.</span>‚Äã</p>', '1745834912.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 10:08:32', '2025-04-28 10:08:32'),
(62, 'Discovering Sheeshnag: The Mystical Lake of Kashmir', 'discovering-sheeshnag-the-mystical-lake-of-kashmir', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"356\" data-end=\"656\">The name <strong>\"Sheeshnag\"</strong> translates to<strong> \"King of Serpents,\"</strong> and there\'s an interesting legend tied to it. It&rsquo;s believed that the lake is guarded by a massive serpent, a mythical protector of the waters. This adds to the aura of mystery surrounding the lake. Some say that the water here is so clear that it reflects the sky like a mirror, but it&rsquo;s also thought that the lake hides secrets deep within its depths.<br><br></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"658\" data-end=\"918\">Nestled between the mesmerizing peaks of the Pir Panjal Range, Sheeshnag is one of the most breathtaking alpine lakes in the region. It&rsquo;s located at an elevation of around 3,600 meters (11,800 feet), and let me tell you, it&rsquo;s every bit as magical as it sounds.<br><br>The road to Sheeshnag is not your regular, easy stroll. This is a trek that calls for a bit of stamina and a lot of enthusiasm. Whether you&rsquo;re beginning from Pahalgam, which is a popular base, or directly from the Amarnath Yatra route, the journey to Sheeshnag will take you through dense pine forests, grassy meadows, and rocky terrains. And while the path may be challenging, the beauty surrounding you will keep your spirits high.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"658\" data-end=\"918\">This blog approach presents Sheeshnag as not just a travel destination but an emotional and spiritual experience. It brings a personal connection and tells a story that can resonate with readers, drawing them into the charm of Sheeshnag.</p>', '1745835999.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 10:26:39', '2025-04-28 10:26:39'),
(63, 'Baltal: The Gateway to Adventure in Kashmir', 'baltal-the-gateway-to-adventure-in-kashmir', '<p>Kashmir is a place that seems to have it all &ndash; the snow-covered peaks, green meadows, and crystal-clear rivers. But there&rsquo;s one little gem that doesn&rsquo;t always make it to the top of tourist lists, and that&rsquo;s <strong data-start=\"393\" data-end=\"403\">Baltal</strong>. Tucked away in the stunning Sonamarg Valley, Baltal is a quieter corner of this paradise that feels like it&rsquo;s waiting to be discovered.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"580\" data-end=\"1012\">f you\'re heading to Baltal, you\'re already in for something special. The journey to this magical place starts in <strong data-start=\"694\" data-end=\"706\">Sonamarg</strong>, where the road leads you through a landscape so beautiful it almost feels like a dream. The crisp mountain air hits you, and the sound of the <strong data-start=\"850\" data-end=\"865\">Sindh River</strong> rushing nearby fills your senses. You can already feel the change from the usual hustle of city life to the peaceful tranquility of the mountains.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1014\" data-end=\"1327\">It&rsquo;s not a place that tries to impress you with flashy attractions or a busy scene. Instead, Baltal gently pulls you in with its simplicity. The mountains here don&rsquo;t try too hard&mdash;they just <em data-start=\"1203\" data-end=\"1208\">are</em>, standing tall and majestic, and the meadows are peaceful with the kind of beauty that takes time to fully appreciate.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1014\" data-end=\"1327\">The <strong data-start=\"2506\" data-end=\"2521\">Sindh River</strong>, snaking its way through the valley, adds a sense of serenity that&rsquo;s hard to put into words. The sound of the water, the quiet chirps of birds in the distance, and the fresh mountain air&mdash;all combine to make you feel as if you\'re in a completely different world, one that&rsquo;s untouched and unhurried. It&rsquo;s the kind of place where you stop for a moment and realize how much we often miss in our busy lives.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1014\" data-end=\"1327\">This version feels more like a friend talking about their experience in Baltal, highlighting the beauty of simplicity, reflection, and the calm nature of the place. It invites the reader to step away from the busy world and find a peaceful escape, whether for adventure or introspection</p>', '1745837078.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 10:44:38', '2025-04-28 10:44:38'),
(64, 'Nilgrath River: The Quiet Beauty of Kashmir‚Äôs Hidden Jewel', 'nilgrath-river-the-quiet-beauty-of-kashmirs-hidden-jewel', '<p><strong data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"406\">Nilgrath River</strong>. Nestled in the northern part of Kashmir, it&rsquo;s a quiet, lesser-known treasure that offers a peaceful escape from the more crowded spots. If you ever find yourself in this magical land, Nilgrath is a place worth discovering.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"662\" data-end=\"1119\">Unlike the loud, roaring rivers that fill the air with their constant rush, Nilgrath feels like it&rsquo;s in no hurry. It quietly winds its way through the valley, its cool, crystal-clear waters glistening under the Kashmir sun. As you approach the river, you&rsquo;ll be immediately struck by the tranquility that surrounds it. There&rsquo;s something soothing about its calm flow, as if the river is trying to tell you that sometimes, it&rsquo;s okay to slow down and just <em data-start=\"1114\" data-end=\"1118\">be</em>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1526\">The journey to Nilgrath is as serene as the river itself. To get there, you&rsquo;ll pass through charming little villages, lush green meadows, and towering pine forests. The roads aren&rsquo;t always perfect, but that only adds to the charm. It&rsquo;s the kind of journey where you can roll down your windows and let the cool mountain breeze wash over you, taking in the beauty of the land as it unfolds before your eyes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1526\">Once you reach Nilgrath, you&rsquo;ll understand why this river has such a special place in my heart. It&rsquo;s a place that invites you to stop, reflect, and reconnect with nature. The banks of the river are lined with smooth, weathered stones that have been shaped by centuries of flowing water. It&rsquo;s easy to find a spot to sit, close your eyes, and just listen. The gentle murmur of the river is the only sound you&rsquo;ll hear, and for a moment, it feels like time has stood still.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1526\">Nilgrath isn&rsquo;t a place that demands attention, but that&rsquo;s exactly what makes it so enchanting. It&rsquo;s not flooded with tourists, and that&rsquo;s a rarity in a place as beautiful as Kashmir. Here, you can experience the raw beauty of the region without the hustle and bustle that often accompanies popular tourist spots. It&rsquo;s perfect for anyone looking to disconnect from the world and reconnect with themselves.2</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1526\">It&rsquo;s a place where the world slows down, where the only thing that matters is the moment you&rsquo;re in. It&rsquo;s a reminder that the most beautiful things in life are often the quietest, the most humble&mdash;and that sometimes, the greatest adventures are found not in the loud and chaotic, but in the stillness and calm of a river like Nilgrath.</p>', '1745837835.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 10:57:15', '2025-04-28 10:57:15'),
(65, '\"Trekking to Amarnath: Where Faith Meets the Majestic Himalayas\"', 'trekking-to-amarnath-where-faith-meets-the-majestic-himalayas', '<p>Kashmir is a land that&rsquo;s as much about its deep blue skies and towering mountains as it is about the stories, legends, and faith that come with it. And if there&rsquo;s one place in Kashmir that blends both nature and spirituality in such a powerful way, it&rsquo;s the <strong data-start=\"417\" data-end=\"434\">Amarnath Cave</strong>. For many, it&rsquo;s not just a trek or a destination; it&rsquo;s a journey of the soul.</p>\r\n<p>At the heart of the <strong data-start=\"557\" data-end=\"574\">Amarnath Cave</strong> is the ice formation that draws millions of people every year&mdash;the <strong data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"657\">Shiva Lingam</strong>. It&rsquo;s not your ordinary religious site. This ice structure forms naturally, and it&rsquo;s believed to represent Lord Shiva in a way that&rsquo;s beyond words. There&rsquo;s something deeply humbling about standing in front of it, knowing that it&rsquo;s been formed by nature itself, year after year, just as it has for centuries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2807\" data-end=\"3330\">The <strong data-start=\"2811\" data-end=\"2829\">Amarnath Yatra</strong> is more than just a pilgrimage; it&rsquo;s an experience. From the moment you set foot on the path, you&rsquo;re not just traveling through the mountains, you&rsquo;re traveling through your own thoughts, emotions, and reflections. The journey isn&rsquo;t just physical&mdash;it&rsquo;s deeply emotional. As you ascend, the fatigue starts to fade, and you realize that the climb isn&rsquo;t just about reaching the cave&mdash;it&rsquo;s about the people you meet along the way, the stories you share, and the sense of peace that slowly builds inside you.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3332\" data-end=\"3760\">The trek, the people, the natural beauty, and the sacredness of the cave all come together to create an experience that stays with you long after you&rsquo;ve left. And that&rsquo;s the magic of Amarnath&mdash;no matter what your reason for visiting, you walk away feeling changed in some way. Whether it&rsquo;s peace, reflection, or simply the beauty of the mountains, Amarnath leaves a mark on your heart.</p>', '1745838246.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:04:06', '2025-04-28 11:04:06'),
(66, 'The Journey to Gadsar Lake: A Test of Willpower and Wonder', 'the-journey-to-gadsar-lake-a-test-of-willpower-and-wonder', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2032\" data-end=\"2331\">Gadsar Lake is often called the &ldquo;<strong data-start=\"2065\" data-end=\"2082\">Sapphire Lake</strong>&rdquo; for a reason. Its waters, a brilliant shade of blue, are nothing short of mesmerizing. Surrounded by snow-capped mountains and pristine alpine meadows, the lake seems to emerge like a dream, tucked away in a valley far from the chaos of the world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2333\" data-end=\"2690\">The first sight of the lake is a surreal moment. The water is so clear and still, it reflects the surrounding peaks like a perfect mirror. The mountains that cradle the lake seem to protect it, standing as silent sentinels. In the summer months, the meadow around the lake comes alive with wildflowers, adding pops of color to the already picturesque scene.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"920\" data-end=\"1281\">Gadsar Lake is not for the faint-hearted. This hidden gem lies at an altitude of around 13,500 feet and is part of the&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"1048\" data-end=\"1068\">Gadsar Lake Trek</strong>, which is a popular but challenging trail in Kashmir. The journey begins in <strong data-start=\"1145\" data-end=\"1157\">Sonamarg</strong>, a beautiful meadow that serves as the perfect starting point before embarking on the trek into the heart of the mountains.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1283\" data-end=\"1589\">The trail to the lake is rugged, often steep, and takes you through a mix of terrains&mdash;from thick forests and alpine meadows to rocky slopes and snow-covered trails. It&rsquo;s a physically demanding trek, and as you make your way higher into the mountains, the air becomes thinner and the path more treacherous.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1591\" data-end=\"1995\">But every step you take brings a new reward. You&rsquo;ll pass through lush green valleys, cross streams with crystal-clear water, and walk along mountain ridges with views that seem to stretch forever. And then, just when you think your legs can&rsquo;t take any more, the landscape opens up, and you&rsquo;re greeted by the stunning sight of <strong data-start=\"1917\" data-end=\"1932\">Gadsar Lake</strong>&mdash;a serene, shimmering body of water surrounded by jagged peaks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1591\" data-end=\"1995\">Gadsar Lake offers a chance to experience Kashmir in its purest form&mdash;a place where nature reigns supreme and time seems to stand still.</p>', '1745838534.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:08:54', '2025-04-28 11:08:54'),
(67, 'Kheer Bhawani: A Sacred Oasis of Peace in Kashmir', 'kheer-bhawani-a-sacred-oasis-of-peace-in-kashmir', '<p><strong data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"478\">Kheer Bhawani</strong>. Tucked away in the serene village of <strong data-start=\"517\" data-end=\"530\">Tula Mula</strong>, this sacred temple is not just a place of worship&mdash;it&rsquo;s a place of peace, reflection, and a deep connection with the divine.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"694\" data-end=\"1102\">Kheer Bhawani is dedicated to the goddess <strong data-start=\"736\" data-end=\"751\">Ragnya Devi</strong>, believed to be the protector of the region. What makes this temple so special is not only its spiritual significance but also the mystical atmosphere that surrounds it. The temple is located next to a sacred spring, and its waters are believed to have healing powers. But beyond the legends, it&rsquo;s the serene energy of the place that draws people in.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1104\" data-end=\"1446\">The temple, surrounded by lush greenery and set against the backdrop of the majestic mountains, feels like a hidden gem. The calmness of the place is almost palpable, inviting you to slow down, breathe deeply, and just <em data-start=\"1323\" data-end=\"1327\">be</em>. There&rsquo;s a sense of timelessness here, where every corner of the temple grounds feels steeped in history and devotion.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1104\" data-end=\"1446\">One of the most fascinating aspects of Kheer Bhawani is the sacred spring that lies within the temple grounds. Legend has it that the waters of the spring change color in response to the moods of the goddess&mdash;often shifting from clear to shades of white, pink, or even black. Pilgrims believe that these changes are symbolic of the goddess&rsquo;s blessings or warnings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"5146\" data-end=\"5553\">Kheer Bhawani, with its rich history and spiritual aura, is a reminder that some places are meant to be experienced not just through sightseeing but through feeling. Whether you&rsquo;re visiting for the first time or returning to reconnect, it&rsquo;s a place that will leave a mark on your soul. It&rsquo;s a quiet sanctuary, a place of healing, and a reminder that peace and beauty can be found in the simplest of moments.</p>', '1745838752.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:12:32', '2025-04-28 11:12:32'),
(68, 'Thajiwas Glacier: A Hidden Treasure in Kashmir‚Äôs Heart', 'thajiwas-glacier-a-hidden-treasure-in-kashmirs-heart', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"187\" data-end=\"492\"><strong data-start=\"471\" data-end=\"491\">Thajiwas Glacier</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"494\" data-end=\"947\">Nestled in the beautiful <strong data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"531\">Sonamarg</strong> Valley, Thajiwas Glacier is one of those hidden gems that will make you fall in love with Kashmir all over again. It\'s a place that feels straight out of a fairytale, where snow-covered peaks kiss the sky, crystal-clear streams run through the meadows, and the air feels like it&rsquo;s been plucked from a dream. For those willing to venture a bit off the beaten path, Thajiwas Glacier offers an unforgettable adventure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1023\" data-end=\"1432\">Reaching Thajiwas Glacier isn&rsquo;t just a trek; it&rsquo;s an immersion into the untouched beauty of Kashmir. The journey begins in <strong data-start=\"1146\" data-end=\"1158\">Sonamarg</strong>, a charming little town known for its lush meadows and panoramic views. From here, the trek to Thajiwas begins with an easy walk along well-marked paths. You&rsquo;ll pass by shimmering rivers, pine forests, and grassy pastures, as you gradually make your way toward the glacier.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1434\" data-end=\"1789\">For many visitors, the path to Thajiwas is an absolute treat for the senses. The lush greenery surrounding you, the sound of the flowing river, and the gentle breeze all seem to encourage you to slow down and appreciate nature&rsquo;s grandeur. The trek is relatively easy for most, and in just a few hours, you&rsquo;re transported into a completely different world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1791\" data-end=\"2049\">As you climb higher, the valley opens up, and you start seeing the snow-capped peaks that rise majestically around you. The Thajiwas Glacier itself is nestled among these towering mountains, a serene and powerful reminder of the natural beauty Kashmir holds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3645\" data-end=\"4067\">In <strong data-start=\"3648\" data-end=\"3658\">winter</strong>, the glacier transforms into a snowy wonderland. The surrounding mountains become even more dramatic, and the landscape feels completely still, as if frozen in time. For those who love winter adventures, this is a whole new side of Thajiwas to explore. The snow-covered trails leading up to the glacier, the stillness of the landscape, and the crisp, fresh air combine to create an almost magical experience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"4069\" data-end=\"4291\">No matter when you visit, the atmosphere of Thajiwas Glacier is one of serenity and wonder. It&rsquo;s a place where you can lose yourself in nature, find peace, and feel that deep sense of awe that only the mountains can offer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1791\" data-end=\"2049\">&nbsp;</p>', '1745838910.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:15:10', '2025-04-28 11:15:10');
