(69, 'Peer Ki Gali: A Tranquil Escape in the Heart of Kashmir', 'peer-ki-gali-a-tranquil-escape-in-the-heart-of-kashmir', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"478\">Kashmir is often called \"Heaven on Earth,\" but it&rsquo;s not just the grand lakes and snow-capped peaks that make this place extraordinary. Nestled between the pristine hills, there&rsquo;s a hidden gem that combines spiritual reverence with stunning natural beauty: <strong data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"477\">Peer Ki Gali</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"480\" data-end=\"871\">Located in the <strong data-start=\"495\" data-end=\"515\">Pir Panjal range</strong>, Peer Ki Gali is a peaceful mountain pass that holds deep significance for locals and travelers alike. It&rsquo;s not just a place on the map, but a sanctuary where nature and spirituality come together in a symphony of serenity. Whether you&rsquo;re seeking reflection, adventure, or simply an escape from the busy world, Peer Ki Gali offers something truly special.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"480\" data-end=\"871\">Getting to Peer Ki Gali is an adventure in itself. It&rsquo;s situated at an altitude of around 11,500 feet, making it one of the highest mountain passes in Kashmir. The journey from <strong data-start=\"1109\" data-end=\"1121\">Pahalgam</strong> to Peer Ki Gali takes you through winding roads that offer spectacular views of the lush green valleys, dense forests, and towering peaks. Each turn reveals a new, more breathtaking landscape, and the roads, though winding and narrow, only add to the excitement of the journey.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"480\" data-end=\"871\">Peer Ki Gali is more than just a scenic spot; it&rsquo;s a place of deep spiritual significance. The name \"Peer Ki Gali\" translates to \"The Pass of the Saint\" and is believed to be named after a revered saint, <strong data-start=\"2029\" data-end=\"2045\">Peer Dastgir</strong>, who is said to have meditated here for many years. It is said that the saint\'s presence continues to bless the area, giving it a sense of calm and spirituality that is palpable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"4973\" data-end=\"5365\">The true magic of Peer Ki Gali lies in its ability to make you pause and reflect. The calmness of the place allows you to disconnect from the noise of the world and reconnect with your inner peace. Whether you spend time at the shrine, take a walk through the meadows, or just sit and take in the view, Peer Ki Gali offers the kind of solitude that&rsquo;s hard to find in today&rsquo;s fast-paced world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"5367\" data-end=\"5710\">It&rsquo;s a place where time seems to slow down. As you gaze at the distant peaks and the vast expanse of nature around you, you begin to realize that sometimes, the most beautiful things are the simplest&mdash;like a moment of quiet, a deep breath of fresh mountain air, or a peaceful prayer at the shrine of a saint who found solace in this very place.</p>', '1745839133.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:18:53', '2025-04-28 11:18:53'),
(70, 'Pampore: A Slice of Kashmir\'s Soul', 'pampore-a-slice-of-kashmirs-soul', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"180\" data-end=\"481\"><strong data-start=\"469\" data-end=\"480\">&nbsp;Pampore, known as the \"Saffron Town\" of Kashmir, is famous worldwide for its exquisite saffron cultivation. The town is home to some of the finest saffron in the world, and the fields, with their vibrant purple blossoms, are nothing short of mesmerizing.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"180\" data-end=\"481\">Famed for its fragrant saffron fields and historical significance, Pampore is a place that often gets overlooked by mainstream tourism. However, for those who venture here, it offers a unique blend of culture, history, and nature that&rsquo;s truly unforgettable. It&rsquo;s a place where the air smells sweet with the scent of saffron, where the people&rsquo;s hospitality warms your heart, and where history and nature intertwine in the most magical way.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1224\" data-end=\"1593\">Visiting Pampore during the saffron harvest season is like stepping into a painting. The fields stretch across the valley, with rows of vibrant purple flowers swaying in the gentle breeze. The air is filled with the heady fragrance of saffron, and the sight of the delicate flowers against the backdrop of the snow-capped Himalayas creates an unforgettable experience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1595\" data-end=\"1986\">The process of harvesting saffron is painstaking, with workers delicately picking the threads from each flower by hand. It&rsquo;s an ancient practice passed down through generations, and if you&rsquo;re lucky enough, you may be able to witness the saffron harvest firsthand. The rich, golden threads are then dried and packaged to be sold worldwide, making Pampore\'s saffron a highly coveted commodity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1988\" data-end=\"2250\">The fields themselves are a sight to behold, especially in autumn when the saffron blooms. The sight of thousands of delicate purple flowers against the backdrop of the sun setting behind the distant peaks is something you&rsquo;ll carry with you long after you leave.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"5911\" data-end=\"6362\">Pampore may not have the fame of places like Srinagar or Gulmarg, but that&rsquo;s exactly why it&rsquo;s so special. It&rsquo;s a place that invites you to slow down, breathe in the fresh air, and experience the simple, profound beauty of Kashmir. From its fragrant saffron fields to its historical sites, local markets, and warm-hearted people, Pampore offers a slice of Kashmir&rsquo;s soul&mdash;a place where nature, culture, and spirituality come together in perfect harmony.</p>', '1745839376.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-28 11:22:56', '2025-04-28 11:22:56'),
(71, 'Hidden in the Mist: A Visit to Drung Waterfall, Kashmir\'s Secret Gem', 'hidden-in-the-mist-a-visit-to-drung-waterfall-kashmirs-secret-gem', '<p><strong>Drung Waterfall</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tucked away in the serene village of Tangmarg, about 40 minutes from Gulmarg in Jammu &amp; Kashmir, lies a place that feels like something out of a dream&mdash;<strong>Drung Waterfall</strong> is a breathtaking spot that feels untouched by time. Water thunders down rocky cliffs, and in winter, it freezes into magical icicles&mdash;like a scene from a fairytale.</p>\r\n<p>The air around Drung is fresh in a way city-dwellers often forget exists. It&rsquo;s a place where you pause&mdash;not because you&rsquo;re tired, but because nature demands your attention. You&rsquo;ll see local children laughing and playing by the banks, elders sipping tea at small dhabas, and tourists like yourself wide-eyed at the natural beauty around them.</p>\r\n<p>The charm of Drung isn&rsquo;t just the waterfall&mdash;it\'s the slow pace, the wooden homes with traditional Kashmiri architecture, and the kindness of the locals. If you stop for a cup of <strong data-start=\"1494\" data-end=\"1507\">noon chai</strong> (salty pink tea) or a plate of <strong data-start=\"1539\" data-end=\"1548\">maggi</strong> (instant noodles) with a view, don&rsquo;t be surprised if someone strikes up a conversation.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s simple, raw, and unforgettable.</p>', '1745904298.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 05:24:58', '2025-04-29 05:24:58'),
(72, 'Gagangir: Where Kashmir Slows Down', 'gagangir-where-kashmir-slows-down', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"125\" data-end=\"377\">Just before the crowds of Sonamarg, Gagangir is a peaceful riverside village where time slows down. With the Sindh River curling around a tiny island, wooden huts, and horses grazing freely, it&rsquo;s a perfect spot for chai, silence, and snow-capped views.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"657\">The Sindh River flows strong and clear here, wrapping around a small island that&rsquo;s home to a few wooden huts and grazing horses. It feels like a slice of life paused in time. The air is cool, clean, and full of pine scent.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"659\" data-end=\"936\">Locals sit by roadside tea stalls, sipping noon chai and chatting softly. Children run freely, their laughter mixing with the river&rsquo;s gurgle. If you stay overnight in one of the homestays or camps, you&rsquo;ll wake to snow peaks bathed in early sun and silence broken only by birds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"938\" data-end=\"1109\">Gagangir isn&rsquo;t flashy. It doesn&rsquo;t try to impress. But if you&rsquo;re tired of picture-perfect filters and crowds, this little village quietly reminds you what peace feels like.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"379\" data-end=\"432\">Skip the rush&mdash;pause at Gagangir. You won&rsquo;t regret it.</p>', '1745906227.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 05:57:07', '2025-04-29 05:57:07'),
(73, 'Baisaran Valley: A Scenic Escape into Kashmir‚Äôs Pristine Wilderness', 'baisaran-valley-a-scenic-escape-into-kashmirs-pristine-wilderness', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Baisaran Valley, often dubbed the <strong>\"Mini Switzerland of India,\"</strong> is a serene meadow located approximately 5 km from Pahalgam in the Anantnag district of Jammu and Kashmir.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The valley is renowned for its lush greenery, dense pine forests, and panoramic views of snow-capped mountains.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">It\'s a haven for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike.</span></p>\r\n<p>A popular way to explore the valley, offering a leisurely journey through its picturesque landscapes.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Experience the thrill of rolling downhill inside a transparent orb on the valley\'s smooth slopes.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">It\'s an exhilarating activity suitable for all ages.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">During the winter months, the valley transforms into a snow-covered wonderland, perfect for snow sledging, sliding, and enjoying the Alpine-like scenery.</span> ‚Äã</p>\r\n<p>Feel free to explore these resources to plan your visit to Baisaran Valley and immerse yourself in its natural beauty.‚Äã</p>', '1745906574.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 06:02:54', '2025-04-29 06:02:54'),
(74, 'Karnah Valley: Kashmir‚Äôs Treasured Heaven', 'karnah-valley-kashmirs-treasured-heaven', '<p>Karnah\'s natural beauty, including its lush meadows and towering peaks, and discusses the reopening of the Shardha Peth Mandir after 75 years, which has spurred interest in the region\'s cultural heritage.</p>\r\n<p>Karnah is often overshadowed by its more famous neighbors, but those who venture into this tranquil valley are rewarded with mesmerizing landscapes and pristine natural beauty. Surrounded by the majestic <strong data-start=\"831\" data-end=\"851\">Himalayan ranges</strong>, Karnah boasts lush green meadows, crystal-clear rivers, and thick forests. The valley is particularly famous for its <strong data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"985\">Sadhna Pass</strong>, which connects Karnah with the rest of Kashmir and offers one of the most scenic drives in the region.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1129\" data-end=\"1489\">The valley is home to a mix of Kashmiri Muslims and Gujjars, who have their own distinct customs and traditions. The people here are known for their warmth and hospitality, and visitors can learn a lot about local life by simply interacting with the residents.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1491\" data-end=\"1763\">The <strong data-start=\"1495\" data-end=\"1510\">Sadhna Pass</strong>, for example, is not only a geographical landmark but also holds significant cultural value, as it has been a trading route for centuries. The area also houses <strong data-start=\"1671\" data-end=\"1686\">old temples</strong>, <strong data-start=\"1688\" data-end=\"1699\">mosques</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"1705\" data-end=\"1716\">shrines</strong>, representing a blend of religious traditions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1491\" data-end=\"1763\">The best time to visit Karnah Valley is during the <strong data-start=\"3092\" data-end=\"3109\">summer months</strong> (April to October), when the weather is pleasant, and the valley is lush and green. For those who love the snow, the <strong data-start=\"3227\" data-end=\"3244\">winter season</strong> (November to February) brings a magical transformation, with the valley covered in snow, perfect for winter sports and photography.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1491\" data-end=\"1763\">If you\'re looking to explore a side of Kashmir that\'s still untouched by mass tourism, <strong data-start=\"3796\" data-end=\"3813\">Karnah Valley</strong> should be at the top of your list. Its natural beauty, rich cultural heritage, and adventure-filled opportunities make it a hidden gem worth discovering.</p>', '1745906927.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 06:08:47', '2025-04-29 06:08:47'),
(75, 'Ferozepur Nallah : A Serene Escape in Kashmir‚Äôs Breathtaking Landscapes\"', 'ferozepur-nallah-a-serene-escape-in-kashmirs-breathtaking-landscapes', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Ferozepur Nallah, also known as Shinmahinyu, is a picturesque alpine stream located approximately 5 kilometers from Gulmarg in Jammu and Kashmir.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Originating from Ferozepur Peak, this serene watercourse meanders through lush valleys between Chinamarg and Nurpur Pass, offering a tranquil retreat for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Surrounded by snow-capped mountains and dense pine forests, Ferozepur Nallah is an ideal spot for various outdoor activities. Visitors can indulge in trout fishing, as the stream is known for its abundant fish population. The area also serves as a base camp for the Tosamaidan Trek, a 50 km journey that takes approximately three days to complete, offering breathtaking views along the way.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Whether you\'re seeking adventure, tranquility, or a picturesque setting for photography, Ferozepur Nallah offers a unique experience that showcases the natural beauty of Kashmir. Its serene environment and diverse activities make it a must-visit destination for travelers exploring the region.</span></p>', '1745907265.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 06:14:25', '2025-04-29 06:14:25'),
(76, 'Sernab Meadows: A Hidden Gem in Kupwara', 'sernab-meadows-a-hidden-gem-in-kupwara', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"258\" data-end=\"415\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"18\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Sernab Meadows</strong> is a vast expanse of lush green grasslands, surrounded by dense forests and snow-capped peaks.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The area is known for its serene environment, making it an ideal spot for camping, trekking, and nature walks.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The meadows are also home to various species of flora and fauna, adding to the ecological richness of the region.</span>‚Äã</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"258\" data-end=\"415\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"34\" data-end=\"50\">Kupwara town</strong>, which is well-connected by road.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">From Kupwara, travelers can proceed towards <strong data-start=\"44\" data-end=\"61\">Machil sector</strong>, passing through picturesque landscapes.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">It\'s advisable to arrange for local guides and obtain necessary permits before embarking on the journey.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1233\" data-end=\"1358\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Sernab Meadows in Kupwara offers a unique blend of natural beauty and tranquility, making it a must-visit destination for those seeking to explore the unexplored regions of Kashmir.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Its serene environment and rich biodiversity make it a perfect getaway for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts.</span>‚Äã</p>', '1745907487.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 06:18:07', '2025-04-29 06:18:07'),
(77, 'Lamayuru: The Moonland of Ladakh', 'lamayuru-the-moonland-of-ladakh', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Nestled approximately 125 kilometers west of Leh on the Srinagar-Leh highway, <strong data-start=\"78\" data-end=\"90\">Lamayuru</strong> is a mesmerizing village in Ladakh, renowned for its unique lunar landscapes and spiritual heritage.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Often referred to as the \"Moonland\" due to its surreal terrain, Lamayuru offers travelers a blend of natural beauty, cultural richness, and historical significance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The barren, craggy hills surrounding Lamayuru resemble the surface of the moon, creating an otherworldly atmosphere. This distinctive landscape has attracted photographers, filmmakers, and nature enthusiasts seeking to capture its ethereal beauty.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] bg-[#FCECC1] dark:bg-[#64572A] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">At the heart of Lamayuru lies the <strong data-start=\"34\" data-end=\"56\">Lamayuru Monastery</strong>, one of the oldest and most revered Tibetan Buddhist monasteries in Ladakh.</span> Established in the 11th century, it is affiliated with the Red Hat sect of Buddhism. The monastery houses sacred murals, thangkas, and statues, offering visitors a glimpse into the region\'s spiritual heritage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Lamayuru serves as a starting point for several trekking routes, including the <strong data-start=\"79\" data-end=\"108\">Lamayuru to Chilling trek</strong>, which offers trekkers a blend of natural beauty and cultural experiences.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Lamayuru\'s unique landscapes, rich cultural heritage, and spiritual ambiance make it a must-visit destination for travelers seeking an authentic Ladakhi experience.</span></p>', '1745907942.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 06:25:42', '2025-04-29 06:25:42'),
(78, 'The Colors, Culture & Calm of Thiksey Monastery', 'the-colors-culture-calm-of-thiksey-monastery', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Thiksey Monastery,</strong> often referred to as the \"Mini Potala Palace of Ladakh,\" is a prominent Tibetan Buddhist monastery situated approximately 19 km east of Leh, the capital of Ladakh.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Perched atop a hill, it offers panoramic views of the Indus Valley and the surrounding Himalayan ranges.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The monastery is renowned for its architectural grandeur, spiritual ambiance, and cultural significance.</span></p>\r\n<p>Thiksey Monastery is one of Ladakh\'s most iconic Tibetan Buddhist monasteries, located just 19 km from Leh. Often called the &ldquo;Mini Potala Palace&rdquo; due to its striking resemblance to Lhasa&rsquo;s Potala, it sits majestically on a hilltop, offering stunning views of the Indus Valley and surrounding mountains. Visitors can explore its 12-story complex, which includes the impressive 15-meter Maitreya Buddha statue, Tara Temple, and Lamokhang Temple that holds sacred scriptures. The rooftop is a favorite spot for sunrise and sunset views.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1906\" data-end=\"2073\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1908\" data-end=\"2073\"><strong data-start=\"1908\" data-end=\"1927\">Gustor Festival</strong> (October-November): <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">A two-day celebration featuring Cham dances, ritual prayers, and the revelation of deity faces, symbolizing the victory of good over evil.</span> ‚Äã</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2075\" data-end=\"2232\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2077\" data-end=\"2232\"><strong data-start=\"2077\" data-end=\"2093\">Yuru Kabgyat</strong> (June-July): <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Commemorates the victory of good over evil with masked dances and traditional rituals.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1745912304.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 07:38:24', '2025-04-29 07:38:24'),
(79, 'Alchi Monastery: Ladakh‚Äôs Hidden Treasure of Ancient Art', 'alchi-monastery-ladakhs-hidden-treasure-of-ancient-art', '<p><strong data-start=\"140\" data-end=\"159\">Alchi Monastery</strong> is a revered Tibetan Buddhist site in Ladakh, India, renowned for its ancient murals and serene ambiance. <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Located approximately 65 km from Leh, the monastery is accessible via the Srinagar-Leh highway.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Visitors can reach it by taxi, private vehicle, or rented motorcycle, with the journey offering scenic views of the Indus River and nearby villages.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Established in the 10th century by Rinchen Zangpo, Alchi Monastery is one of the few surviving monasteries from that era. Unlike other Ladakhi monasteries built on hilltops, Alchi is situated on flat ground, showcasing unique architectural styles influenced by Kashmiri artists. ‚Äã<br><br>The monastery houses some of the oldest surviving paintings in Ladakh, created using natural pigments like lapis lazuli and malachite. These murals depict scenes from Buddhist mythology and daily life during the 10th century. ‚Äã<br><br>Alchi hosts several Buddhist festivals between May and September, including Chotrul Duchen, Galdan Namchot, and Losar (Tibetan New Year). These festivals feature traditional dances, music, and cultural performances, providing visitors with a deeper understanding of Ladakhi heritage. ‚Äã<br></span></p>', '1745912493.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 07:41:33', '2025-04-29 07:41:33'),
(80, 'Hanle: Ladakh‚Äôs Hidden Stargazing Haven', 'hanle-ladakhs-hidden-stargazing-haven', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Hanle<br></strong><br>Nestled at an altitude of 4,500 meters in eastern Ladakh, <strong data-start=\"58\" data-end=\"67\">Hanle</strong> is a remote village that has recently garnered attention as India&rsquo;s first <strong data-start=\"142\" data-end=\"162\">Dark Sky Reserve</strong>.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Spanning over 1,073 square kilometers, this reserve aims to preserve the region\'s exceptionally dark skies, making it an ideal destination for stargazing and astrophotography enthusiasts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Hanle is home to the <strong data-start=\"21\" data-end=\"56\">Indian Astronomical Observatory</strong>, one of the highest optical telescopes in the world. The observatory\'s location, combined with the area\'s clear skies and minimal light pollution, provides unparalleled opportunities for astronomical research and observation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Visitors to Hanle can witness the Milky Way in its full glory, with the Bortle-1 sky rating ensuring a spectacular view of celestial bodies. The region\'s dry weather and high altitude contribute to its status as a premier stargazing destination.</span></p>', '1745912669.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 07:44:29', '2025-04-29 07:44:29'),
(81, 'Zanskar Valley: A Journey Through Ladakh‚Äôs Untouched Wilderness', 'zanskar-valley-a-journey-through-ladakhs-untouched-wilderness', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"50\" data-end=\"68\">Zanskar Valley</strong> is a pristine haven for nature lovers, trekkers, and cultural explorers.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Often overshadowed by its more accessible neighbors, Zanskar offers an untouched glimpse into traditional Tibetan Buddhism and Himalayan wilderness.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"576\">Zanskar</strong> is an adventure in itself. The most popular way to reach the valley is by road, starting from <strong data-start=\"671\" data-end=\"678\">Leh</strong>. From Leh, you will travel towards <strong data-start=\"714\" data-end=\"724\">Kargil</strong> and then take the road to <strong data-start=\"751\" data-end=\"760\">Padum</strong>, the main town of the valley. The roads can be challenging, especially during the monsoon season, and the journey takes time, but the views along the way are incredibly scenic.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2575\" data-end=\"2933\">Zanskar is basic but charming. The main town of <strong data-start=\"2640\" data-end=\"2649\">Padum</strong> has a few guesthouses and homestays where visitors can rest. These homestays provide a great way to experience Ladakhi hospitality. Staying with local families gives travelers an authentic cultural experience, and some hosts even offer tours of the monasteries and surrounding areas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2935\" data-end=\"3115\">For trekkers, <strong data-start=\"2949\" data-end=\"2960\">camping</strong> is a popular option, especially on longer treks like the Chadar trek. The experience of camping under the stars in such a remote location is unparalleled.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2935\" data-end=\"3115\"><strong data-start=\"4312\" data-end=\"4330\">Zanskar Valley</strong> offers an incredible combination of adventure, culture, and spirituality, making it a must-visit for those seeking to explore the wild side of Ladakh. Whether you&rsquo;re trekking through its majestic landscapes, visiting ancient monasteries, or simply soaking in the beauty, Zanskar promises a journey that will stay with you forever.</p>', '1745913055.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 07:50:55', '2025-04-29 07:50:55'),
(82, 'In the Footsteps of Serenity: Discovering Athwatoo, Kashmir', 'in-the-footsteps-of-serenity-discovering-athwatoo-kashmir', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"12\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Athwatoo</strong> is a serene village nestled in the foothills of the Harmukh mountain range in north Kashmir&rsquo;s Bandipora district.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Located approximately 12 km from Bandipora town, this picturesque spot is renowned for its tranquil environment, lush meadows, and crystal-clear streams.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The name \"Athwatoo\" translates to \"confluence of eight roads,\" reflecting its strategic location at the junction of various trails</span> .‚Äã</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Athwatoo is surrounded by dense forests, including the Chitternar forests, which are home to the state\'s only Forest Training School established in 1911</span> . <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The area boasts a rich biodiversity, offering opportunities for wildlife photography and bird watching.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The crystal-clear waters of the Madhumati River provide ideal conditions for trout fishing, a popular activity among locals and visitors alike</span> .‚Äã</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Athwatoo remains one of Kashmir\'s untouched treasures, offering a peaceful retreat for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those seeking to experience the authentic rural life of the region.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Despite its infrastructural challenges, the village\'s natural beauty and cultural richness make it a worthwhile destination for travelers looking to explore beyond the usual tourist spots.</span></p>', '1745915201.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 08:26:41', '2025-04-29 08:26:41'),
(83, 'The Sindh River: Kashmir‚Äôs Pristine Waterway', 'the-sindh-river-kashmirs-pristine-waterway', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Flowing through the heart of the Kashmir Valley, the <strong data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"68\">Sindh River</strong> is a vital tributary of the Jhelum River, originating from the majestic <strong data-start=\"141\" data-end=\"159\">Machoi Glacier</strong> near the Amarnath Temple.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Spanning approximately 108 kilometers, it meanders through the Ganderbal district, enriching the region\'s landscape and ecology.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"378\" data-end=\"535\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The Sindh River is renowned for its crystal-clear waters and picturesque surroundings.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">It traverses through the <strong data-start=\"25\" data-end=\"40\">Sind Valley</strong>, offering breathtaking views of snow-capped mountains, dense forests, and alpine meadows.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">This serene environment makes it a popular spot for trekkers, nature enthusiasts, and photographers.</span>‚Äã</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"537\" data-end=\"698\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Culturally, the river holds immense significance for the local communities.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">It supports agriculture by providing irrigation to the fertile lands along its banks.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The river\'s waters are also integral to traditional practices and festivals, reflecting the deep connection between the people and their natural resources.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"537\" data-end=\"698\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The Sindh River is more than just a waterway; it\'s a lifeline for the Kashmir Valley, intertwining with the region\'s culture, economy, and natural beauty.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Its preservation is vital for maintaining the ecological balance and sustaining the livelihoods of the communities that depend on it.</span>‚Äã</p>', '1745918551.jpeg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 09:22:31', '2025-04-29 09:22:31'),
(84, 'Puga Valley: Ladakh‚Äôs Boiling Beauty in the Cold Desert', 'puga-valley-ladakhs-boiling-beauty-in-the-cold-desert', '<p>Tucked away in the remote <strong data-start=\"209\" data-end=\"231\">Changthang plateau</strong> of eastern Ladakh, <strong data-start=\"251\" data-end=\"266\">Puga Valley</strong> is unlike any other place in India. While Ladakh is known for its stark landscapes and monasteries, Puga surprises visitors with something unexpected &mdash; <strong data-start=\"419\" data-end=\"443\">steaming hot springs</strong>, <strong data-start=\"445\" data-end=\"456\">geysers</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"462\" data-end=\"483\">boiling mud pools</strong>. It&rsquo;s not just scenic; it&rsquo;s a glimpse into the Earth&rsquo;s fiery core.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"585\" data-end=\"917\">Puga is considered one of India&rsquo;s most promising <strong data-start=\"634\" data-end=\"657\">geothermal hotspots</strong>. As you approach the valley, you&rsquo;ll notice plumes of steam rising from the earth and sulfur-rich soil glowing with vibrant hues &mdash; yellow, orange, and white. The air smells faintly of minerals and heat, a natural spa set against the cold wind of the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"919\" data-end=\"1172\">This geothermal activity has also caught scientific and industrial attention. In 2021, Puga was selected for India&rsquo;s <strong data-start=\"1036\" data-end=\"1071\">first geothermal energy project</strong>, led by ONGC, with the goal of harnessing natural underground heat to produce renewable electricity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"919\" data-end=\"1172\">Puga isn&rsquo;t about resorts or crowds &mdash; it&rsquo;s about raw nature. Surrounded by towering mountains, marshy fields, and rare migratory birds, it&rsquo;s a haven for offbeat explorers. The nearby <strong data-start=\"1752\" data-end=\"1771\">Tso Moriri Lake</strong> and <strong data-start=\"1776\" data-end=\"1794\">Karzok village</strong> make great stops if you\'re on a longer itinerary through <strong data-start=\"1852\" data-end=\"1866\">Changthang</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"919\" data-end=\"1172\"><strong data-start=\"2926\" data-end=\"2941\">Puga Valley</strong> is not your typical tourist spot &mdash; it&rsquo;s a rare geological wonder in a high-altitude desert. Whether you\'re a science enthusiast, nature lover, or just someone looking for an offbeat destination, this boiling beauty in Ladakh is sure to leave a lasting impression.</p>', '1745918967.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 09:29:27', '2025-04-29 09:29:27'),
(85, 'Into the Silence: A Journey to Nyoma, Ladakh', 'into-the-silence-a-journey-to-nyoma-ladakh', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Nyoma </strong>is a tranquil village in southern Ladakh, India, known for its serene landscapes, Buddhist heritage, and strategic location near the Line of Actual Control (LAC) with China.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Situated approximately 150 km southeast of Leh along the Indus River, Nyoma offers visitors a glimpse into Ladakh\'s rich culture and natural beauty.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Nyoma is renowned for its breathtaking views of the Indus River, surrounding mountains, and expansive plains. The village\'s remote location provides a peaceful retreat away from the more frequented tourist spots in Ladakh.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Perched on a hill above the village, Nyoma Gompa is a Buddhist monastery that offers panoramic views of the surrounding area. The monastery is a place of spiritual significance and tranquility.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Visitors can engage with the local Ladakhi culture, characterized by its unique traditions, cuisine, and hospitality. The village offers opportunities for trekking, photography, and experiencing the lifestyle of the Changpa nomads.</span></p>', '1745922178.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 10:22:58', '2025-04-29 10:22:58'),
(86, 'Hall of Fame Museum, Leh ‚Äì A Tribute to Indian Soldiers', 'hall-of-fame-museum-leh-a-tribute-to-indian-soldiers', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Hall of Fame Museum </strong>stands as a poignant tribute to the valor and sacrifices of Indian soldiers.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Established by the Indian Army, this museum offers visitors a deep dive into the history of India\'s military endeavors, particularly in the challenging terrains of Ladakh.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Located just outside Leh, the Hall of Fame Museum is a powerful tribute to the bravery of Indian soldiers, especially those who served in the Kargil War and the Siachen Glacier. Run by the Indian Army, the museum showcases war memorabilia, weapons, photographs, and touching stories of sacrifice. With galleries on Operation Vijay and Ladakhi culture, it offers both history and heart. A must-visit for travelers seeking meaning beyond the mountains.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The Hall of Fame Museum is more than just a collection of artifacts; it\'s a testament to the courage and dedication of India\'s armed forces. A visit here is both educational and emotionally moving, making it a must-see for anyone traveling to Leh.</span></p>', '1745922414.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 10:26:54', '2025-04-29 10:26:54'),
(87, 'Chumathang: Ladakh‚Äôs Hidden Hot Spring Retreat', 'chumathang-ladakhs-hidden-hot-spring-retreat', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Nestled along the Indus River, approximately 130 km southeast of Leh, <strong data-start=\"70\" data-end=\"84\">Chumathang</strong> is a tranquil village renowned for its natural hot springs.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] bg-[#FCECC1] dark:bg-[#64572A] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Situated at an altitude of around 4,000 meters, the springs offer mineral-rich waters believed to have therapeutic properties, particularly beneficial for joint pain and skin ailments.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] bg-[#FCECC1] dark:bg-[#64572A] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Tucked away along the Indus River, <strong data-start=\"158\" data-end=\"172\">Chumathang</strong> is a peaceful Ladakhi village best known for its natural hot springs the steaming waters are believed to have healing properties and provide a warm escape from the cold desert air. Surrounded by raw Himalayan beauty and traditional Ladakhi life, it&rsquo;s a perfect offbeat stop for wellness and tranquility seekers.</span></p>', '1745922569.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 10:29:29', '2025-04-29 10:29:29'),
(88, 'Kargil ‚Äì The Heart of Ladakh‚Äôs Untold Stories', 'kargil-the-heart-of-ladakhs-untold-stories', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong data-start=\"46\" data-end=\"56\">Kargil</strong> is a town that offers more than its historical significance.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">While it gained prominence during the 1999 Kargil War, today, it stands as a serene destination for travelers seeking authentic Ladakhi experiences.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Often remembered for the 1999 conflict, <strong data-start=\"167\" data-end=\"177\">Kargil</strong> is a peaceful town today, tucked between rugged mountains and the Suru River. It&rsquo;s a gateway to untouched valleys, Buddhist monasteries like Mulbekh and Rangdum, and scenic drives toward Zanskar and Batalik. Kargil blends culture, history, and adventure&mdash;perfect for travelers who want to go beyond the usual tourist trail in Ladakh.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">For those venturing towards Leh, consider the <strong data-start=\"46\" data-end=\"63\">Batalik route</strong>. This offbeat path takes you through the <strong data-start=\"40\" data-end=\"61\">Hamboting La Pass</strong>, the Aryan Valley, and the historic Batalik village, offering a unique perspective of Ladakh\'s diverse landscapes.</span></p>', '1745925563.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-29 11:19:23', '2025-04-29 11:19:23'),
(89, 'A Step Back in Time: The Story of Leh Palace', 'a-step-back-in-time-the-story-of-leh-palace', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Leh Palace, perched atop Namgyal Hill in Leh, Ladakh, is a remarkable 17th-century structure that offers a glimpse into the region\'s royal past and architectural brilliance.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Constructed by King Sengge Namgyal, the palace is often compared to the Potala Palace in Lhasa due to its similar architectural style.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Today, it stands as a testament to Ladakh\'s rich history and cultural heritage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The nine-storey palace was built using local materials like stone, mud bricks, and wood, showcasing traditional Tibetan architecture.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Its design includes intricately carved overhanging balconies and a well-planned layout that once housed the royal family and their court.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The upper floors offered panoramic views of the surrounding mountains and Leh town.</span>‚Äã‚Äã</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Inside the palace, visitors can explore a museum that houses a rich collection of artifacts, including jewelry, ceremonial dresses, crowns, and Tibetan thangka paintings.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">These artifacts, dating back over 400 years, provide insight into the opulence and cultural practices of the time.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The palace also features the Namgyal Stupa and the Chandazik Gompa, adding to its spiritual significance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">A visit to Leh Palace offers more than just a historical tour; it provides breathtaking views of Leh and the surrounding Zanskar mountain range. The Archaeological Survey of India currently maintains the site, ensuring its preservation for future generations.‚Äã</span></p>', '1745998824.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 07:40:24', '2025-04-30 07:40:24'),
(90, 'Bactrian Camels & Sand Dunes: Discovering Hunder Village', 'bactrian-camels-sand-dunes-discovering-hunder-village', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Nestled in the Nubra Valley of Ladakh, Hunder Village offers a unique blend of desert landscapes and Tibetan culture. Known for its striking sand dunes and the rare double-humped Bactrian camels, Hunder provides a surreal experience amidst the Himalayan backdrop.</span><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">&nbsp;Ladakh\'s Nubra Valley, is a captivating destination that blends natural beauty with cultural heritage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Experience unique grey sand dunes and embark on rides atop double-humped Bactrian camels, reminiscent of the Silk Route era.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">visit this ancient 14th-century monastery, offering panoramic views and insights into Tibetan Buddhism.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Explore forests of this medicinal plant, known for its health benefits and used in various local products.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Discover remnants of the former Nubra Kingdom, including the Elephant Palace and Gula Fort.</span></p>', '1745999122.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 07:45:22', '2025-04-30 07:45:22');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `image`, `status`, `published_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(91, 'Sankar Gompa: A Tranquil Gem in the Heart of Leh.', 'sankar-gompa-a-tranquil-gem-in-the-heart-of-leh', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Sankar Gompa,</strong> also known as <strong>Sankar Monastery,</strong> is a serene Buddhist monastery located approximately 3 km from Leh, Ladakh.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Situated on a hillock, it offers panoramic views of the surrounding Namgyal Tsemo Hills and the town of Leh.</span>‚Äã</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Sankar Gompa offers a tranquil escape into Ladakh\'s spiritual heart.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Unlike the larger, more frequented monasteries, Sankar provides an intimate glimpse into Buddhist monastic life, making it a must-visit for those seeking peace and reflection.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Adorned with murals depicting Buddhist deities and teachings, this hall serves as the monastery\'s spiritual center.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Home to around 20 monks, Sankar Gompa is a place of daily prayers, meditation, and study, offering visitors a chance to witness and partake in these practices.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The monastery\'s elevated position provides panoramic views of the Stok Kangri range and Leh town. Visitors can enjoy the serene atmosphere, observe monastic rituals, and explore the surrounding barley fields.</span></p>', '1745999371.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 07:49:31', '2025-04-30 07:49:31'),
(92, 'Tosamaidan: Kashmir\'s Hidden Alpine Gem', 'tosamaidan-kashmirs-hidden-alpine-gem', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Nestled in the Pir Panjal range of Central Kashmir\'s Budgam district, <strong data-start=\"70\" data-end=\"84\">Tosamaidan</strong>&mdash;meaning \"King of Meadows\"&mdash;is a sprawling 60-square-kilometer alpine meadow renowned for its lush greenery, pristine lakes, and panoramic mountain vistas.</span>‚Äã</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">At an elevation of approximately 10,000 feet, Tosamaidan offers a serene escape with its expansive meadows, dense deodar forests, and vibrant wildflowers.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The area is a haven for trekkers, with popular trails leading to nearby meadows like <strong data-start=\"85\" data-end=\"96\">Gadasar</strong>, <strong data-start=\"98\" data-end=\"107\">Chanz</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"113\" data-end=\"125\">Damansar</strong>, as well as alpine lakes such as <strong data-start=\"159\" data-end=\"173\">Sundooqsar</strong> and <strong data-start=\"178\" data-end=\"189\">Chanaaz</strong>.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">In winter, the snow-covered landscape transforms into a playground for skiing and snowboarding enthusiasts</span> .</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">For decades, Tosamaidan served as a military artillery firing range, earning it the somber nickname \"Meadow of Death.\"</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Between 1964 and 2014, unexploded ordnance led to numerous casualties.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">However, following public outcry and a demining operation in 2014, the area was cleared and opened to eco-tourism.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '1745999899.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 07:58:19', '2025-04-30 07:58:19'),
(93, 'Drass: The Coldest Inhabited Place in India', 'drass-the-coldest-inhabited-place-in-india', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"59\" data-end=\"566\"><strong>Drass,&nbsp;</strong>often called the \"Gateway to Ladakh,\" is a place where history, natural beauty, and adventure converge. From its chilly weather to its serene landscapes, this small town in the Kargil district offers a unique experience for travelers. Whether it\'s visiting the <strong data-start=\"327\" data-end=\"349\">Drass War Memorial</strong> to pay tribute to the Kargil heroes, trekking the challenging terrain of <strong data-start=\"423\" data-end=\"437\">Tiger Hill</strong>, or immersing yourself in the local culture and tranquility of the surrounding valleys, Drass promises an unforgettable journey.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"568\" data-end=\"876\">The town\'s rich history, especially the events of the Kargil War, adds depth to its beauty, making it not just a travel destination, but also a place of reflection. Whether you\'re an adventure seeker, history enthusiast, or someone simply wanting to connect with nature, Drass has something special in store.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"878\" data-end=\"1064\">So, pack your bags and make your way to this cold and captivating corner of India&mdash;it&rsquo;s sure to leave you with lasting memories and a deep appreciation for this remarkable part of Ladakh.</p>\r\n<p>‚Äã</p>', '1746000417.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 08:06:57', '2025-04-30 08:06:57'),
(94, 'Sindhu Ghat ‚Äì A Serene Escape by the Indus River in Leh', 'sindhu-ghat-a-serene-escape-by-the-indus-river-in-leh', '<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\"><strong>Sindhu Ghat in Leh,</strong> Ladakh, is a serene riverside destination that blends spiritual significance with natural beauty.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Located near Shey Palace on the Manali-Leh Highway, approximately 9 kilometers from Leh town, it offers a tranquil setting for reflection and cultural experiences.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The ghat is named after the Sindhu River, known as the Indus River in English. It serves as a sacred site for both Hindu and Buddhist pilgrims. Visitors often come here for prayers, rituals, and to meditate along the riverbanks, surrounded by the majestic Himalayan landscape.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Sindhu Ghat is renowned for hosting the annual Sindhu Darshan Festival, a three-day event celebrated during the full moon of Guru Purnima in June. The festival honors the Sindhu River and promotes national integration through cultural exchange.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"891\" data-end=\"1057\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The ghat\'s architecture features wide stone steps leading down to the river, providing a peaceful spot for meditation and photography.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The surrounding area offers stunning views of the rugged mountains and the flowing river</span> .<span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">For adventure enthusiasts, river rafting is available in the vicinity, offering an adrenaline rush amidst the serene landscape</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">‚Äã</span></p>', '1746010183.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 10:49:43', '2025-04-30 10:49:43'),
(95, 'Chadar Trek - Living the ICE AGE Dream', 'chadar-trek-living-the-ice-age-dream', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"481\">The <strong>Chadar Trek</strong> is not just a trek&mdash;it\'s a walk across a frozen river, a test of endurance, and a spiritual journey through the icy heart of Ladakh. For eight surreal days, I walked on the glassy surface of the frozen Zanskar River, surrounded by towering cliffs and absolute silence, broken only by the crunch of my boots and the occasional crack of shifting ice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"483\" data-end=\"818\">Each morning began in sub-zero temperatures, layering up before stepping back onto the \"chadar\" (ice sheet). The frozen waterfalls, caves, and sheer beauty of the snow-clad Zanskar valley made every shiver worth it. The highlight? Reaching the Nerak waterfall&mdash;a surreal curtain of frozen blue ice that felt like nature&rsquo;s own sculpture.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"820\" data-end=\"1086\">It wasn&rsquo;t easy&mdash;temperatures dropped below -20&deg;C, and every step had to be carefully placed&mdash;but the sense of achievement at the end was like no other. If you\'re looking for adventure, solitude, and raw Himalayan beauty, the Chadar Trek will leave you changed forever.</p>', '1746010387.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 10:53:07', '2025-04-30 10:53:07'),
(96, 'Finding Myself in the Mountains: A Solo Journey Through Ladakh', 'finding-myself-in-the-mountains-a-solo-journey-through-ladakh', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"187\" data-end=\"374\">Traveling solo to Ladakh wasn&rsquo;t a decision&mdash;it was a calling. I had been yearning for stillness, for space, for something that would shake me gently awake. Ladakh did all of that and more.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"376\" data-end=\"708\">From the moment I landed in Leh, the air felt different&mdash;not just thinner, but clearer, purer. I spent the first couple of days acclimatizing, sipping endless cups of butter tea, and watching the town unfold around me. The silence in the mountains is loud in the best way&mdash;it makes room for your thoughts, your fears, and your wonder.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"710\" data-end=\"1071\">I joined a shared taxi to Nubra Valley. We were strangers at first, but something about freezing together at Khardung La and laughing over Maggi noodles made us feel like old friends by the end. Pangong Lake took my breath away&mdash;literally and figuratively. I stood by its shimmering blue expanse, completely alone but feeling more connected than I had in months.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1073\" data-end=\"1264\">What I learned? You&rsquo;re never truly alone in Ladakh. The mountains watch over you, the locals smile with quiet warmth, and every curve in the road feels like it\'s leading you back to yourself.</p>', '1746010682.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 10:58:02', '2025-04-30 10:58:02'),
(97, 'Into the Meadows: My Walk to Lidderwat', 'into-the-meadows-my-walk-to-lidderwat', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"166\" data-end=\"239\">I hadn&rsquo;t planned to fall in love with Lidderwat&mdash;it just sort of happened.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"241\" data-end=\"516\">It started in Aru, a sleepy little village near Pahalgam, where pine trees lean in like they&rsquo;re sharing secrets. I packed a light bag, laced up my boots, and followed the trail with no expectations&mdash;just a quiet excitement and the sound of the Lidder River keeping me company.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"518\" data-end=\"796\">The path to Lidderwat winds gently through forests that smell of pine and damp earth. Every so often, the trees open up to wide green meadows where shepherds wave as you pass, and wildflowers nod in the breeze. It doesn&rsquo;t feel like a trek; it feels like a long, peaceful exhale.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"798\" data-end=\"1088\">When I finally reached Lidderwat, the valley just opened up&mdash;lush, silent, and seemingly untouched. A few Gujjar huts sat in the distance, smoke rising in lazy spirals. I pitched my tent by the river, and as night fell, the stars spilled across the sky like they were poured out just for me.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1090\" data-end=\"1206\">There was no WiFi, no noise, no rush. Just the mountains, the river, and the stillness I&rsquo;d been unknowingly craving.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1208\" data-end=\"1296\">Lidderwat isn&rsquo;t just a place&mdash;it&rsquo;s a feeling. And it stays with you long after you leave.</p>', '1746010935.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 11:02:15', '2025-04-30 11:02:15'),
(98, 'Awantipora Ruins: A Journey Through Kashmir\'s Ancient Heritage', 'awantipora-ruins-a-journey-through-kashmirs-ancient-heritage', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"443\">The<em><strong> Awantipora Ruins</strong></em> are a testament to Kashmir\'s rich architectural and cultural heritage. These ancient temples, dating back to the 9th century, were built by King Avantivarman of the Utpala dynasty. The site features two temples: the Avantiswami Temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu and the Avantishwara Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"445\" data-end=\"688\">The intricate stone carvings and detailed architecture of these temples showcase the craftsmanship of that era. The Avantiswami Temple, in particular, is known for its two-tiered structure, a paved courtyard, and columns with sculpted reliefs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"954\">Awantipora was once a center of Hindu philosophy and Sanskrit learning. However, by the 14th century, the region fell under Muslim rule, leading to the decline of these temples. Rediscovered in the early 20th century, the ruins now serve as a window into the past.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"956\" data-end=\"1191\">The site, maintained by the Archaeological Survey of India, is best visited during the post-monsoon months of October and November, when the surrounding saffron fields near Pampore bloom, adding to the beauty of this historic location.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1193\" data-end=\"1373\">If you\'re ever in Kashmir, don\'t miss the chance to visit the Awantipora Ruins &mdash; a peaceful, historical escape that offers both serenity and a deep connection to the region&rsquo;s past.</p>', '1746011652.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-04-30 11:14:12', '2025-04-30 11:14:12'),
(100, 'Dachigam National Park: Kashmir‚Äôs Wild Sanctuary of the Hangul', 'dachigam-national-park-kashmirs-wild-sanctuary-of-the-hangul', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"40\" data-end=\"152\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Dachigam National Park, nestled in the picturesque Kashmir Valley near Srinagar, is a sanctuary for wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers alike.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Spanning approximately 141 square kilometers, the park is renowned for its rich biodiversity and stunning landscapes.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"188\" data-end=\"385\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Dachigam is globally recognized as the last refuge of the critically endangered Hangul, or Kashmir stag (Cervus hanglu), the only species of red deer native to India.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The park is also home to a diverse array of mammals, including the Himalayan black bear, musk deer, leopard, Himalayan brown bear, and the elusive snow leopard in its upper reaches.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Birdwatchers can delight in spotting over 145 bird species, such as the Himalayan monal, crimson tragopan, koklass pheasant, and golden oriole</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"413\" data-end=\"612\"><span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">The park\'s varied terrain ranges from dense coniferous forests to alpine meadows, with elevations between 1,600 and 4,200 meters.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Flora includes over 500 species of herbs, 50 types of trees, and 20 types of shrubs, featuring species like walnut, oak, pine, and wild cherry.</span> <span class=\"relative -mx-px my-[-0.2rem] rounded px-px py-[0.2rem] transition-colors duration-100 ease-in-out\">Notable water bodies within the park include the serene Marsar Lake and the Dagwan River</span></p>', '1746271114.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-03 11:18:34', '2025-05-03 11:18:34'),
(101, 'Top Places to Visit in Kashmir ‚Äì Heaven on Earth', 'top-places-to-visit-in-kashmir-heaven-on-earth', '<p>Known as &ldquo;Paradise on Earth,&rdquo; <strong data-start=\"208\" data-end=\"219\">Kashmir</strong> is a stunning valley nestled in the Himalayas, offering breathtaking landscapes, snow-capped mountains, serene lakes, and vibrant culture. Whether you&rsquo;re seeking adventure, tranquility, or cultural richness, Kashmir has something for every kind of traveler. Here&rsquo;s a curated list of the top places to visit in Kashmir that will make your journey unforgettable.<br><br></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"587\" data-end=\"626\"><strong data-start=\"590\" data-end=\"626\">1. Srinagar &ndash; The Summer Capital</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"627\" data-end=\"799\">Srinagar is the heart of Kashmir and a must-visit. Famous for the <strong data-start=\"693\" data-end=\"705\">Dal Lake</strong>, <strong data-start=\"707\" data-end=\"721\">houseboats</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"727\" data-end=\"745\">Mughal gardens</strong>, it&rsquo;s a perfect blend of natural beauty and heritage.<br><br><strong>A must-visit place:-</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"817\" data-end=\"968\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"817\" data-end=\"845\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"819\" data-end=\"845\">A Shikara ride on Dal Lake</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"846\" data-end=\"882\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"848\" data-end=\"882\">Staying in a traditional houseboat</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"883\" data-end=\"924\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"885\" data-end=\"924\">Exploring Nishat Bagh and Shalimar Bagh</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"925\" data-end=\"968\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"927\" data-end=\"968\">Shopping at the floating vegetable market.<br><br><br></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"975\" data-end=\"1014\"><strong data-start=\"978\" data-end=\"1014\">2. Gulmarg &ndash; The Skiing Paradise</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1015\" data-end=\"1181\">A haven for adventure lovers, Gulmarg is India&rsquo;s top skiing destination. Covered in snow during winter and blooming with wildflowers in summer, it&rsquo;s a year-round gem.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1183\" data-end=\"1203\"><strong data-start=\"1183\" data-end=\"1203\">Top attractions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1204\" data-end=\"1387\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1204\" data-end=\"1266\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1206\" data-end=\"1266\">Gulmarg Gondola (one of the highest cable cars in the world)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1267\" data-end=\"1302\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1269\" data-end=\"1302\">Skiing and snowboarding in winter</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1303\" data-end=\"1360\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1305\" data-end=\"1360\">Golfing at one of the highest golf courses in the world</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1361\" data-end=\"1387\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1363\" data-end=\"1387\">Trekking and photography.<br><br></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1394\" data-end=\"1438\"><strong data-start=\"1397\" data-end=\"1438\">3. Pahalgam &ndash; The Valley of Shepherds</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1439\" data-end=\"1591\">A peaceful town surrounded by lush meadows and pine forests, Pahalgam is ideal for nature lovers. It&rsquo;s also a starting point for the <strong data-start=\"1572\" data-end=\"1590\">Amarnath Yatra</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1593\" data-end=\"1608\"><strong data-start=\"1593\" data-end=\"1608\">Highlights:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1609\" data-end=\"1745\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1609\" data-end=\"1658\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1611\" data-end=\"1658\">Betaab Valley (named after the Bollywood movie)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1659\" data-end=\"1683\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1661\" data-end=\"1683\">Aru and Lidder Valleys</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1684\" data-end=\"1715\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1686\" data-end=\"1715\">River rafting in Lidder River</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1716\" data-end=\"1745\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1718\" data-end=\"1745\">Horseback riding and hiking<br><br></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1752\" data-end=\"1791\"><strong data-start=\"1755\" data-end=\"1791\">4. Sonamarg &ndash; The Meadow of Gold</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1792\" data-end=\"1934\">True to its name, Sonamarg dazzles with golden meadows and glaciers. It&rsquo;s the gateway to several high-altitude treks and the <strong data-start=\"1917\" data-end=\"1933\">Zoji La Pass</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1936\" data-end=\"1958\"><strong data-start=\"1936\" data-end=\"1958\">Things to explore:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1959\" data-end=\"2088\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1959\" data-end=\"1982\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1961\" data-end=\"1982\">Thajiwas Glacier trek</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1983\" data-end=\"2014\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1985\" data-end=\"2014\">Pony rides across the meadows</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2015\" data-end=\"2043\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2017\" data-end=\"2043\">Camping by the Sindh River</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2044\" data-end=\"2088\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2046\" data-end=\"2088\">Photography of snow-capped Himalayan peaks.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1746425823.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-05 06:17:03', '2025-05-05 06:17:03'),
(102, 'Kashmir Through the Seasons ‚Äì Travel Guide by Joy Travels', 'kashmir-through-the-seasons-travel-guide-by-joy-travels', '<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"426\"><strong data-start=\"367\" data-end=\"392\">Spring (March to May)</strong> &ndash; <em data-start=\"395\" data-end=\"424\">Blossoms &amp; Pleasant Weather</em></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"427\" data-end=\"568\">Spring transforms Kashmir into a colorful paradise. The <strong data-start=\"483\" data-end=\"499\">Tulip Garden</strong> in Srinagar comes alive, and the weather is perfect for sightseeing.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"660\"><strong data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"583\">Best for:</strong> Garden lovers, nature walks, and photography.<br><br></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"660\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"667\" data-end=\"735\">üåø <strong data-start=\"674\" data-end=\"701\">Summer (June to August)</strong> &ndash; <em data-start=\"704\" data-end=\"733\">Green Valleys &amp; Clear Skies</em></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"736\" data-end=\"904\">This is peak tourist season. The valleys are lush, the lakes are sparkling, and the temperatures are mild. Ideal for <strong data-start=\"853\" data-end=\"872\">houseboat stays</strong>, <strong data-start=\"874\" data-end=\"886\">trekking</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"892\" data-end=\"903\">camping</strong>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"906\" data-end=\"998\"><strong data-start=\"906\" data-end=\"919\">Best for:</strong> Family vacations, adventure travel.<br><br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1005\" data-end=\"1075\">üçÅ <strong data-start=\"1012\" data-end=\"1046\">Autumn (September to November)</strong> &ndash; <em data-start=\"1049\" data-end=\"1073\">Golden Glow of Chinars</em></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1076\" data-end=\"1219\">Autumn in Kashmir is magical, with <strong data-start=\"1111\" data-end=\"1127\">Chinar trees</strong> turning red and gold. The air is crisp, and the landscapes look straight out of a painting.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1221\" data-end=\"1311\"><strong data-start=\"1221\" data-end=\"1234\">Best for:</strong> Scenic beauty, fewer crowds, peaceful travel.<br><br data-start=\"1279\" data-end=\"1282\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1221\" data-end=\"1311\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1318\" data-end=\"1380\">‚ùÑÔ∏è <strong data-start=\"1325\" data-end=\"1358\">Winter (December to February)</strong> &ndash; <em data-start=\"1361\" data-end=\"1378\">Snow Wonderland</em></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1381\" data-end=\"1536\">Kashmir turns into a snowy fairytale. <strong data-start=\"1419\" data-end=\"1430\">Gulmarg</strong> is a hotspot for <strong data-start=\"1448\" data-end=\"1458\">skiing</strong> and <strong data-start=\"1463\" data-end=\"1479\">snowboarding</strong>, while Srinagar offers frozen lakes and cozy houseboats.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1538\" data-end=\"1624\"><strong data-start=\"1538\" data-end=\"1551\">Best for:</strong> Snow lovers, winter sports, Couples.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1538\" data-end=\"1624\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1538\" data-end=\"1624\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1631\" data-end=\"1668\">üèîÔ∏è <strong data-start=\"1639\" data-end=\"1666\">So, When Should You Go?</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1669\" data-end=\"1874\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1669\" data-end=\"1707\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1671\" data-end=\"1707\"><strong data-start=\"1671\" data-end=\"1684\">For snow:</strong> December to February</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1708\" data-end=\"1762\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1710\" data-end=\"1762\"><strong data-start=\"1710\" data-end=\"1747\">For flowers and pleasant weather:</strong> March to May</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1763\" data-end=\"1818\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1765\" data-end=\"1818\"><strong data-start=\"1765\" data-end=\"1801\">For green meadows and adventure:</strong> June to August</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1819\" data-end=\"1874\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1821\" data-end=\"1874\"><strong data-start=\"1821\" data-end=\"1852\">For golden leaves and calm:</strong> September to November</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1746433362.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-05 08:22:42', '2025-05-05 08:22:42'),
(103, 'Warming Flavors of the Valley: Must-Try Foods in Kashmir', 'warming-flavors-of-the-valley-must-try-foods-in-kashmir', '<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"311\" data-end=\"332\">1. <strong data-start=\"318\" data-end=\"332\">Rogan Josh</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"333\" data-end=\"557\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"333\" data-end=\"428\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"335\" data-end=\"428\"><strong data-start=\"335\" data-end=\"349\">What it is</strong>: A slow-cooked lamb curry flavored with Kashmiri chillies, fennel, and ginger.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"431\" data-end=\"557\"><strong data-start=\"431\" data-end=\"446\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;It\'s the most iconic Kashmiri dish and perfect for explaining local spice blends and slow cooking techniques.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"559\" data-end=\"578\">2. <strong data-start=\"566\" data-end=\"578\">Gushtaba</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"579\" data-end=\"782\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"579\" data-end=\"695\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"581\" data-end=\"695\"><strong data-start=\"581\" data-end=\"595\">What it is</strong>: Hand-pounded meatballs in a yogurt-based gravy, usually served at the end of a traditional wazwan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"698\" data-end=\"782\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Called the &ldquo;dish of kings&rdquo;; essential in Kashmiri wedding feasts.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"784\" data-end=\"801\">3. <strong data-start=\"791\" data-end=\"801\">Yakhni</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"802\" data-end=\"984\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"802\" data-end=\"888\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"804\" data-end=\"888\"><strong data-start=\"804\" data-end=\"818\">What it is</strong>: Mild mutton cooked in a yogurt-based gravy with fennel and cardamom.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"891\" data-end=\"984\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Highlights subtlety in Kashmiri cooking&mdash;light, aromatic, and non-spicy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"891\" data-end=\"984\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"986\" data-end=\"1005\">4. <strong data-start=\"993\" data-end=\"1005\">Dum Aloo</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1201\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1094\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1008\" data-end=\"1094\"><strong data-start=\"1008\" data-end=\"1022\">What it is</strong>: Baby potatoes cooked in a spicy red gravy made with Kashmiri chillies.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1097\" data-end=\"1201\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A vegetarian delight, great for discussing Himalayan ingredients like dried ginger.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1097\" data-end=\"1201\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1203\" data-end=\"1223\">5. <strong data-start=\"1210\" data-end=\"1223\">Haak Saag</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1224\" data-end=\"1398\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1224\" data-end=\"1299\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1226\" data-end=\"1299\"><strong data-start=\"1226\" data-end=\"1240\">What it is</strong>: Collard greens simply cooked with mustard oil and garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1226\" data-end=\"1299\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This humble, everyday dish reflects the simple beauty of Kashmiri home cooking.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1400\" data-end=\"1422\">6. <strong data-start=\"1407\" data-end=\"1422\">Modur Pulao</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1423\" data-end=\"1619\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1423\" data-end=\"1513\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1425\" data-end=\"1513\"><strong data-start=\"1425\" data-end=\"1439\">What it is</strong>: Sweet Kashmiri pulao made with dry fruits, saffron, and a hint of sugar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1516\" data-end=\"1619\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A visual post&mdash;its colors and aromas are photogenic and rich in storytelling potential.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1621\" data-end=\"1656\">7. <strong data-start=\"1628\" data-end=\"1656\">Kashmiri Naan &amp; Sheermal</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1657\" data-end=\"1813\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1657\" data-end=\"1735\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1659\" data-end=\"1735\"><strong data-start=\"1659\" data-end=\"1676\">What they are</strong>: Slightly sweet flatbreads often served with tea or curry.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1738\" data-end=\"1813\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Perfect for breakfast or food pairing features with kahwa.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1815\" data-end=\"1852\">8. <strong data-start=\"1822\" data-end=\"1852\">Kahwa (Kashmiri Green Tea)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1853\" data-end=\"2012\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1853\" data-end=\"1935\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1855\" data-end=\"1935\"><strong data-start=\"1855\" data-end=\"1869\">What it is</strong>: Green tea infused with saffron, cinnamon, cardamom, and almonds.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1855\" data-end=\"1935\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ideal for cozy food stories and wellness-related content.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2014\" data-end=\"2045\">9. <strong data-start=\"2021\" data-end=\"2045\">Noon Chai (Pink Tea)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2046\" data-end=\"2214\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2046\" data-end=\"2121\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2048\" data-end=\"2121\"><strong data-start=\"2048\" data-end=\"2062\">What it is</strong>: A salty, buttery pink tea made with baking soda and milk.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2122\" data-end=\"2214\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2124\" data-end=\"2214\">Unique in taste and appearance&mdash;great conversation starter in blogs.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2216\" data-end=\"2254\">10. <strong data-start=\"2224\" data-end=\"2254\">Wazwan (Traditional Feast)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2255\" data-end=\"2457\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2255\" data-end=\"2343\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2257\" data-end=\"2343\"><strong data-start=\"2257\" data-end=\"2271\">What it is</strong>: A multi-course Kashmiri feast served during weddings and celebrations.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2344\" data-end=\"2457\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2346\" data-end=\"2457\">Feature the <strong data-start=\"2376\" data-end=\"2390\">experience</strong>&mdash;not just the food but also the culture, rituals, and presentation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1746440576.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-05 10:22:56', '2025-05-05 10:22:56'),
(105, 'Unseen Kashmir: Secret Valleys, Waterfalls & Villages Worth the Journey', 'unseen-kashmir-secret-valleys-waterfalls-villages-worth-the-journey', '<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"325\" data-end=\"349\">1. <strong data-start=\"332\" data-end=\"347\">Doodhpathri</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"550\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"446\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"352\" data-end=\"446\">&nbsp;Meadows, pine forests, and streams with far fewer tourists than Gulmarg.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"447\" data-end=\"550\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"449\" data-end=\"550\">Peaceful treks, picnic spots, and the milky-white stream (\"Doodh\" means milk).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"552\" data-end=\"578\">2. <strong data-start=\"559\" data-end=\"576\">Bangus Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"579\" data-end=\"778\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"579\" data-end=\"691\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"581\" data-end=\"691\">A remote, untouched valley near Kupwara&mdash;green pastures and rare Himalayan wildlife.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"692\" data-end=\"778\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"694\" data-end=\"778\">&nbsp;Perfect for wilderness lovers and those looking for off-grid travel.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"780\" data-end=\"805\">3. <strong data-start=\"787\" data-end=\"803\">Gurez Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"806\" data-end=\"1030\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"806\" data-end=\"935\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"808\" data-end=\"935\">&nbsp;Snow-capped peaks, wooden homes, and the Habba Khatoon peak named after a famous Kashmiri poetess.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"936\" data-end=\"1030\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"938\" data-end=\"1030\">&nbsp;Near the Line of Control, yet safe and surreal. Great for cultural storytelling.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1032\" data-end=\"1058\">4. <strong data-start=\"1039\" data-end=\"1056\">Tulail Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1059\" data-end=\"1220\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1059\" data-end=\"1135\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1061\" data-end=\"1135\">Located beyond Gurez; few tourists ever reach here.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1136\" data-end=\"1220\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1220\">Highlight the road less traveled and the silence of raw landscapes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1222\" data-end=\"1247\">5. <strong data-start=\"1229\" data-end=\"1245\">Lolab Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1248\" data-end=\"1428\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1248\" data-end=\"1335\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1250\" data-end=\"1335\">&nbsp;Quiet villages, rice fields, ancient springs, and warm locals.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1336\" data-end=\"1428\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1338\" data-end=\"1428\">&nbsp;A natural beauty spot that rarely appears on mainstream travel guides.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1430\" data-end=\"1450\">6. <strong data-start=\"1437\" data-end=\"1448\">Chatpal</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1563\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1486\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1453\" data-end=\"1486\">&nbsp;Near Anantnag.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1487\" data-end=\"1563\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1489\" data-end=\"1563\">&nbsp;Like Pahalgam but without the crowds&mdash;lush and photogenic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1565\" data-end=\"1595\">7. <strong data-start=\"1572\" data-end=\"1593\">Aharbal Waterfall</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1598\" data-end=\"1645\"><strong data-start=\"1598\" data-end=\"1610\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong>The \"Niagara Falls of Kashmir.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1648\" data-end=\"1740\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Grand waterfall in a pine forest&mdash;not as known as it deserves to be.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1742\" data-end=\"1781\">8. <strong data-start=\"1749\" data-end=\"1779\">Kokernag &amp; Verinag Springs</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1782\" data-end=\"1948\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1782\" data-end=\"1862\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1784\" data-end=\"1862\">&nbsp;Ancient Mughal-era gardens and crystal-clear natural springs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1863\" data-end=\"1948\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1865\" data-end=\"1948\">&nbsp;Ideal for photo essays or \"tranquil Kashmir\" themes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"1976\">9. <strong data-start=\"1957\" data-end=\"1974\">Warwan Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1977\" data-end=\"2137\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1977\" data-end=\"2070\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1979\" data-end=\"2070\">Unreachable for most of the year, making it untouched and pristine.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2071\" data-end=\"2137\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2073\" data-end=\"2137\">&nbsp;Feature it as an \"extreme escape\" destination.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2139\" data-end=\"2179\">10. <strong data-start=\"2147\" data-end=\"2177\">Tarsar &amp; Marsar Lakes Trek</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2180\" data-end=\"2326\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2180\" data-end=\"2252\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2182\" data-end=\"2252\">&nbsp;Less crowded than the Kashmir Great Lakes trek.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2253\" data-end=\"2326\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2255\" data-end=\"2326\">&nbsp;Adventure-focused blog readers and nature photographers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '1746442410.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-05 10:53:30', '2025-05-05 10:53:30'),
(106, 'Kashmir‚Äôs Most Breathtaking Treks for Adventure Enthusiasts', 'kashmirs-most-breathtaking-treks-for-adventure-enthusiasts', '<p>The adventure-seeker, it\'s a land of untamed beauty, towering mountains, and pristine alpine trails waiting to be explored. Whether you\'re an experienced trekker or a beginner with a love for nature, Kashmir offers some of the most breathtaking trekking experiences in the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"574\" data-end=\"608\">1. <strong data-start=\"580\" data-end=\"608\">Kashmir Great Lakes Trek</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"609\" data-end=\"638\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"611\" data-end=\"638\">A high-altitude odyssey through seven crystal-clear alpine lakes&mdash;Vishansar, Krishansar, Gadsar, Satsar, Nundkol, and Gangbal. You\'ll walk through blooming meadows, steep ridges, and glacier-fed rivers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"611\" data-end=\"638\">7-day scenic trek covering seven beautiful lakes. Best from July to September.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"611\" data-end=\"638\"><br><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>2. &nbsp;Tarsar Marsar Trek</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li data-start=\"611\" data-end=\"638\">This offbeat trail takes you through charming valleys like Aru and Lidderwat to the mystical twin lakes of Tarsar and Marsar, set in an amphitheater of peaks.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;A moderate 6-day trek through Aru Valley to twin alpine lakes. Peaceful and photogenic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>3. <strong data-start=\"1433\" data-end=\"1460\">Naranag to Gangbal Trek</strong></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This less-traveled route leads to the sacred Gangbal and Nundkol Lakes beneath the imposing Mount Harmukh. Dense forests and remote campsites make it a spiritual and adventurous journey.</li>\r\n<li>A spiritual and quiet route to sacred lakes near Mount Harmukh.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1858\" data-end=\"1888\">4. <strong data-start=\"1864\" data-end=\"1888\">Kolahoi Glacier Trek</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1889\" data-end=\"1918\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1891\" data-end=\"1918\">This trail starts from Pahalgam and takes you through pine forests, river crossings, and mountain villages to the majestic Kolahoi Glacier&mdash;often called the \"Matterhorn of Kashmir.\"</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Trek from Pahalgam to the majestic glacier, with forests and river crossings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong data-start=\"754\" data-end=\"786\">5.Yousmarg to Doodhpathri Trek</strong> &ndash;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gentle meadows, whispering pines, and peaceful rivers make this an excellent choice for beginners or families. A relatively unexplored trail, it connects two of Kashmir&rsquo;s greenest hill stations.</li>\r\n<li>Easy trek ideal for beginners, with rolling meadows and serene landscapes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Kashmir isn&rsquo;t just a destination&mdash;it&rsquo;s an experience. These treks offer more than just adventure; they provide a deep connection with nature, glimpses into local life, and unforgettable mountain moments. If you\'re an adventure lover, trekking in Kashmir should be on your bucket list.</strong></p>', '1746518987.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-06 08:09:47', '2025-05-06 08:09:47'),
(107, 'Beyond the Headlines: The Real Kashmir You Haven‚Äôt Seen', 'beyond-the-headlines-the-real-kashmir-you-havent-seen', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"623\">When people hear<strong> &ldquo;Kashmir,</strong>&rdquo; their impressions are often shaped by headlines filled with conflict and unrest. But the ground reality is far richer, deeper, and more peaceful than what&rsquo;s often portrayed. Let&rsquo;s break down the <strong data-start=\"573\" data-end=\"594\">myths vs. reality</strong> of this breathtaking region.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"625\" data-end=\"628\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"630\" data-end=\"673\"><strong data-start=\"637\" data-end=\"673\">Myth 1: Kashmir Is Always Unsafe</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"674\" data-end=\"919\"><strong data-start=\"674\" data-end=\"686\">Reality:</strong> Most areas in Kashmir, especially tourist hubs like Srinagar, Gulmarg, Pahalgam, and Sonamarg, are safe and welcome thousands of visitors every year. Tourists often describe the locals as warm, respectful, and incredibly hospitable.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"921\" data-end=\"924\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"926\" data-end=\"979\"><strong data-start=\"933\" data-end=\"979\">&nbsp;Myth 2: Kashmiris Are Hostile to Outsiders</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"980\" data-end=\"1128\"><strong data-start=\"980\" data-end=\"992\">Reality:</strong> Kashmiris are known for their generosity and warmth toward visitors. Most travelers leave with new friendships and stories of kindness.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1130\" data-end=\"1133\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1135\" data-end=\"1195\"><strong data-start=\"1143\" data-end=\"1195\">Myth 3: There&rsquo;s Nothing to Do Except Sightseeing</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1196\" data-end=\"1416\"><strong data-start=\"1196\" data-end=\"1208\">Reality:</strong> Beyond sightseeing, Kashmir offers trekking, skiing, rafting, Sufi music, culinary exploration, and cultural tours. It\'s an all-season destination for adventurers, spiritual seekers, and nature lovers alike.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1418\" data-end=\"1421\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1423\" data-end=\"1473\"><strong data-start=\"1430\" data-end=\"1473\">Myth 4: The Media Shows the Whole Truth</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1474\" data-end=\"1706\"><strong data-start=\"1474\" data-end=\"1486\">Reality:</strong> While news often focuses on political unrest, it rarely covers the region&rsquo;s art, culture, resilience, or daily life. There\'s so much beauty in how locals live, celebrate festivals, and preserve centuries-old traditions.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1713\" data-end=\"1772\"><strong data-start=\"1720\" data-end=\"1772\">Myth 5: The Region Is Culturally One-Dimensional</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1773\" data-end=\"1930\"><strong data-start=\"1773\" data-end=\"1785\">Reality:</strong> Kashmir has a rich tapestry of cultures&mdash;Muslim, Hindu, Sikh, and Buddhist influences&mdash;reflected in its architecture, food, language, and rituals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1773\" data-end=\"1930\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1956\" data-end=\"2168\">Kashmir is more than beautiful&mdash;it\'s a land of stories, smiles, and unmatched beauty. The next time you hear about Kashmir, look beyond the headlines. You may just discover a world the media often overlooks.</p>', '1746520154.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-06 08:29:14', '2025-05-06 08:29:14');
