(108, 'Joy Travels: Deluxe vs Luxury Travel in Kashmir', 'joy-travels-deluxe-vs-luxury-travel-in-kashmir', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"156\" data-end=\"396\">If you&rsquo;ve ever dreamed of visiting Kashmir&mdash;the land of snow-capped mountains, floating gardens, and soul-soothing silence&mdash;you&rsquo;re not alone. But one question always pops up: <span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><strong data-start=\"329\" data-end=\"396\">Should you go all out on luxury or explore Kashmir on a budget?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\">The good news? You can do both. If you book with <span style=\"background-color: rgb(241, 196, 15);\"><strong>Joy Tour and Travels</strong>,</span> we&rsquo;ll tailor your trip to match your travel style and vibe.</p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong>Where You&rsquo;ll Stay:</strong></em></span></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><em><strong><strong data-start=\"132\" data-end=\"148\">Deluxe Stay:</strong></strong></em></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For the budget-conscious traveler, we offer multiple spacious and comfortable options&mdash;guesthouses, homestays, and small hotels that feel cozy and welcoming. With us, you&rsquo;ll find rooms at very affordable prices, often hosted by warm, friendly locals. Picture yourself sipping hot chai by the window while soaking in a beautiful Kashmiri view.</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong data-start=\"83\" data-end=\"99\">Luxury Stay:</strong></span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If you&rsquo;re after indulgence, Joy Tour and Travels won&rsquo;t disappoint. Picture this: a private balcony overlooking snow-draped pine trees, heated floors, and relaxing spa treatments. Premium properties like&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"305\" data-end=\"330\">The Khyber in Gulmarg</strong> or <strong data-start=\"334\" data-end=\"359\">The Lalit in Srinagar</strong> offer unmatched luxury&mdash;and we can book them for you at the best available rates.</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><strong data-start=\"88\" data-end=\"102\">Getting Around</strong></strong></em></span></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">DeluxeTravel:</span></em></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">You&rsquo;ll find the best rates for private cabs when you book with us. We make it extra special by offering affordable and comfortable transport options, especially tailored for our budget-friendly guests.</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"114\">Luxury Travel:</strong></span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We offer multiple private cab options that are both comfortable and spacious. And if you\'re looking for something truly exclusive, even helicopter trips to Amarnath are possible through us. Comfort, flexibility, and speed&mdash;luxury travel comes at a price, but it\'s worth</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"398\" data-end=\"497\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><em><strong>Food: Street Eats vs Fine Dining</strong></em></span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Affordable meals:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grab a hot plate of Rajma-Chawal or Rogan Josh from a roadside dhaba.Kashmiri food on a budget is flavorful, authentic, and always filling.</p>\r\n<p><strong data-start=\"1809\" data-end=\"1831\"> Gourmet Dining:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Luxury resorts offer curated multi-course Wazwan dinners, organic ingredients, and elegant presentations where every bite will feel like a celebration.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><strong>Shopping in Kashmir:</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2493\" data-end=\"2645\"><strong data-start=\"2493\" data-end=\"2507\">Affordable:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2493\" data-end=\"2645\">Local markets sell beautiful souvenirs&mdash;papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute; boxes, wool shawls, and Copy (but pretty) pashminas. Bargaining is part of the fun</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2647\" data-end=\"2807\"><strong data-start=\"2647\" data-end=\"2661\">&nbsp;Luxury:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2647\" data-end=\"2807\">Visit certified shops for real pashmina, hand-knotted silk carpets, and saffron. You&rsquo;ll pay more, but the quality is top-tier and long-lasting.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2976\" data-end=\"3019\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(224, 62, 45);\"><strong data-start=\"2983\" data-end=\"3019\">So, Which One Should You Choose?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"3021\" data-end=\"3193\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"3021\" data-end=\"3108\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3023\" data-end=\"3108\"><strong data-start=\"3023\" data-end=\"3036\">Go Deluxe</strong>&nbsp;if you&rsquo;re into cultural immersion, flexible travel, and meeting locals.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"3109\" data-end=\"3193\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3111\" data-end=\"3193\"><strong data-start=\"3111\" data-end=\"3124\">Go Luxury</strong> if comfort, convenience, and curated experiences matter most to you.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3195\" data-end=\"3349\"><strong data-start=\"3195\" data-end=\"3207\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(241, 196, 15);\">Pro tip:</span> Joy Tour and Travels will offer the best package options&mdash;whether it&rsquo;s staying in a fancy houseboat for a night or exploring Gulmarg like a backpacker. No matter how you choose to experience Kashmir, Joy Travels will make it even more magical.</strong></p>', '1746612959.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-07 10:15:59', '2025-05-07 10:15:59'),
(109, 'Joy Presents: Top 10 Instagrammable Locations in Kashmir', 'joy-presents-top-10-instagrammable-locations-in-kashmir', '<p><strong>Kashmir</strong> isn&rsquo;t just a destination&mdash;it&rsquo;s a postcard in every direction. From snow-covered peaks to colorful markets and dreamy lakes, this paradise on earth is packed with places that are perfect for your Instagram feed. Whether you&rsquo;re a travel blogger or just love capturing beauty, here are 10 spots that are too stunning to skip.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"653\" data-end=\"685\"><strong data-start=\"659\" data-end=\"685\">1. Dal Lake &ndash; Srinagar</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"686\" data-end=\"754\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"688\" data-end=\"754\">Famous for: Shikara rides, floating markets, reflections at sunset</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"757\" data-end=\"816\">Early morning mist gives a dreamy, soft glow to photos</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"818\" data-end=\"862\"><strong data-start=\"824\" data-end=\"862\">2. Gulmarg &ndash; The Meadow of Flowers</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"863\" data-end=\"918\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"865\" data-end=\"918\">Famous for: Snowy slopes, gondola rides, pine forests</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"921\" data-end=\"966\">Try a wide-angle shot from the cable car.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"968\" data-end=\"1005\"><strong data-start=\"974\" data-end=\"1005\">3. Betaab Valley &ndash; Pahalgam</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1006\" data-end=\"1066\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1008\" data-end=\"1066\">Famous for: Lush meadows, turquoise river, Bollywood vibes</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1069\" data-end=\"1130\">Capture the valley framed by trees or riverside boulders.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1132\" data-end=\"1170\"><strong data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1170\">4. Mughal Gardens &ndash; Srinagar</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1171\" data-end=\"1234\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1173\" data-end=\"1234\">Famous for: Symmetrical gardens, fountains, and floral beauty</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1237\" data-end=\"1276\">Perfect for aesthetic outfit shots.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1278\" data-end=\"1319\"><strong data-start=\"1284\" data-end=\"1319\">5. Sonamarg &ndash; The Golden Meadow</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1320\" data-end=\"1373\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1322\" data-end=\"1373\">Famous for: Vast open fields, snow-capped backdrops</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1376\" data-end=\"1412\">Drone shots here are unbeatable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1414\" data-end=\"1448\"><strong data-start=\"1420\" data-end=\"1448\">6. Pari Mahal &ndash; Srinagar</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1449\" data-end=\"1510\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1510\">Famous for: Historic architecture with panoramic city views</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1513\" data-end=\"1562\">Shoot during golden hour for a magical touch.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1564\" data-end=\"1609\"><strong data-start=\"1570\" data-end=\"1609\">7. Shankaracharya Temple &ndash; Srinagar</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1610\" data-end=\"1665\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1612\" data-end=\"1665\">Famous for: Ancient vibes with a city view at the top</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1668\" data-end=\"1708\">Monochrome shots here feel timeless.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1710\" data-end=\"1756\"><strong data-start=\"1716\" data-end=\"1756\">8. Tulip Garden (Spring Season Only)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1757\" data-end=\"1818\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1759\" data-end=\"1818\">Famous for: Rows of colorful tulips with mountain backdrops</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1821\" data-end=\"1883\">Visit in April for full bloom&mdash;ideal for vibrant portraits.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1885\" data-end=\"1920\"><strong data-start=\"1891\" data-end=\"1920\">9. Houseboats on Dal Lake</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1921\" data-end=\"1987\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1923\" data-end=\"1987\">Famous for: Traditional wood-carved interiors, lakeside serenity</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1990\" data-end=\"2046\">Night shots with reflections of lights are stunning.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"2048\" data-end=\"2083\"><strong data-start=\"2054\" data-end=\"2083\">10. Aru Valley &ndash; Pahalgam</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2084\" data-end=\"2134\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2086\" data-end=\"2134\">Famous for: Rustic landscapes, peaceful villages</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2137\" data-end=\"2193\">&nbsp;Capture candid shots with local shepherds or horses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2219\" data-end=\"2431\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(241, 196, 15);\"><strong>These Instagram-worthy spots in Kashmir are more than just pretty pictures&mdash;they&rsquo;re moments frozen in time. Whether you\'re after nature, culture, or a little bit of both, Kashmir delivers it with unmatched beauty.</strong></span></p>', '1746614253.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-07 10:37:33', '2025-05-07 10:37:33'),
(110, 'Wildlife Sanctuaries and National Parks in Kashmir: A Brief Guide', 'wildlife-sanctuaries-and-national-parks-in-kashmir-a-brief-guide', '<p>Kashmir isn&rsquo;t just about snow and shikaras&mdash;it&rsquo;s also a haven for wildlife lovers. With its rich forests and alpine meadows, the region shelters rare animals like the Hangul deer, snow leopards, and Himalayan black bears. Here are some key spots to explore.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"513\" data-end=\"559\"><strong data-start=\"520\" data-end=\"546\">1.Dachigam National Park</strong> (Srinagar)</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"560\" data-end=\"690\">Home to the endangered Hangul, this park offers stunning landscapes and rich biodiversity. Best visited between April and October.</p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"734\" data-end=\"869\"><strong data-start=\"878\" data-end=\"910\">3.Overa-Aru Wildlife Sanctuary</strong> (Pahalgam)</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"924\" data-end=\"1018\">Nestled in scenic valleys, this sanctuary hosts brown bears, musk deer, and many bird species.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1020\" data-end=\"1069\"><strong data-start=\"1027\" data-end=\"1057\">4.Hirpora Wildlife Sanctuary</strong> (Shopian)</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1070\" data-end=\"1175\">Famous for the endangered Markhor (wild goat), this quiet sanctuary is perfect for peaceful nature walks.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1177\" data-end=\"1215\"><span data-start=\"1184\" data-end=\"1213\">5.</span><strong data-start=\"1184\" data-end=\"1213\">Gulmarg Biosphere Reserve</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1216\" data-end=\"1324\">Rich in birdlife and known for musk deer, this reserve is a dream for birdwatchers and nature photographers.</p>', '1746684233.png', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-07 11:23:56', '2025-05-08 06:03:53'),
(111, 'The Art of Kashmiri Pashmina: A Timeless Legacy of Elegance', 'the-art-of-kashmiri-pashmina-a-timeless-legacy-of-elegance', '<h2 data-start=\"194\" data-end=\"463\">What is Pashmina?</h2>\r\n<p>Pashmina is derived from the Persian word <em data-start=\"614\" data-end=\"623\">\"Pashm\"</em>, meaning \"soft gold,\" and rightly so. This ultra-fine cashmere wool comes from the undercoat of a rare breed of goat known as the <strong data-start=\"754\" data-end=\"786\">Changthangi or Pashmina goat</strong>, found at high altitudes in the cold desert of Ladakh. The harsh climate prompts the goats to grow a warm under-fleece, which is painstakingly collected each spring.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"194\" data-end=\"463\">Woven in the heart of Kashmir,&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"225\" data-end=\"237\">Pashmina</strong> is more than just a luxurious fabric &mdash; it&rsquo;s a centuries-old tradition. Made from the soft undercoat of Changthangi goats found in Ladakh, this fine wool is hand-spun and handwoven by skilled artisans using age-old techniques.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"465\" data-end=\"694\">Delicate embroidery styles like <strong data-start=\"497\" data-end=\"506\">Sozni</strong>, <strong data-start=\"508\" data-end=\"517\">Tilla</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"523\" data-end=\"531\">Kani</strong> add to its elegance, often taking months to complete a single piece. Authentic Kashmiri Pashmina is rare, incredibly soft, and symbolizes timeless craftsmanship.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2149\" data-end=\"2186\"><strong data-start=\"2153\" data-end=\"2186\">Why is Pashmina So Expensive?</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2187\" data-end=\"2560\">Authentic Kashmiri Pashmina is not just a product &mdash; it is a <strong data-start=\"2247\" data-end=\"2291\">labor-intensive piece of living heritage</strong>. The rarity of the raw material, the time taken, and the skill of the artisans all contribute to its cost. Sadly, mass-produced and machine-made imitations have flooded the market, but a genuine Pashmina is always warm, featherlight, and exquisitely soft to the touch.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"3052\" data-end=\"3087\"><strong data-start=\"3056\" data-end=\"3087\">A Gift of Grace</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3088\" data-end=\"3373\">Owning a Kashmiri Pashmina is like holding a piece of Kashmir in your hands &mdash; warm, delicate, and timeless. Whether draped around the shoulders on a chilly evening or passed down generations, a Pashmina shawl tells a story &mdash; of mountains, tradition, and the undying art of human hands.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"696\" data-end=\"770\">Owning one is not just fashion &mdash; it&rsquo;s owning a piece of Kashmiri heritage.</p>', '1746686979.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-08 06:49:39', '2025-05-08 06:49:39'),
(112, 'Adventure Sports in Kashmir: Joyrides Through Snow and Sky', 'adventure-sports-in-kashmir-joyrides-through-snow-and-sky', '<p class=\"\" data-start=\"192\" data-end=\"580\">When most people think of Kashmir, they picture serene lakes, Mughal gardens, and snow-draped mountains. But for thrill-seekers, the Valley offers something even more exciting &mdash; a playground for <strong data-start=\"387\" data-end=\"407\">adventure sports</strong> that rival some of the best destinations in the world. Whether it\'s skiing down powdery slopes or soaring high above the valley, <strong data-start=\"537\" data-end=\"579\">Kashmir is an adrenaline lover&rsquo;s dream</strong>.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"582\" data-end=\"585\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"587\" data-end=\"641\"><strong data-start=\"591\" data-end=\"641\">1. Skiing &amp; Snowboarding &ndash; Gulmarg&rsquo;s Icy Magic</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"642\" data-end=\"958\">Nestled at 8,690 ft, <strong data-start=\"663\" data-end=\"674\">Gulmarg</strong> is India&rsquo;s top skiing destination. From December to March, it transforms into a winter wonderland perfect for skiing, snowboarding, and heli-skiing. The <strong data-start=\"828\" data-end=\"847\">Gulmarg Gondola</strong>, one of the world&rsquo;s highest cable cars, takes you to Apharwat Peak, offering runs for both beginners and pros.</p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"960\" data-end=\"1062\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"960\" data-end=\"996\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"962\" data-end=\"996\"><strong data-start=\"962\" data-end=\"976\">Best time:</strong> December to March</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"997\" data-end=\"1062\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"999\" data-end=\"1062\">&nbsp;Hire a local ski instructor if you\'re new to the sport</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1064\" data-end=\"1067\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1069\" data-end=\"1113\"><strong data-start=\"1073\" data-end=\"1113\">2. Paragliding &ndash; Fly Over the Valley</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1114\" data-end=\"1331\">For a bird&rsquo;s-eye view of Kashmir&rsquo;s beauty, try <strong data-start=\"1161\" data-end=\"1210\">paragliding in Srinagar, Pahalgam, or Sonmarg</strong>. Glide over green meadows, pine forests, and sparkling rivers &mdash; the thrill is unforgettable and the views are unmatched.</p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1333\" data-end=\"1440\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1333\" data-end=\"1366\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1335\" data-end=\"1366\">Best Time: May to October</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1367\" data-end=\"1440\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1369\" data-end=\"1440\"><strong data-start=\"1369\" data-end=\"1387\">Popular spots:</strong> Aru Valley (Pahalgam), Astanmarg (Srinagar), Sonmarg</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1442\" data-end=\"1445\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1447\" data-end=\"1492\"><strong data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1492\">3. River Rafting &ndash; Conquer the Rapids</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1493\" data-end=\"1703\">The <strong data-start=\"1497\" data-end=\"1525\">Lidder River in Pahalgam</strong> and <strong data-start=\"1530\" data-end=\"1556\">Sindh River in Sonmarg</strong> offer grade II&ndash;III rapids, perfect for both beginners and seasoned rafters. Rafting in Kashmir combines adventure with spectacular alpine scenery.</p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1705\" data-end=\"1799\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1705\" data-end=\"1742\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1707\" data-end=\"1742\"><strong data-start=\"1707\" data-end=\"1721\">Best time:</strong> April to September</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1743\" data-end=\"1799\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1745\" data-end=\"1799\">&nbsp;Always go with certified rafting operators</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1801\" data-end=\"1804\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1806\" data-end=\"1848\"><strong data-start=\"1810\" data-end=\"1848\">4. Trekking &ndash; Walk the Wild Trails</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1849\" data-end=\"2081\">From short hikes to multi-day expeditions, Kashmir&rsquo;s trails lead you to <strong data-start=\"1921\" data-end=\"1973\">alpine lakes, high passes, and secluded villages</strong>. The <strong data-start=\"1979\" data-end=\"1999\">Great Lakes Trek</strong>, <strong data-start=\"2001\" data-end=\"2023\">Tarsar Marsar Trek</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"2029\" data-end=\"2053\">Kolahoi Glacier Trek</strong> are among the most popular.</p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2083\" data-end=\"2169\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2083\" data-end=\"2119\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2085\" data-end=\"2119\"><strong data-start=\"2085\" data-end=\"2099\">Best time:</strong> June to September</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2120\" data-end=\"2169\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2122\" data-end=\"2169\">&nbsp;Ranges from easy to challenging</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2171\" data-end=\"2174\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2176\" data-end=\"2214\"><strong data-start=\"2180\" data-end=\"2214\">5. Mountain Biking &amp; ATV Rides</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2215\" data-end=\"2395\">Mountain biking in Gulmarg or ATV rides through rugged terrain in Pahalgam offer high-octane fun amidst natural beauty. These are great options for those who love off-road thrills.</p>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2397\" data-end=\"2400\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2402\" data-end=\"2436\"><strong data-start=\"2406\" data-end=\"2436\">6. Camping &amp; Rock Climbing</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2437\" data-end=\"2621\">Remote valleys like Yusmarg and Doodhpathri are perfect for camping, while <strong data-start=\"2512\" data-end=\"2544\">rock climbing and rappelling</strong> are emerging in places like Sonmarg. It&rsquo;s adventure with a side of solitude.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2628\" data-end=\"2647\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2648\" data-end=\"2919\">Kashmir isn\'t just for poets and photographers &mdash; it&rsquo;s also for those who chase adrenaline. Whether you\'re skiing down the world-class slopes of Gulmarg, rafting through wild rivers, or flying high over the Valley, <strong data-start=\"2862\" data-end=\"2918\">adventure in Kashmir is raw, real, and unforgettable</strong>.</p>', '1746688855.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-08 07:20:55', '2025-05-08 07:20:55'),
(113, 'Joy Travels Presents: A Guide to Kashmiri Handicrafts & Local Markets', 'joy-travels-presents-a-guide-to-kashmiri-handicrafts-local-markets', '<p>A walk through the local markets of Kashmir is like stepping into a living museum of artistry and tradition. From handwoven shawls to intricately carved woodwork, the region&rsquo;s rich heritage is best experienced through its <strong data-start=\"446\" data-end=\"470\">timeless handicrafts</strong> and <strong data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"494\">vibrant bazaars</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"497\" data-end=\"552\"><strong data-start=\"501\" data-end=\"550\">1. Pashmina Shawls &ndash; The Soft Gold of Kashmir</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"553\" data-end=\"796\">No trip to Kashmir is complete without admiring (or buying!) an authentic <strong data-start=\"627\" data-end=\"645\">Pashmina shawl</strong>. Made from fine cashmere wool and often embroidered by hand, these shawls are luxurious, warm, and deeply connected to the valley&rsquo;s cultural identity.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"798\" data-end=\"844\"><strong data-start=\"802\" data-end=\"842\">2. Papier-M&acirc;ch&eacute; &ndash; Art in Every Curve</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"845\" data-end=\"1036\">A centuries-old craft, Kashmiri papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute; involves molding paper pulp into boxes, vases, and decor pieces, then hand-painting them with floral or Mughal designs in gold and vibrant colors.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1038\" data-end=\"1097\"><strong data-start=\"1042\" data-end=\"1095\">3. Walnut Wood Carving &ndash; Where Skill Meets Nature</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1098\" data-end=\"1262\">Kashmiri artisans transform local walnut wood into beautifully carved furniture, jewelry boxes, and home d&eacute;cor. Each piece reflects incredible detail and precision.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1264\" data-end=\"1312\"><strong data-start=\"1268\" data-end=\"1310\">4. Kashmiri Carpets &ndash; Weaving Heritage</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1313\" data-end=\"1513\">Hand-knotted <strong data-start=\"1326\" data-end=\"1351\">silk and wool carpets</strong> from Kashmir are world-renowned for their intricate designs and durability. Often taking months or years to complete, these carpets are prized collector&rsquo;s items.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1515\" data-end=\"1556\"><strong data-start=\"1519\" data-end=\"1554\">5. Saffron, Spices &amp; Dry Fruits</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1557\" data-end=\"1744\">Markets in <strong data-start=\"1568\" data-end=\"1579\">Pampore</strong> (the saffron town), <strong data-start=\"1600\" data-end=\"1613\">Lal Chowk</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"1619\" data-end=\"1639\">Polo View Market</strong> are filled with the aroma of saffron, dried apricots, and rich spices like kehwa mix and Kashmiri chili.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1746\" data-end=\"1783\"><strong data-start=\"1750\" data-end=\"1781\">6. Local Markets to Explore</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1784\" data-end=\"2056\">\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1784\" data-end=\"1877\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1786\" data-end=\"1877\"><strong data-start=\"1786\" data-end=\"1809\">Lal Chowk, Srinagar</strong> &ndash; A bustling city center with everything from shawls to antiques.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1878\" data-end=\"1963\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1880\" data-end=\"1963\"><strong data-start=\"1880\" data-end=\"1900\">Polo View Market</strong> &ndash; Famous for handicrafts, paper-m&acirc;ch&eacute;, and embroidered wear.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1964\" data-end=\"2056\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1966\" data-end=\"2056\"><strong data-start=\"1966\" data-end=\"1992\">Old City (Zaina Kadal)</strong> &ndash; For authentic, old-world charm and direct-from-artisan finds.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2058\" data-end=\"2061\">\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2063\" data-end=\"2082\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Kashmiri handicrafts are not just souvenirs &mdash; they&rsquo;re stories, woven, carved, and painted with love. Exploring the markets is an experience in itself, where every alley echoes with tradition and every purchase supports a legacy.</span></h3>', '1746690529.jpg', 'draft', NULL, '2025-05-08 07:48:49', '2025-05-08 07:48:49'),
