(89, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Jammu To Kashmir Darshan Yatra', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1745651073.jpg', '<p><span data-huuid=\"9762879327230123551\">A tour package combining Mata Vaishno Devi darshan with a trip to Kashmir offers&nbsp;<mark class=\"QVRyCf\">a blend of spiritual experience and scenic beauty</mark>.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"9762879327230122002\">The trip begins with a visit to the holy shrine of Mata Vaishno Devi, located in Katra, Jammu, followed by a journey to Kashmir\'s enchanting landscapes, including Srinagar, Gulmarg, and Pahalgam.<span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"2860128a-6d3f-4862-96c6-f7ab73113d2d\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>', '10', '9', 'Day 1: Arrival Jammu Arrive at the Jammu Airport/ Railway Station. Meet the local Airport Representative/Our Driver and proceed towards your pre booked hotel Hotel for check in. After you check-in and freshen up. After than visit. Raghunath Temple ‚Äì Awe-Striking Architecture/ Ranbireshwar Temple ‚Äì Abode Of 12 Lingam/ Bahu Fort And Temple ‚Äì Amidst Scenic Beauty. Overnight stay on the Hotel.,Day 2: Jammu ‚Äì Katra After Breakfast proceed for Katra. Katra is a small town in Reasi district in the union territory of Jammu and Kashmir situated in the foothills of the Trikuta mountains where the holy shrine of Vaishno Devi is located. In the evening arrive and Check into the hotel. Overnight stay will in Katra. You can also proceed to Mata Vaishnodevi shrine (Trek/Pony on direct payment) in the night.,Day 3: Katra (Darshan Mata Vaishnodevi Temple) After Breakfast proceed for Mata Vaishno Devi Bhawan - one of the most popular pilgrimage of India situated at an altitude of around 5200 feet. Yatra involves a trek of nearly 14 Kms from base camp at Katra known as Ban Ganga. Alternate way to perform darshans is by Helicopter (Need to be booked by guest on shrine board website) or battery operated cars which one can get from midway ( need to be booked well in advance on shrine board website) Ponies/Palkis. Guest can also visit Ardhkuwari & Bhairo Mandir (One can go Bhairo Mandir by ropeway from Vaishno Devi Bhavan tickets for which can be booked on real time basis). After visiting the temples return back to the hotel in Katra and relax for an overnight stay.,Day 4: Katra ‚Äì Patnitop After Breakfast proceed for Patnitop Visit Sudh Mahadev Temple And Naag Devta Temple. After visiting the temples return back to the hotel and relax for an overnight stay,Day 5: Patnitop ‚Äì Pahalgam After Breakfast proceed for Pahalgam Visit Mamal Temple or Mamaleshwar Temple Shri Gaurishanker Temple. After visiting the temples Check inn hotel and relax for an overnight stay.,Day 6: Pahalgam (Half Day excursion to Aru Valley-Betaab Valley-Chandanwari) Today after breakfast visit Aru Valley - offering some fantastic scenes of the lush meadows and mountains. Visit Betaab valley ‚Äì initially known as the Harjan Valley this valley was renamed after the hit Bollywood movie Betaab which was shot in its picturesque surroundings. Visit Chandanwari - starting point for Amarnath Yatra and is a popular hiking destination. Rest of the day is free to stroll in the local market of Pahalgam. Overnight at the hotel in Pahalgam.,Day 7: Pahalgam - Gulmarg (En-route Visit Sun Temple in Martand/Awantipora ruins) Today after breakfast- enjoy a picturesque drive to Gulmarg - \"Meadow of Flowers\". En-route Visit Sun Temple in Martand. Visit Avantipur ruins -A excavated Temple complex dedicated to Lord Shiva and Vishnu were built by King Avantiraman in 9th century. Arrive and check-in at hotel. Evening is free to stroll on own. Overnight stay in Gulmarg.,Day 8: Gulmarg - Srinagar (Enjoy Gondola And Visit Shankaracharya Temple) After Buffet breakfast. Enjoy Asia\'s Highest Cable Car Project Gulmarg Gondola - The Gondola offers all tourists scenic views of Pir Panjal Mountains and Valley as you head towards Phase 1: KHILANMARG. You may enjoy a Sledge ride or Snow Mobile ride on the snow-covered slopes (on direct payment basis) Later proceed to Srinagar. Arrive at Srinagar Visit Shankaracharya Temple Than Check- in into the Hotel. Overnight stay at hotel in Srinagar,Day 9: Day Excursion to Sonmarg (En-route - Visit Kheer Bhawani Temple) After Buffet Breakfast- proceed for day excursion to Sonmarg- En-route - Visit Kheer Bhawani Temple. Arrive Sonamarg. Sonmarg lies in Sind Valley streamed with flowers and surrounded by mountains. Sonmarg is also the base for some interesting treks to the high altitude of Himalayan Lakes. Enjoy riding on a pony up to Thajiwas Glacier (on direct payment basis & subject to Operation) or Sledge Riding on snow (on direct payment). Return back to Srinagar by evening. Overnight stay at hotel,Day 10: Fly Back Home Today after breakfast Do spare a few minutes to share your feedback And Your valued suggestions will be most appreciated. Arrive home with pleasant memories of your Kashmir tour with Joy Tours.', 'Jammu Station/Airport', 'Jammu Station/Airport', '39900', NULL, 'Customized Yatra Holiday', '35999', '9906786356', '2025-04-26 07:04:33', '2025-04-26 07:04:33', '1N Jammu  2N Katra', '1N Patnitop 2N Pahalgam', '1N Gulmarg 2N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
