(105, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Joy Bhaderwah Sintan Top Tour', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746000965.jpg', '<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 1 Jammu &ndash; Bhaderwah (190 kms/5-6 hrs)</h4>\r\n<p>Meet and greet on arrival at Jammu airport/railway station and proceed for Bhaderwah. Bhaderwah Valley in Doda district of Jammu, is situated in the lap of the Himalayas, which offers a perfect escape from the city cacophonies. Perched at an altitude of 1613 meters above sea-level, the town is also famous for adventure tourism. Enjoy the splendid view of lush green meadows surrounded by rich green mountains. O/n Bhaderwah.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 2 Bhaderwah &ndash; Jai Valley &ndash; Bhaderwah</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast leave for a day trip to enchanting Jai Valley &amp; Chinta Valley &ndash; Everlasting lush Green Valley &amp; paradise for Nature lovers. O/n Bhaderwah.</p>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\"><strong>Day : 3 Bhaderwah &ndash; Padri Pass &ndash; Bhaderwah (40 kms one way)</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast proceed for Padri Pass. Padri is at an elevation of 10,000 feet approx., Padri is the highest point on Bhaderwah &ndash; Chamba road. Enjoy magnificent views of luch green meadows from the top. O/n Bhaderwah.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 4 Bhaderwah &ndash; Sinthan Top &ndash; Daksum (195 kms approx. /7-8 hrs)</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast proceed for Daksum. Enroute Sinthan top; a popular tourist destination located at 12,500 feet (3,800 m) above sea level and is snow-capped for most of the year. Reach Daksum &amp; check into the hotel. Daksum is a reviving experience -the bracing mountain air, the solitude, the densely clad hills, and beyond them, snow covered mountains, all contribute to Daksum\'s mystique, making it the perfect retreat. O/n Daksum.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 5 Daksum&nbsp; &ndash; Kokernag&nbsp; &ndash; Daksum</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast leave for Kokernag &ndash; Botanical garden with largest freshwater stream, Verinag &ndash; A major source of River Jhelum; An Octagonal stone basin built by Mughal Emperors is the main attraction and Achabal Garden. O/n Daksum.<br><br></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 6 Daksum &ndash; Srinagar (110 kms/5-6 hrs)</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast proceed for Srinagar. Reach Srinagar; check into the hotel. Enjoy near beautiful Dal Lake. O/n Srinagar.<br><br><strong>Day : 7 Srinagar Local Sightseeing&nbsp;<br></strong>Srinagar local Sightseeing Visit Botinical Garden, pari Mahal, Nishat Bagh, Shalimar Bagh, Chashma Shahi Garden, Shankaracharya Temple, Boulevard Road Nigeen lake and Dal Lake.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 8&nbsp;Final departure</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast drop at Srinagar airport for your onward journey. The tour ends here with the sweet memories of Joy tour and Travels.</p>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '8', '7', 'Day : 1 Jammu ‚Äì Bhaderwah (190 kms/5-6 hrs),Day : 2¬†Bhaderwah ‚Äì Jai Valley ‚Äì Bhaderwah,Day : 3 Bhaderwah ‚Äì Padri Pass ‚Äì Bhaderwah (40 kms one way),Day : 4 Bhaderwah ‚Äì Sinthan Top ‚Äì Daksum (195 kms approx. /7-8 hrs),Day : 5 Daksum¬† ‚Äì Kokernag¬† ‚Äì Daksum,Day : 6 Daksum ‚Äì Srinagar (110 kms/5-6 hrs),Day : 7 Srinagar Local Sightseeing,Day : 8¬†Final departure', 'Jammu Railway Station', 'Srinagar International Airport', '85000', NULL, 'Experience the magic of Himalayas.', '75000', '9906786356', '2025-04-29 07:45:49', '2025-04-30 08:20:30', '3N Bhaderwah', '2N Daksum', '2N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palac