(123, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Joy Leh ‚Äì Kargil ‚Äì Srinagar Tour (With Pangong Lake Night Stay)', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746529052.jpg', '<p>Day 01: Meet and greet on arrival at Kushok Bakula Rimpochee - Leh airport and transfer to the hotel. Full day free for acclimatization. You are advised to stay and relax in the hotel. It&rsquo;s important to take rest for 24 hours and wear heavy woolens.Overnight stay in a Hoteln at Leh City.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why acclimatization is mandatory</strong> &ndash; Leh is at an elevation of 11,500 ft approximately above sea level. When you scale such heights, your body may not get enough time to adapt to the changing surroundings. Though most people do not experience symptoms of Acute Mountain Sickness (AMS) in Leh. But it is advisable to be cautious and be alert for symptoms of AMS. The most common symptoms of AMS are headache, disturbed sleep, loss of appetite, coughing and irregular breathing. One should avoid smoking tobacco, alcohol and caffeine-based drinks as they dehydrate the body and interfere with the process of acclimatization.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 02:After breakfast proceed for Leh city sightseeing which includes Hemis Monastery &ndash; Oldest and richest monastery of Ladakh, Thiksey Monastery &ndash; Historic Buddhist monastery on a Hill, Shey palace, Rancho School &ndash; subject to permission, Sindhu Ghat, Hall of fame museum &ndash; Indian army operated memorial &amp; museum, Shanti stupa &ndash; Domed Buddhist temple on a hill, and Leh Palace &ndash; Centuries old mountaintop palace. Evening explore Leh market.Overnight stay in a Hoteln at Leh City.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 03:After early breakfast leave for Nubra valley (5-6 hrs drive) via Khardungla pass @ 18,380 ft (World&rsquo;s highest motorable road). Reach Nubra valley by afternoon. Nubra Valley offers tremendous scenery on a grand scale with green oasis villages surrounded by thrillingly stark scree slopes and harsh arid mountains. You can enjoy Two hump camel safari on the World&rsquo;s highest coldest desert at own expenses. Overnight stay in a&nbsp; Nubra Valley.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 04: After breakfast proceed for Leh by same route via Diskit &ndash; Future Buddha Statue &amp; Khardungla pass. Overnight stay in Leh</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 05: After breakfast leave for Pangong Lake (4-5 hrs drive) through Changla pass (17,350 ft - world&rsquo;s third highest motorable road). Pangong Lake is at an altitude of 14,500 ft and is World&rsquo;s highest and longest salt water lake. Check into the tents near Pangong lake. Enjoy changing colours of the Blue brackish Lake. Overnight stay at&nbsp; Pangong Lake.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 06:After breakfast proceed for Leh by same route via Changla Pass. Overnight stay in Leh.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 07: After breakfast proceed for Kargil (9-10 hrs drive); Enroute visit Pathar Saheb Gurudwara, Confluence of Indus &amp; Zanskar rivers, Magnetic Hill, also visit Lamayuru Monastery &amp; enjoy magnificent view of &ldquo;Moonland - An undulating series of mountains that resemble the surface of the moon.&rdquo;, Mulbek (1st Century Giant Living Buddha Sculpture on Rock Mountain). Reach Kargil &amp; check into the hotel. Overnight stay in Kargil.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 08:Early morning proceed for Srinagar; En route Kargil War Famous Peaks, Drass Village and Zojila Pass. Enjoy hot breakfast at Sonmarg. Reach Srinagar; check into the hotel. Overnight stay in Kargil.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Day 09: Drop at Srinagar airport and catch flight for your onward journey. The tour ends here with the sweet memories of&nbsp; Joy Tour and Travels.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '9', '8', 'Day 01 L: Arrival at Leh Airport,Day 02: Leh City Sightseeing,Day 03: Leh ‚Äì Nubra Valley,Day 04:Nubra Valley ‚Äì Leh,Day 05:  Leh ‚Äì Pangong Lake,Day 06: Pangong Lake ‚Äì Leh,Day 07: Leh ‚Äì Kargil,Day 08: Kargil ‚Äì Srinagar,Day 09: Drop at Srinagar Airport', 'Kushok Bakula Rimpochee Airport', 'Srinagar Airport', '28000', NULL, 'Special offer', '24000', '9906786356', '2025-05-06 10:57:32', '2025-05-06 10:57:32', '04N Leh,01 N Nubra', '01N Pangong,01N Kargil,', '01N Sgr', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(124, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Tarsar Marsar Trek, Kashmir', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746603641.jpg', '<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 1 Srinagar &ndash; Pahalgam Valley.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Meet and greet on arrival at Srinagar airport and proceed for Pahalgam (4-5hrs). Reach Pahalgam and check into the hotel. O/n Pahalgam Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 2 Pahalgam &ndash; Aru Valley.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast leave for Aru Camp (2414 Mts/ 10 kms by road). Check into the tents. You can go for a small trek around Aru valley. O/n Aru Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 3 Aru &ndash; Lidderwat Valley.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast trek to Lidderwat (3050 Mts &ndash; Trek: 10 kms). The trail on way is a pleasant one, with easy uphill ascent. Reach Camp and relax. O/n Lidderwat Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 4 Lidderwat &ndash; Shekwas Valley.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After breakfast Trek to Shekwas (Trek: 6 Kms). The trail is mostly ascending with intermediate flat grounds and one river crossing en route. After passing through pine forests and some intermittent clearings you will reach wide sweeping grasslands that are formed from the merger of many valleys that converge here. The trail climbs swiftly pass a few Gujjar huts to the camping grounds of Shekhwas. O/n Shekwas Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 5 Shekhwas &ndash; Tarsar Lake.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">After early breakfast Trek for Tarsar Lake (Trek: 5 Kms). It is a gentle climb to Tarsar through tall grasses, a few ridges and finally to the shore of the lake. The turquoise blue water is surrounded by lush meadows and snow-capped peaks. This campsite is truly heaven on earth. O/n Tarsar Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 6 Tarsar &ndash; Sundersar Lake.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Today morning start trek to Sundersar (Trek: 5 Kms). Sundarsar has big flat streches that is a perfect camping spot. O/n Sundersar Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 7 Sundersar &ndash; Marsar &ndash; Sonamasti Valley.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Trek to Marsar Lake (Trek: 8 kms). Enjoy the beautification of Marsar lake and move further to Sonamasti. The Sonamasti valley is a breathtaking piece of nature&rsquo;s art with small streams, brooks and green pastures. O/n Sonamasti Valley.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 8 Sonamasti &ndash; Sumbal &ndash; Srinagar City.</h4>\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Today start for trek to Sumbal (Trek: 11 Kms/ By road: 2 hrs). Reach sumbal and proceed for Srinagar by vehicle. Check into the hotel. O/n Srinagar City.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Day : 9 Drop at Srinagar Airport.</h4>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n<div id=\"printContent\" class=\"tour_head1 l-info-pack-days days\">\r\n<p class=\"wow fadeInUp animated\">Today drop at Srinagar airport drop for your final departure. The trek ends here with sweet memories of&nbsp;<strong>Joy Tour and Travels.</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '9', '8', 'Day : 1 Srinagar ‚Äì Pahalgam Valley.,Day : 2 Pahalgam ‚Äì Aru Valley.,Day : 3 Aru ‚Äì Lidderwat Valley.,Day : 4 Lidderwat ‚Äì Shekwas Valley.,Day : 5 Shekhwas ‚Äì Tarsar Lake.,Day : 6 Tarsar ‚Äì Sundersar Lake.,Day : 7 Sundersar ‚Äì Marsar ‚Äì Sonamasti Valley.,Day : 8 Sonamasti ‚Äì Sumbal ‚Äì Srinagar City.,Day : 9 Drop at Srinagar Airport.', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Srinagar International Airport', '65000', NULL, '\"Find Your Peace Amidst the Himalayas\".', '52000', '9906786356', '2025-05-07 07:40:41', '2025-05-07 07:40:41', '1N Pahalgam 1N Aru 1N Lidderwat', '1N Shekwas 1N Tarsar', '1N Sundersar 1N Marsar Lake 1N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(125, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Incredible Leh & Ladakh | Journey to the Land of Lamas', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746609803.jpg', '<p>Ladakh is&nbsp;<strong>one of the highest regions of the world</strong>. Its natural features consist mainly of high plains, deep valleys, rivers, lakes, and a series of mountain passes such as Umling La, through which runs the world\'s highest drivable road. The high plain predominates in the east, diminishing gradually toward the west.</p>\r\n<h1 class=\"ProductInfo_header__6VcVQ\">&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<div class=\"ProductInfo_infoDurationWrapper__p9Zap\">&nbsp;</div>', '05', '04', 'Arrival Leh,assist and transfer you to Hotel in Leh. Rest of the day free to acclimatize to the high altitude of Ladakh. In the evening take a walk to the local bazaar in Leh. Overnight at Hotel in Leh.,Morning after breakfast visit Hall of Fame,Spituk Monastery and Kali Mata Temple,Magnetic Hill,Gurudwara Patthar Sahib and Confluence of Zanskar - Indus rivers. Return to Leh for lunch (on own). In the evening visit Leh Palace,Donkey Sanctuary and Shanti Stupa for beautiful sunset view. Dinner and overnight stay at the hotel in Leh.     LADAKH HALL OF FAME : The Hall of Fame is a glorious museum constructed by the Indian Army. It is worth a visit for every citizen. You can see the memorabilia,eminent defense personalities with biographies,images and  weapons used during the Kargil and other key strategic battles fought in Ladakh.  And belongings of the enemy soldiers found at war site. All the martyr and the gallantry awards‚Ä¶     SPITUK GOMPA: 8 Kms from Leh,it stands prominently on the top of hillock commanding a panoramic view of the Indus Valley for miles. Many icons of Buddha and fine Thankas are to be found in this 15th century Gompa. The Gompa also houses a collection of ancient masks,antique arms,and an awe-inspiring image of Mahakaal. The face of the Kali image is kept covered and is revealed only at the annual function at January every year.     MAGNETIC HILL : Defying the Law of gravity. This place is close to the Gurdwara Shri Patthar Sahib. It has been noticed that when a vehicle is parked on neutral gear on this metallic road the vehicle slides up-hill that‚Äôs the Believe it or not of Ladakh!     GURDWARA SHRI PATTHAR SAHIB: The Shrine known as Gurdwara Patthar sahib is situated about 25 kms. Short of Leh town on the Leh-Srinagar road. Built in the everlasting memory of Shri Guru Nanak Deve Ji the great prophet who sanctified the place by his sacred visit during the year 1517 while on his second missionary tour (2nd Udassi 1515-1518). The Guru reached here via Nepal,Sikkim,Tibet Yarkand and Leh after having spiritual discourses with the sidhas at Mount Sumer (Central Himalayas).     CONFLENCE OF THE ZANSKAR & INDUS: On way to Sham Valley before Nimu village one can have this magnificent view of two rivers in wed-lock! In seasons they have different colors and flow and wildness.     DONKEY SANCTUARY: The sanctuary is situated just off the road leading to Khardungla Pass. The public is encouraged to visit the sanctuary and friendly signs will direct you to the sanctuary from the center of Leh. Once at the sanctuary,the artistic surprise awaiting you is well worth the effort.     LEH PALACE : The Palace overlooks Leh town and is modeled on the Potala Palace in Lhasa,Tibet. The palace was built by King Sengge Namgyal in the 17th century,but was later abandoned when Dogra forces took control of Ladakh in the mid-19th century. The royal family moved to Stok Palace. Leh Palace is nine storeys high;The palace,a ruin,is currently being restored by the Archaeological Survey of India. The palace is open to the public and the roof provides panoramic views of Leh and the surrounding areas. The richest collection of jewellery,ornaments,Thangkas,ceremonial dresses,crowns,and centuries-old pieces of jewellery are kept here for public display.     SHANTI STUPA (Japanese Peace Pagoda) : Shanti Stupa/Japanese peace pagoda is build by a Japanese religious organization headed by Head monk Nakamura with the help from the organization and local people. It is situated at a hill top in Cahngspa village providing a bird eye view of the Leh town and the surrounding mountain peaks. Architecturally it has the Japanese touch with small clean rooms on the side for meditators and the main Japanese shrine at the entrance.,After breakfast drive to Nubra en routeKhardungla is the World\'s highest motor able road at 18832 feet above sea level. At Khardungla pass the snowcapped peaks and the mountain views are amazing. The road then passes through a bridge laid on Glacier which finds its way in Guinness Book of world records,Drive through the Valley which is extremely beautiful for photography. Nubra Valley is the Oasis of Ladakh as you see some colourful trees in this region. Later reach your camp visit the Sand Dunes if lucky you will get the sight of the Two Hump Bactrian camels,enjoy time at the Sand Dunes of Nubra valley spread across Hundar Village. Dinner and Overnight stay at the camp.,After Breakfast proceed to Diskit monastery which is 515 years old situated on a hill top giving panoramic view of the valley later walk around the town of Diskit which has a small village market. Giant Buddha Statue. Proceed back to Leh via same route. Dinner & Overnight stay at the hotel.,Leave on time for Leh airport to board your flight to Delhi', 'Leh Airport', 'Leh Airport', '56000', NULL, 'Beautiful Leh with Nubra', '45000', '9906786356', '2025-05-07 09:23:23', '2025-05-07 09:23:23', 'Leh/Nubra Valley', 'Khardung-La Pass', 'Pangong Lake', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel 