(163, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Joy Journey to the Heart of Himalayas', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746685021.jpg', '<p><strong>Experience the mesmerizing beauty of Kashmir with this 5 Nights / 6 Days package covering the serene valleys of Pahalgam, the snow-covered slopes of Gulmarg, and the Mughal charm of Srinagar. From tranquil boat rides on Dal Lake to thrilling gondola rides in Gulmarg and riverside walks in Pahalgam, this journey promises a perfect blend of relaxation, romance, and adventure.</strong></p>', '6', '5', 'Day: 01 Srinagar ‚Äì Gulmarg Valley.,Meet and greet on arrival at Srinagar airport and proceed for Gulmarg (2-3 hrs drive). Check into the hotel. O/n Gulmarg.  Gulmarg has one of the best Ski slopes in the world and highest golf course with 18 holes. One can also have the view of Nanga Parbhat if weather permits. The view en route from Tangmarg to Gulmarg is fascinating.,Day: 02 Gulmarg Valley ‚Äì Pahalgam Valley.,After breakfast proceed for Pahalgam (5-6 hrs drive). Reach Pahalgam and check into the hotel. Pahalgam is also known as ‚ÄòValley of Shepherds‚Äô. Post lunch you can visit Baisaran valley by walk or on pony at extra cost. Baisaran is a vast meadow situated on top of the mountain range overlooking the Lidder River. It has been christened as the Mini-Switzerland of India.O/n Pahalgam.,Day: 03 Pahalgam Valley Local Sightseeing.,After breakfast visit Chandanwadi - Snow point and mainly known as the starting point of sacred Amarnath yatra,Betaab valley and Aru valley by local union vehicle. Evening free for shopping and exploring local bazaar. O/n Pahalgam.,Day: 04 Pahalgam Valley ‚Äì Srinagar City.,After breakfast proceed for Srinagar (4-5 hrs drive). En route Awantipuram ‚Äì Ancient Ruins,Cricket Bat factory and witness Saffron farms on both sides of the road. Reach Srinagar and check into the hotel. Day free for shopping and personal activities. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 05 Srinagar Local Sightseeing.,After breakfast visit famous Mughal gardens like Pari Mahal Shalimar bagh Nishat bagh Chashmeshahi bagh Also visit Shankaracharya temple - Abode of Lord Shiva from where you can have bird\'s eye view of Srinagar. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 06 Final Departure.,Today drop at Srinagar airport for your onward journey. The tour ends here with the sweet memories of Joy Tour and Travels.', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Srinagar International Airport', '39999', NULL, 'Honeymoon Features Complementary.', '33999', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 06:17:01', '2025-05-08 06:17:01', '1N Gulmarg', '2N Pahalgam', '2N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(169, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Joy Splendid Kashmir Tour', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746686050.jpg', '<p>Escape to the serene beauty of Kashmir with our specially curated 6-day tour package. Witness snow-capped mountains, shimmering lakes, colorful gardens, and experience the warm hospitality of the Kashmiri people. Ideal for couples, families, and nature lovers</p>', '06', '05', 'Day 1: Arrival and Srinagar Local Sightseeing Welcome to the Srinagar the Lake City. On arrival at Srinagar Airport being your tour of Royal Kashmir Tour. You will be transferred to Hotel . Proceed on a city tour visiting the Shankracharya temple situated on the highest hill of Srinagar the famous Mughal Gardens-Chashmashahi Nishat & Shalimar. These gardens were Mughal Emperors concept of Paradise and today these are popular picnic spots. Also visit a handicraft shop where you can purchase local Hand Crafted items-Shawls Jackets  Bed Covers Paper Mache Carpets & much more! In the evening leisurely stroll alongside the Dal Lake exploring the local markets . Overnight stay at the Hotel.,Day 2: Excursion to Sonamarg Today you embark on a full day excursion to the picturesque meadow of gold Sonamarg. Sonamarg is last stop of Kashmir district. From here starts the territory of ladhakh. Situated at an altitude of 2743 mt above sea level. The fast flowing Sindh River makes it popular for trout and masher fishing in summer. You can opt for a pony ride to one of the glaciers for some fun in snow and ice (by your own payment).Return to the Hotel in Srinagar in the evening and enjoy comfortable overnight stay.,Day 3: Transfer to Pahalgam Early in the morning leave for Pahalgam the valley of shepherds which is situated at the confluence of the streams flowing from river Lidder and Sheeshnag Lake. En route visit the Awantipura ruins an 1100 year old temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu and built by King Awantivarman. On arrival into Pahalgam enjoy the surrounding beauty or walk to Baisaren which is about 2 km from Pahalgam. A small village set in pine and fir forest is pleasing and offers good view. Night halt at Hotel in Pahalgam.,Day 4: Pahalgam to Gulmarg In morning having Breakfast drive to Gulmarg the meadow of flowers. The route from Srinagar to Gulmarg is fascinating. You will be mesmerized by its beauty. Gulmarg is famous all over the world for Skiing and Snowboarding. During the British Raj.  Gulmarg hosted the Britishers and Europeans and as such they created a European hill resort and named it Gulmarg. In Gulmarg you would be able to find European surroundings and 18-hole Golf Course. Night halt at Hotel in Gulmarg.,Day 5: Gulmarg to Srinagar  After having breakfast enjoy Gondola Cable Car Ride worlds highest and the Asias longest cable car (at your own cost).Enjoy photography horse riding and shopping at this beautiful snow point. In the Afternoon return to Srinagar and do local sight seen of remaining Srinagar.Houseboat in Srinagar in the evening and enjoy comfortable overnight stay.,Day 6: Departure  After breakfast transfer to Srinagar Airport to board your flight with Everlasting Memories of Joy Tour and Travels', 'Srinagar Airport', 'Srinagar Airport', '20000', NULL, 'With shikara ride Free', '18000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 06:34:10', '2025-05-08 06:34:10', '3N Srinagar', '1N Gulmarg', '1N Pahalgam', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\