(170, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Explore Ladakh - The Land of High Passes', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746686281.jpg', '<p>Constructed during the 17th century by the royal Namgyal family, Leh Palace, located in Leh city, is a fine example of medieval Tibetan architecture. While it earlier served as the residence to the Namgyal dynasty, today the palace is the administrative office of the Archaeological Conservation Organization which is owned by the Indian Government. A Victory Tower, built in the memory of Ladakhi soldiers is a famous landmark here. From the palace, one could see spectacular views, making it popular amongst photographers. Comfortable shoes are advised as a fair amount of walking is involved</p>', '07', '06', 'Arrival in Leh,Leh local sightseeing,Leh to Nubra Valley,Nubra Valley to Pangong,Pangong to Leh,Thiksey Monastery Around 19 kilometers from Leh,Thiksey Monastery (also known as Mini Patola) is a beautiful red,ochre and white colored establishment on the top of a hill. Located at an altitude of 11,840 feet and counted amongst the largest monasteries in Ladakh,the 12 storied building houses Buddhist art such as paintings,swords,thangkas,statues,etc. The monastery features a huge pillar engraved with the Buddha\'s teachings and a 15 meter high Buddha statue at the main prayer hall. The monastery is known for its temples,mainly the Maitrayee Buddha and Lamokhang Temple. The iconic 49 feet tall statue of Maitreya Buddha is the star highlight of the monastery. It is advised to dress conservatively while visiting the monastery.,Departure from Leh', 'Leh Airport', 'Leh Airport', '52800', NULL, 'Free Camel Safari Ride', '45000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 06:38:01', '2025-05-08 06:38:01', 'leh', 'shanti stupa', 'Nubra/Pangong', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(171, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Kashmir Fly Away Package', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746687571.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span data-huuid=\"3100260315214693321\"><mark class=\"QVRyCf\">Is it typically includes visits to Pahalgam, Gulmarg, and Sonmarg, offering diverse experiences from serene valleys to thrilling adventure</mark>.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"3100260315214694362\">Pahalgam, known as the \"Valley of Shepherds,\" boasts lush landscapes, while Gulmarg features skiing and cable car rides.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"3100260315214695403\">Sonmarg, meaning \"Meadow of Gold,\" is home to glaciers and alpine meadows.<span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"2fc18ae2-5558-468e-9924-9af59189d6b9\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong></span></p>', '9', '8', 'Day 01: Arrival at Srinagar Airport and Transfer to Srinagar Hotel.,Meet and greet on arrival at Srinagar airport and proceed to the hotel near Dal Lake. Check into the hotel. Evening enjoy near beautiful World famous Dal Lake. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 02 Srinagar ‚Äì Sonmarg Valley ‚Äì Srinagar City.,Today after early breakfast proceed for Sonmarg (3 hrs drive). Sonmarg is also known as Meadows of Gold. You can take a walk/ Pony ride at extra cost up to Thajwasa Glacier. Enjoy snow activities at own expenses. Back to Srinagar by evening. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 03 Srinagar City ‚Äì Gulmarg Valley.,After breakfast proceed for Gulmarg (2-3 hrs drive). Gulmarg has one of the best Ski slopes in the world and highest golf course with 18 holes. One can also have the view of Nanga Parbhat if weather permits. The view en route from Tangmarg to Gulmarg is fascinating.  Reach Gulmarg and check into the hotel. Enjoy local surroundings by walk or on pony at extra cost. O/n Gulmarg.,Day: 04 Gulmarg Valley Local Sightseeing.,After breakfast walk towards Gondola rope way - Highest and longest cable car ride in India with 2 phases. Enjoy snow activities like Snow scooters sledging Skiing etc. at extra cost. Back to hotel for lunch. Evening free at leisure. O/n Gulmarg,Day: 05 Gulmarg Valley ‚Äì Pahalgam Valley.,After breakfast proceed for Pahalgam (5-6 hrs drive). Reach Pahalgam and check into the hotel. Pahalgam is also known as ‚ÄòValley of Shepherds‚Äô. Post lunch you can visit Baisaran valley by walk or on pony at extra cost. Baisaran is a vast meadow situated on top of the mountain range overlooking the Lidder River. It has been christened as the Mini-Switzerland of India. O/n Pahalgam.,Day: 06 Pahalgam Valley Local Sightseeing.,After breakfast visit Chandanwadi - Snow point and mainly known as the starting point of sacred Amarnath yatra Betaab valley and Aru valley by local union vehicle. Evening free for shopping and exploring local bazaar. O/n Pahalgam.,Day: 07 Pahalgam Valley ‚Äì Srinagar City.,After breakfast proceed for Srinagar (4-5 hrs drive). En route Awantipuram ‚Äì Ancient Ruins Cricket Bat factory and witness Saffron farms on both sides of the road. Reach Srinagar and check into the hotel. Day free for shopping and personal activities. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 08 Srinagar Local Sightseeing.,After breakfast visit famous Mughal gardens like Pari Mahal Shalimar bagh Nishat bagh Chashmeshahi bagh. Also visit Shankaracharya temple - Abode of Lord Shiva from where you can have bird\'s eye view of Srinagar. O/n Srinagar.,Day: 09 Final Departure.,Today drop at Srinagar airport to catch flight for Mumbai. The tour ends here with the sweet memories of Joy Tour and Travels.', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Srinagar International Airport', '65000', NULL, 'Shikara Ride in Dal Lake and Gondola Ride in Gulmarg', '50000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 06:59:31', '2025-05-08 06:59:31', '2N Srinagar', '2N Gulmarg 2N Pahalgam', '2N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and 