(172, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', '\"Joy Journey Through High-Altitude Wonders\"', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746687966.jpg', '<p><span data-huuid=\"5604438771530097435\">Ladakh, often called \"Little Tibet\" or the \"Land of High Passes,\" is&nbsp;<mark class=\"QVRyCf\">a high-altitude, mountainous region in Northern India, known for its remote beauty, Buddhist culture, and unique lunar-like landscape</mark>.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"5604438771530098884\">It\'s characterized by towering mountain ranges, river valleys, and high plateaus, and the region is deeply influenced by Tibetan culture and Buddhism.<span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"1f01feed-0c1a-43eb-a139-e94b7df4b582\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>', '10', '9', 'Day : 1 Srinagar,Meet and greet on arrival at Srinagar airport by our representative and proceed to the hotel near World famous Dal Lake. Check into the hotel. Enjoy near blissful Dal Lake. Overnight stay at Srinagar.,Day : 2 Srinagar ‚Äì Kargil,Early morning after breakfast leave for Kargil (9-10 hrs drive). En route Zojila Pass Drass Village (2nd Coldest Inhabited place in the World) Kargil war famous peaks and Kargil war Memorial. Reach Kargil by evening. Check into the hotel. Overnight stay in Kargil.,Day : 3 Kargil ‚Äì Leh,After breakfast leave for Leh (9-10 hrs drive) enroute Mulbek (1st Century Giant Living Buddha Sculpture on Rock Mountain) later visit Lamayuru Monastery & enjoy magnificent view of Moonland - An undulating series of mountains that resemble the surface of the moon. Magnetic Hill Confluence of Indus and Zanskar rivers and Patharsaheb Gurudwara. Reach Leh and check into the hotel. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 4 Leh City Sightseeing,After breakfast proceed for Leh city sightseeing which includes Hemis Monastery Oldest and richest monastery of Ladakh Thiksey Monastery Historic Buddhist monastery on a Hill Shey palace Sindhu Ghat Rancho School subject to permission Hall of fame museum Indian army operated memorial & museum Shanti stupa Domed Buddhist temple on a hill and Leh Palace Centuries old mountain top palace. Evening explore Leh market. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 5 Leh ‚Äì Nubra Valley,After early breakfast leave for Nubra valley (5-6 hrs drive) via Khardungla pass @ 18380 ft (Worlds highest motorable road). Reach Nubra valley by afternoon. Nubra Valley offers tremendous scenery on a grand scale with green oasis villages surrounded by thrillingly stark scree slopes and harsh arid mountains. You can enjoy Two hump camel safari on the Worlds highest coldest desert at own expenses. Overnight Nubra Valley.,Day : 6 Nubra Valley ‚Äì Leh,After breakfast proceed for Leh by same route via Diskit  Future Buddha statue & Khardungla pass. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 7 Leh ‚Äì Pangong Lake Leh (8-9 hrs drive both ways),After early breakfast leave for Pangong Lake through Changla pass (17350 ft- worlds third highest motorable road). Pangong Lake is at an altitude of 14500 ft and is Worlds highest and longest salt water lake. Enjoy changing colours of the Blue brackish Lake. Back to leh by evening. Overnight stay at  Leh.,Day : 8 Leh Tsomoriri Lake (Breakfast & Dinner),After breakfast proceed for Tsomoriri Lake (7 8 hrs drive). Check into the tents. Tsomoriri Lake (4522 M) is a sweet water lake and a sanctuary for several Himalayan birds and animals apart from being one of the most treasured high altitude lakes in India.Overnight stay at Tsomoriri Lake.,Day : 9 Tsomoriri Lake ‚Äì Leh (Breakfast & Dinner),After early breakfast proceed for Leh (7-8 hrs). Check into the hotel. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 10 Final Departure,After Breakfast Proceed for Leh airport to catch flight for your onward journey. The tour ends here with the sweet memories of Joy Tour and Travels!!!!!.', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Kushok Bakula Rimpochee Airport', '65000', NULL, 'Tso Moriri Exploration', '55000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 07:06:06', '2025-05-08 07:11:55', '1N Srinagar, 1N Kargil, 4N Leh', '5N Leh, 1N Nubra Valley,', '1N Tsomoriri Lake', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(173, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Feel the Essence of Buddhism in Ladakh', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746688089.jpg', '<p>Pangong Lake is a stunning high-altitude lake located in the Himalayas, primarily in India and partially in China. It is renowned for its mesmerizing blue waters that change color throughout the day, surrounded by majestic mountains. The lake is approximately 134 kilometers long and is situated at an elevation of about 4,350 meters (14,270 feet). It is a popular destination for tourists seeking breathtaking views, photography opportunities, and a serene environment. Visitors can enjoy activities such as boating and camping along the shores of the lake, making it a must-visit spot in the region.</p>', '08', '07', 'Arrive by flight at Leh. Welcome to Leh! Few places in India are at once so traveler-friendly and yet so enchanting and hassle-free as mountain-framed Leh. Dotted with stupas and crumbling mudbrick houses,the Old Town is dominated by a dagger of steep rocky ridge topped by an imposing Tibetan-style palace and fort. A private car will pick you up from Leh Airport and transfer you to the hotel. Check-in at the hotel on arrival. [NOTE: Standard check-in time is 12:00 pm] The entire day is at your leisure. Relax and acclimatize to the high altitude of Leh. Dinner & overnight stay will be at the hotel in Leh.,After breakfast head out for local sightseeing. Visit Leh Palace built in the 17th century and the roof top of the palace provides spectacular views of the mountain of Stok Kangri and the Ladakh mountain range. Visit Shey Palace & Monastery built in 1665 by the King of Ladakh (Deldon Namgyal) as his summer retreat house. Afterwards visit Thiksey Monastery,one of the finest examples of Ladakhi architecture. This Monastery is located on the top of the hill in solitude which lies at a distance of 20 kilometers away from Leh. It is very famous for its similarity with the Potala Palace of Lhasa. Reach back at the hotel by evening. Dinner & overnight stay will be at the hotel in Leh.,After breakfast,head out for full day sightseeing tour; visit Hall of fame (a famed museum constructed by the Indian Army); Gurudwara Pathar Sahib (a beautiful Sikh Temple built in 1517 to commemorate the visit to the Ladakh region of Guru Nanak Dev,the founder Guru of the Sikh faith),Magnetic hill & Alchi Monastery (the artistic and spiritual details of both Buddhism and the Hindu kings of that time in Kashmir are reflected in the wall paintings in the monastery complex. The complex also has huge statues of the Buddha and lavish wood carvings and artwork ‚Äî almost baroque in style). On the way also visit Sangam (the confluence of Zanskar & Indus rivers),a very picturesque site. Reach back Leh by evening and visit Shanti Stupa a Buddhist white-domed stupa on a hilltop in Chanspa. It was built in 1991 by Japanese Buddhist Bhikshu,Gyomyo Nakamura and part of the Peace Pagoda mission. Dinner & overnight stay will be at the hotel in Leh.  Read less,drive from Leh to Nubra Valley via Khardung-La Pass (18380ft) ‚Äì one of the world\'s highest motorable roads. The valley is located around 159 km from Leh. The route will be Leh ‚Äì Phyang ‚Äì Khardung La ‚Äì Khalsar ‚Äì Diskit ‚Äì Nubra Valley. This valley is a virgin destination for people who seek peace and interaction with the tribal community of Ladakh. The Sasser Pass and the famous Karakoram Pass of the Silk Route fame lie to the northwest of the valley and connect Nubra with Xinjiang (China). You will also see the goats that give you the famous Pashmina shawls. Check-in at the hotel on arrival. Dinner & overnight stay will be at the hotel in Nubra Valley.  Read less More about Nubra Va,head out for Nubra Valley sightseeing tour. Visit Diskit Monastery,the largest and the oldest surviving monastery in Nubra Valley. The prime attraction of the Diskit monastery is 100 feet high Maitreya Buddha statue,which was inaugurated by the holy Dalai Lama. Afterwards visit Hunder Sand dunes. Try a ride over the rare Bactrian Camel (double-humped camel),which should not be missed. Later visit Panamic Hot Springs where you can take a bath. It is considered good for the skin to take a bath in the hot sulfur spring. Reach back at the hotel by the evening. Dinner & overnight stay will be at the hotel in Nubra Valley.,After breakfast drive from Nubra Valley to Pangong Lake. This endorheic Himalayan Lake lies at a height of about 4,350 m (14,270 ft). It is 134 km (83 mi) long and extends from India to China. Check-in to the camps which offer unparallel views of the surrounding mountain ranges and a wonderful view of Pangong Lake. Its water is salty,crystal clear,and has a lovely shade of blue. It looks its best when the sun is shining bright. The evening is at your leisure. You can also indulge in a Yak Safari. Dinner & night stay is at the camps near Pangong Lake.  Read less,drive from Pangong Lake to Leh. On the way visit Hemis Monastery,Hemis Monastery,revered as the largest monastic institution in Ladakh. It is the wealthiest Buddhist monastery in India and is famous for its rich collection of ancient remnants like the statue of Buddha made of copper,and stupas made of gold and silver. The monastery also has sacred Thangkas,murals,and various artifacts. Reach Leh in the evening and check-in at the hotel. The evening is at your leisure. Dinner & Overnight stay will be at the hotel in Leh.,After early breakfast check-out from the hotel. The private car will drop you at Leh airport for your return flight. To all the good things comes an end. Leave with wonderful memories of this amazing trip to Leh-Ladakh,worth remembering for a lifetime.', 'Leh Airport', 'Leh Airport', '79000', NULL, 'wonders of ladakh', '65000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 07:08:09', '2025-05-08 07:08:09', 'leh/sham valley', 'nubra', 'Pangong', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r