(176, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Joy Majestic Gurez Valley Package', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746689898.jpg', '<p><strong><span data-huuid=\"2654443447262809053\">Gurez Valley and Tulail Valley, located in the northern part of Kashmir, are known for their stunning natural beauty and remote location, making them ideal for nature lovers and those seeking tranquility.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"2654443447262809738\">Gurez Valley, about 123 km from Srinagar, is characterized by snow-capped mountains, the Kishanganga River, and the presence of the Dard people, who speak the Shina language.&nbsp;</span></strong><span data-huuid=\"2654443447262806327\"><strong>Tulail Valley, within the Gurez region, is a smaller, less-explored valley known for its alpine landscape, lush meadows, and pristine surroundings.</strong><span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"3e7223c8-70b9-4649-9602-04337f9c966b\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>', '6', '5', 'DAY 01: Arrival at Srinagar Airport and Srinagar Local sightseeing.,Arrival at Srinagar Airport and Srinagar Local sightseeing visit famous Mughal gardens like Pari Mahal Shalimar bagh Nishat bagh Chashmeshahi bagh. Also visit Shankaracharya temple - Abode of Lord Shiva from where you can have bird\'s eye view of Srinagar. O/n Srinagar.,DAY 02: Srinagar City to Gurez Valley (123 km 6 to 7 hours of drive).,Begin your day of majestic Gurez valley package with breakfast and get ready for the drive towards Gurez valley. Gurez valley is located in the Himalayas and you reach there through road from Bandipora via Razdan Top. The drive is nothing less than a spectacular experience and you will notice the beauty of nature at its best. Visit Razdon top located at an altitude of 11672 feet. It is famous for its medicinal plant. Razdan Pass is an adrenaline-pumping road in India. From Razdan top you can view the snow-capped Harmukh Peak which is the highest mountain peak of Kashmir. On reaching Gurez check in to your hotel for an overnight stay.,DAY 03: Gurez Local Sightseeing.,Start your day with morning breakfast and prepare yourself for local sightseeing of Gurez. You will be visiting a local town known as Dawar. It is famous as an archaeological site. Here you will get to see beautiful log wood houses. The local people of Dawar town are called Dards. They are very friendly you can talk to them and explore more about their local lives. Later you visit the pyramid-shaped Habba Khatoon peak. The beautiful mountain peak is an important part of Kashmir‚Äôs history. It is named after famous Kashmiri poetess Habba Khatoon. Another attraction of this place is Habba Khatoon spring. Lucid water gushing out of the mountain range is crystal clear and has medicinal properties. After a fun filled day head back to your hotel. Take the dinner and prepare for an overnight stay.,DAY 04: Gurez Valley ‚Äì Tulail Valley ‚Äì Gurez Valley (40 km 2 hours).,After having your breakfast you will drive towards Tulail valley via Dawar. This valley is one of the remotest valleys of the region. On reaching the valley take a foot walk around the place. Explore the beautiful natural beauty of the region. This place is nothing less than a dreamland. Just sit and relax around lush green meadows and enjoy the beauty of Mother Nature. On your way back you will also visit the majestic Sheikhpura and Chakwali villages. Chakwali village is the last Indian village on the line of control. Later in the evening drive back to Gurez valley for an overnight stay.,DAY 05: Gurez Valley to Srinagar City (123 km 6 to 7 hours of drive).,Begin this day of your majestic Gurez valley package with breakfast and get ready for a drive towards Srinagar. On your way visit the Izamrg village and capture the splendid green meadows on your camera. You can also choose to take a walk around the village to explore its charm. On arrival in Srinagar check into the hotel take your dinner and head for an overnight stay.,DAY 06: Srinagar Airport Departure.,After having your breakfast head towards Srinagar airport to board your flight for the onward journey.', 'Srinagar International Airport.', 'Srinagar International Airport', '70000', NULL, 'Kashmir‚Äôs Untouched Beauty You Need to Experience.', '55000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 07:38:18', '2025-05-08 07:38:18', '1N Srinagar', '3N Gurez Valley', '1N Srinagar', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(177, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Leh Ladakh - Best of Tibet Experience', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746690031.jpg', '<p><span data-huuid=\"16467084002613754249\">Pangong Tso and Tso Moriri are both beautiful high-altitude lakes in Ladakh, but they offer different experiences.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"16467084002613751956\"><mark class=\"QVRyCf\">Pangong Tso is more popular and easily accessible, making it a popular day trip, while Tso Moriri is less crowded and requires a more adventurous trip with an overnight stay</mark>.<span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"38e540af-34a2-4443-81a9-f2ec18ca77a4\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>', '09', '08', 'On the day of arrival at Leh airport,our Holidays At representative will assist you for transfer to your hotel. During the day,acclimate yourself with the weather and high pressure of Ladakh. Overnight at Hotel.,proceed for day excursion tour to Alchi,visit the 1000 year old paintings of Alchi Monastery 68 Kms from Leh,via en-route visit the great statue of Maitreya Buddha at Likir monastery,Sangam of Indus & Zanskar rivers which are the two major rivers in Ladakh,Magnetic Hill and military Hall of Fame. Overnight at Hotel.  Read more,Upon arrival at Nubra valley check-in to your camp for night stay. Later explore Hunder & Diskit Monastery and white sand dunes via camel safari. The safari tour is done with double humped camels that are found only in Nubra Valley. Overnight at Camp.,Upon arrival at Leh check-in to your hotel for night stay. Evening free in Leh bazaars for last minute shooping,in Leh items like pure Pashmina shawls,good pearls,Chinese cutleries and beautiful Ladakhi wooden handicrafts can be purchased. Overnight at Hotel.,Today early morning after breakfast at hotel,later check out and proceed for Pangong Lake.,Today morning after breakfast at camp,later check out and drive to Tso Moriri Lake,Today morning after breakfast at hotel,later check out from hotel and drive to Leh,later proceed for full day guided tour to Leh,visit to Thiksey Gompa - is a gompa affiliated with the Gelug sect of Tibetan Buddhism. It is located on top of a hill in Thiksey approximately 19 Kms east of Leh in Ladakh. Also visit Shey Palace in the vicinity. After that proceed for Hemis which hosts one of the most well known festivals in Ladakh. After visiting the monasteries we will drive to Stok Palace Museum which showcases royal artefacts and paraphernalia. Overnight at Hotel.,later check out and transfer to Leh airport to board the flight for your home', 'Leh Airport', 'Leh Airport', '99900', NULL, 'Best of Ladakh', '85000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 07:40:31', '2025-05-08 07:40:31', 'Leh/Alchi', 'Nubra/Pangong', 'Tsomoriri', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(178, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Joy Kashmir special With Pahalgam Stay', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746690903.jpg', '<p>Escape to the serene beauty of Kashmir with our specially curated 6-day tour package. Witness snow-capped mountains, shimmering lakes, colorful gardens, and experience the warm hospitality of the Kashmiri people. Ideal for couples, families, and nature lovers!</p>', '06', '05', 'Day 1: Arrival and Srinagar Local Sightseeing Welcome to the Srinagar the Lake City. On arrival at Srinagar Airport being your tour of Royal Kashmir Tour. You will be transferred to Hotel . Proceed on a city tour visiting the Shankracharya temple situated on the highest hill of Srinagar the famous Mughal Gardens-Chashmashahi Nishat & Shalimar. These gardens were Mughal Emperors concept of Paradise and today these are popular picnic spots. Also visit a handicraft shop where you can purchase local Hand Crafted items-Shawls Jackets  Bed Covers Paper Mache Carpets & much more! In the evening leisurely stroll alongside the Dal Lake exploring the local markets . Overnight stay at the Ho,Day 2: Excursion to Sonamarg Today you embark on a full day excursion to the picturesque meadow of gold Sonamarg. Sonamarg is last stop of Kashmir district. From here starts the territory of ladhakh. Situated at an altitude of 2743 mt above sea level. The fast flowing Sindh River makes it popular for trout and masher fishing in summer. You can opt for a pony ride to one of the glaciers for some fun in snow and ice (by your own payment).Return to the Hotel in Srinagar in the evening and enjoy comfortable overnight stay.,Day 03: Day Trip To Gulmarg Today After Breakfast you will directly proceed towards Gulmarg Valley Known as Meadow of Flowers. Enjoy Gondola Cable Ride. highest and the Asias longest cable car (at your own cost). Later return back to Srinagar for dinner and overnight stay at Srinagar Hotel.,Day 4: Srinagar to Pahalgam Early in the morning leave for Pahalgam the valley of shepherds which is situated at the confluence of the streams flowing from river Lidder and Sheeshnag Lake. En route visit the Awantipura ruins an 1100 year old temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu and built by King Awantivarman. On arrival into Pahalgam enjoy the surrounding beauty or walk to Baisaren which is about 2 km from Pahalgam. You can explore Aru Valley Betaab Valley and Chandanwari on your own cost. A small village set in pine and fir forest is pleasing and offers good view. Night halt at Hotel in Pahalgam.,Day 5: Pahalgam to Srinagar Today checkout from pahalgam hotel later drive towards Srinagar. After reaching Srinagar complete all checkin formalities at Houseboat. At evening do Shikara ride 1 hour free. Enjoy dinner and over night stay at Houseboat in Dal Lake.,Day 6: Departure  After breakfast transfer to Srinagar Airport to board your flight with Everlasting Memories of Joy Tour and Travels', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Srinagar International Airport', '40000', NULL, 'with shikara ride Free', '36000', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 07:55:03', '2025-05-08 07:55:03', '3N Srinagar', '1N Dal Lake', '1N Pahalgam', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe date is valid for travel till Tuesday, 30 September 2025.\r\n\r\nEasy Cancellation Policy\r\nIn case of more than 30 days prior to departure date, initial booking amount and any additional amount of air fare will be charged as penalty. *Less than 30 days: 50% of total tour cost will be charged as penalty.\r\n\r\nGuaranteed Dates\r\nYour selected travel dates are guaranteed in the unlikely event of a death and not due guarantee * - 12 days from your preferred dates.', NULL),
(179, 'Kashmir Tour Packages', 'Misty Srinagar With Free Photoshoot', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746691959.jpg', '<p><span data-huuid=\"596468480744428201\"><mark class=\"QVRyCf\">Srinagar offers a visually stunning backdrop for a free photoshoot, particularly with its iconic Dal Lake, Mughal gardens, and scenic landscapes</mark>, all of which are perfect for capturing memories.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"596468480744428300\">You can explore the vibrant colors and tranquil atmosphere of the lake while taking photos of the houseboats and Shikaras,&nbsp;<a class=\"uVhVib\" href=\"https://travelmykashmir.com/srinagar-photo-and-video-services/\">according to Travel my kashmir</a>.&nbsp;</span><span data-huuid=\"596468480744428399\">Additionally, the city\'s Mughal gardens, like Nishat Garden and Shalimar Garden, provide beautiful settings for capturing the rich history and beauty of the region.<span class=\"pjBG2e\" data-cid=\"f70d1f4d-0940-40c4-926c-b1e0e750c2aa\"><span class=\"UV3uM\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>', '3', '2', 'Day 1: Arrival at Srinagar International Airport and Proceed for Srinagar City Local Sightseeing. Overnight stay in Hotel at Srinagar City.,Day 2: Proceed for Dal Lake. Check Inn at the Houseboat and enjoy 1 Hr Shikara ride and free Photoshoot at Dal Lake. Overnight stay in Houseboat at Dal Lake.,Day 3: Departure to Srinagar International Airport with sweet memories of Joy Tour and Travels', 'Srinagar International Airport', 'Srinagar International Airport', '9999', NULL, 'Fabulous Srinagar', '7999', '9906786356', '2025-05-08 08:12:39', '2025-05-08 08:12:39', '1N Srinagar', '1N Dal Lake', '-', 'Accommodation at hotel\r\nWelcome drink on arrival\r\nDaily breakfast and dinner\r\nNon A/C Vehicle for sightseeing\r\nAirport/Train Station Transfer\r\nAll applicable taxes', '5 % GST\r\nEntry fees to monuments and Palaces\r\nAny meals not mentioned, Any transfers, Any insurance\r\nAnything not mentioned in the inclusions', 'Travel Validity\r\nThe dat