(180, 'Ladakh Tour Packages', 'Unleash Your Inner Explorer: Solo in Ladakh.', 'admin@joy.com', '1', '1746692205.jpg', '<p>Embark on a soul-stirring journey through the majestic landscapes of Ladakh with our specially curated 4N/5D Solo Traveler Package. Designed for adventure seekers and peace lovers alike, this trip offers the perfect blend of thrilling experiences and tranquil moments.</p>', '5', '4', 'Day : 1 Leh,Meet and greet on arrival at Kushok Bakula Rimpochee Leh airport and transfer to the hotel. Full day free for acclimatization. You are advised to stay and relax in the hotel. It‚Äôs important to take rest for 24 hours and wear heavy woolens. Overnight stay at  Leh. Why acclimatization is mandatory Leh is at an elevation of 11500 ft approximately above sea level. When you scale such heights your body may not get enough time to adapt to the changing surroundings. Though most people do not experience symptoms of Acute Mountain Sickness (AMS) in Leh. But it is advisable to be cautious and be alert for symptoms of AMS. The most common symptoms of AMS are headache disturbed sleep loss of appetite coughing and irregular breathing. One should avoid smoking tobacco alcohol and caffeine based drinks as they dehydrate the body and interfere with the process of acclimatization.,Day : 2 Leh City Sightseeing,After breakfast proceed for Leh city sightseeing which includes Hemis Monastery Oldest and richest monastery of Ladakh Thiksey Monastery Historic Buddhist monastery on a Hill Shey palace and Sindhu Ghat Rancho School ‚Äì subject to permission Hall of fame museum Indian army operated memorial & museum Shanti stupa Domed Buddhist temple on a hill and Leh Palace Centuries old mountaintop palace. Evening explore Leh market. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 3 Leh ‚Äì K Top ‚Äì Leh,After breakfast leave for K Top (2 hrs drive). Reach Khardungla pass @ 18380 ft (World‚Äôs highest motorable road). Enjoy scenic beauty from K Top. Back to hotel. Overnight stay at Leh.,Day : 4 L